  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Call and Commission"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Call and Commission"
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Jeremiah the son of Hilkiah, [one] of the priests
        who were in Anathoth in the land of Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'to whom the word of the Lord came during the thirteenth year (627
        b.c.) of the reign of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It came [to Jeremiah] also in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah,
        king of Judah, [continuing] until the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah
        the son of Josiah, king of Judah, [and continuing] until the exile of [the
        people of] Jerusalem in the fifth month (July-August, 586 b.c.).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now the word of the Lord came to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBefore I formed you in the womb I knew you [and approved of
        you as My chosen instrument],And before you were born I consecrated you [to
        Myself as My own];I have appointed you as a prophet to the nations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord God!Behold, I do not know how to speak,For
        I am [only] a young man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the Lord said to me,\u201CDo not say, \u2018I am [only] a young
        man,\u2019Because everywhere I send you, you shall go,And whatever I command
        you, you shall speak.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Do not be afraid of them [or their hostile faces],For I am with you
        [always] to protect you and deliver you,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord stretched out His hand and touched my mouth, and the
        Lord said to me,\u201CBehold (hear Me), I have put My words in your mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Almond Branch and Boiling Pot'
      title: The Almond Branch and Boiling Pot
      number: 10
      content: "See, I have appointed you this day over the nations and over the
        kingdoms,To uproot and break down,To destroy and to overthrow,To build and
        to plant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The word of the Lord came to me, saying, \u201CJeremiah, what do
        you see?\u201D And I said, \u201CI see the branch of an almond tree.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CYou have seen well, for I am [actively]
        watching over My word to fulfill it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The word of the Lord came to me a second time, saying, \u201CWhat
        do you see?\u201D And I said, \u201CI see a boiling pot, tilting away from
        the north [its mouth about to pour out on the south, on Judea].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201COut of the north the evil [which
        the prophets foretold as the result of national sin] will reveal itself and
        spill out on all the people of the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For, behold, I will call all the tribes of the kingdoms of the north,\u201D
        says the Lord; \u201Cand they will come and each one will set his throne
        at the entrance of the gates of Jerusalem, and against all its surrounding
        walls, and against all the cities of Judah [as My judicial act, the consequence
        of Judah\u2019s deliberate disobedience]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I will speak My judgments against them for all the wickedness of
        those who have abandoned (rejected) Me, offered sacrifices or burned incense
        to other gods, and worshiped the [idolatrous] works of their own hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But you [Jeremiah], gird up your loins [in preparation]! Get up and
        tell them all which I command you. Do not be distraught and break down at
        the sight of their [hostile] faces, or I will bewilder you before them and
        allow you to be overcome. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now behold, I have made you today like a fortified city and like
        an iron pillar and like bronze walls against the whole land\u2014against
        the [successive] kings of Judah, against its leaders, against its priests,
        and against the people of the land [giving you divine strength which no hostile
        power can overcome]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They will fight against you, but they will not [ultimately] prevail
        over you, for I am with you [always] to protect you and deliver you,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Apostasy"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Apostasy"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the word of the Lord came to me saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo and proclaim in the ears of Jerusalem, saying, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord,\u201CI remember [earnestly] the lovingkindness and devotion
        of your youth,Your time of betrothal [like that of a bride during the early
        years in Egypt and again at Sinai],When you followed Me in the wilderness,Through
        a land not sown.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  Israel was holy [something set apart from ordinary purposes, consecrated]
        to the Lord,The first fruits of His harvest [in which no outsider was allowed
        to share].All who ate of it [injuring Israel] became guilty;Evil came on
        them,\u201D says the Lord.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear the word of the Lord, O house of Jacob, and all the families
        of the house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CWhat injustice or unrighteousness did your
        fathers find in Me,That they have wandered far from MeAnd [habitually] walked
        after emptiness and futility and became empty?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They did not say, \u2018Where is the LordWho brought us up from the
        land of Egypt,Who led us through the wilderness,Through a land of deserts
        and of pits,Through a land of drought and of the deep darkness [of the shadow
        of death],Through a land that no man passed throughAnd where no man lived?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I brought you into a plentiful landTo eat its fruit and [enjoy] its
        good things.But you came and defiled My landAnd you made My inheritance repulsive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "[Even] the priests did not say, \u2018Where is the Lord?\u2019And
        those who deal with the law [given to Moses] did not know Me.The rulers and
        shepherds also transgressed against Me,And the prophets prophesied by [the
        authority and in the name of] BaalAnd walked after [idolatrous] things that
        did not benefit [them].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTherefore I will still contend (struggle) with you [by bringing
        judgment on you],\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAnd I will contend with your
        children\u2019s children.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CFor cross over to the coasts of Kittim (Cyprus) [to the west]
        and see,Send also to Kedar (Arabia) [to the east] and carefully observe and
        considerAnd see whether there has been such [a thing] as this!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Has a nation [ever] changed godsEven though they were not gods [but
        merely man-made objects]?But My people have exchanged their Glory (the true
        God)For that [man-made idol] which does not benefit [them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Be appalled, O heavens, at this;Be shocked and shudder with horror
        [at the behavior of the people],\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFor My people have committed two evils:They have abandoned
        (rejected) Me,The fountain of living water,And they have carved out their
        own cisterns,Broken cisternsThat cannot hold water.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIs Israel a servant? Is he a slave by birth?Why has he become
        a captive and a prey?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The young lions have roared at him,They have made their voices heard
        and roared loudly.And they have made his land a waste;His cities have been
        destroyed and are burned ruins, without inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover, the men of Memphis and Tahpanhes [as powerful enemies]Have
        shaved the crown of your head [to degrade you].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Have you not brought this on yourselfBy abandoning (rejecting) the
        Lord your GodWhen He led you in the way?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now what are you doing by going to Egypt [in search of an ally],To
        drink the [muddy] waters of the Nile?Or what are you doing by going to Assyria
        [in search of an ally],To drink the [muddy] waters of the Euphrates?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Your own wickedness will discipline you,And your desertion of the
        faith will punish you.Know therefore that it is an evil and bitter thingFor
        you to abandon (reject) the Lord your God,And for you to be indifferent to
        Me and dismiss the [reverent] fear of Me,\u201D says the Lord God of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFor long ago you broke your yoke [in deliberate disobedience]And
        tore off your bonds [of the law that I gave you];You said, \u2018I will not
        serve and obey You!\u2019For on every high hillAnd under every green treeYou
        have lain down [in idolatrous worship] like a [compliant] prostitute.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yet I had planted you [O house of Israel as] a choice vine,A completely
        faithful seed.How then have you turned against MeInto degenerate shoots of
        a foreign and wild vine [alien to Me]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For though you wash yourself with lyeAnd use much soap,The stain
        of your guilt is [still] before Me [and you are soiled and dirty],\u201D
        says the Lord God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CHow can you say, \u2018I am not defiled,I have not gone after
        [man-made gods like] the Baals\u2019?Look at your way in the valley;Know
        [without any doubt] what you have done!You are a swift and restless young
        [female] camel [in the heat of her passion] running here and there,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Or [you have the untamed and reckless nature of] a wild donkey accustomed
        to the wilderness,That sniffs the wind in her passion [for the scent of a
        mate].In her mating season who can restrain her?No males seeking her need
        to weary themselves;In her month they will find her [looking for them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "[Cease your mad running after idols to]Keep your feet from becoming
        bareAnd your throat from becoming dry;But you said, \u2018It is hopeless!For
        I have loved strangers and foreign gods,And I will walk after them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAs the thief is shamed when he is caught,So the house of Israel
        is shamed\u2014They, their kings, their leaders,Their priests, and their
        prophets\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Who say to a tree, \u2018You are my father,\u2019And to a stone,
        \u2018You gave me birth.\u2019For they have turned their backs to Me,And
        not their faces;But in the time of their trouble they will say,\u2018Arise
        [O Lord] and save us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But where are your godsWhich you made for yourself?Let them get up,
        if they can save youIn the time of your trouble!For [as many as] the number
        of your citiesAre your gods, O Judah. [Why do not your many man-made idols
        run to help you?]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CWhy do you complain and contend with Me?You have all rebelled
        (transgressed) against Me,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CIn vain I have punished your people [with the consequences
        of their disobedience];They received no insight from correction [and refused
        to change].Your [own] sword has devoured your prophetsLike a destroying lion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "O generation [that you are], consider and regard carefully the word
        of the Lord.Have I been a wilderness to Israel [like a land without food],A
        land of thick and deep darkness [like a path without light]?Why do My people
        say, \u2018We [have broken loose and we] are free to roam [at will];We will
        no longer come to You\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Can a virgin forget [to wear] her ornaments,Or a bride her attire
        [that identifies her as a married woman]?Yet My people have forgotten MeDays
        without number.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'How well you prepare your pathTo seek and obtain [adulterous] love!Even
        the most wicked of womenHave learned [indecent] ways from you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Also on your skirts is foundThe lifeblood of the innocent poor;You
        did not find them breaking in [a house].But in spite of all these things
        [your disobedience, your love of idolatry, your lack of compassion]\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Yet you keep saying, \u2018I am innocent;Surely His anger has turned
        away from me.\u2019Behold (listen very carefully), I will bring you to judgment
        and will plead my case against youBecause you say, \u2018I have not sinned.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Why do you go around and wander so muchChanging your way?Also, you
        will be shamed by EgyptAs you were shamed by Assyria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "From Egypt also you will come away [as captives]With your hands on
        your head;For the Lord has rejected those in whom you trust (confide),And
        you will not be successful with them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Polluted Land'
      title: The Polluted Land
      number: 1
      content: "  That is to say, \u201CIf a man divorces his wifeAnd she goes [away]
        from himAnd becomes another man\u2019s [wife],Will he return to her again?
        [Of course not!]Will not that land [where such a thing happened] be completely
        desecrated?But you [rebelled against Me and you] are a prostitute with many
        lovers;Yet you turn to Me.\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CLift up your eyes to the barren heights and see;Where have
        you not been violated?You sat by the road waiting [eagerly] for them [those
        man-made gods]Like an Arab [tribesman who waits to attack] in the desert,And
        you have desecrated the landWith your [vile] prostitution and your wickedness
        (disobedience to God).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore the showers have been withheld,And there has been no spring
        rain.Yet you have the forehead (appearance) of a prostitute;You refuse to
        be ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Will you not just now call out to Me,\u2018My Father, you were the
        guide and companion of my youth?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Faithless Israel'
      title: Faithless Israel
      number: 5
      content: "Will He be angry forever?Will He be indignant to the end?\u2019Behold,
        you have spoken,And you have done all the evil things [you could],And you
        have had your way and have carried out your wickedness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Moreover, the Lord said to me in the days of Josiah the king [of
        Judah], \u201CHave you seen what that faithless Israel has done\u2014how
        she went up on every high hill and under every green tree, and there she
        was a prostitute? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I thought, \u2018After she has done all these things she will return
        to Me\u2019; but she did not return, and her treacherous (faithless) sister
        Judah saw it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I saw [that even though Judah knew] that for all the acts of
        adultery (idolatry) of faithless Israel, I [the Lord] had sent her away and
        given her a certificate of divorce, yet her treacherous sister Judah was
        not afraid; but she went and was a prostitute also [following after idols]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Because of the thoughtlessness of Israel\u2019s prostitution [her
        immorality mattered little to her], she desecrated the land and committed
        adultery with [idols of] stones and trees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: God Invites Repentance'
      title: God Invites Repentance
      number: 10
      content: "Yet in spite of all this her treacherous sister Judah did not return
        to Me with her whole heart, but rather in [blatant] deception [she merely
        pretended obedience to King Josiah\u2019s reforms],\u201D declares the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u201CFaithless Israel has proved herself
        less guilty than treacherous Judah [a land of renegades]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Go and proclaim these words toward the north [where the ten tribes
        have been taken as captives] and say,\u2018Return, faithless Israel,\u2019
        says the Lord;\u2018I will not look on you in anger.For I am gracious and
        merciful,\u2019 says the Lord;\u2018I will not be angry forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Only understand fully and acknowledge your wickedness and guilt,That
        you have rebelled (transgressed) against the Lord your GodAnd have scattered
        your favors among strangers under every green tree,And you have not obeyed
        My voice,\u2019 says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Return, O faithless children [of the twelve tribes],\u2019
        says the Lord,\u2018For I am a master and husband to you,And I will take
        you [not as a nation, but individually]\u2014one from a city and two from
        a [tribal] family\u2014And I will bring you to Zion.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThen [in the final time] I will give you [spiritual] shepherds
        after My own heart, who will feed you with knowledge and [true] understanding. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "It will be in those days when you have [repented and] multiplied
        and increased in the land,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthey will no longer
        say, \u2018The ark of the covenant of the Lord.\u2019 It will not come to
        mind, nor will they [seriously] remember it, nor will they miss it, nor will
        it be made again [for instead of the ark, which symbolized My presence, I
        will be present]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "At that time they will call Jerusalem \u2018The Throne of the Lord,\u2019
        and all the nations will be gathered to it, to Jerusalem, for the name (renown)
        of the Lord; and they will not walk anymore after the stubbornness of their
        [own] evil heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In those days the house of Judah will walk with the house of Israel,
        and they will come together from the land of the north to the land that I
        gave your fathers as an inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen I said,\u2018How [gloriously and honorably] I would set
        you among My childrenAnd give you a pleasant land\u2014a wonderful heritage,The
        most beautiful inheritance of the nations!\u2019And I said, \u2018You shall
        call Me, My FatherAnd not turn away from following Me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Surely, as a wife treacherously (unfaithfully) leaves her husband,So
        you have dealt treacherously with Me,O house of Israel,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'A voice is heard on the barren heights,The weeping and pleading of
        the children of Israel,Because they have lost their way,They have [deliberately]
        forgotten the Lord their God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CReturn, O faithless sons,\u201D [says the Lord],\u201CI will
        heal your unfaithfulness.\u201D[They answer] \u201CBehold, we come to You,For
        You are the Lord our God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Truly, [the hope of salvation from] the hill [where idols are worshiped]
        is a deception,A tumult and noisy multitude on the mountains;Truly in the
        Lord our GodIs the salvation of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CBut the shameful act [of idolatry] has consumed the labor of
        our fathers since our youth\u2014their flocks and their herds, their sons
        and their daughters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Let us lie down in our shame, and let our dishonor and humiliation
        cover us; for we have sinned against the Lord our God, we and our fathers;
        from our youth even to this day we have not obeyed the voice of the Lord
        our God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judah Threatened with Invasion'
      title: Judah Threatened with Invasion
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf you will return, O Israel,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CIf
        you will return to Me,And if you will put away your detestable things and
        remove your man-made gods from My sight,And not stray or waver,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And if you swear [your oaths], \u2018As the Lord lives,\u2019In truth,
        in justice, and in righteousness,Then the nations will bless themselves in
        Him,And in Him they will glory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For this is what the Lord says to the men of Judah and to Jerusalem,\u201CPlow
        your uncultivated ground [for a season],And do not sow among thorns.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Circumcise (dedicate, sanctify) yourselves to the LordAnd remove
        the foreskin [sins] of your heart,Men of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem,Or
        else My wrath will go forth like fire [consuming all that gets in its way]And
        burn and there will be no one to quench it,Because of the evil of your acts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Declare in Judah and proclaim in Jerusalem, and say,\u201CBlow the
        trumpet in the land;Cry aloud and say,\u2018Assemble yourselves, and let
        us goInto the fortified cities.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Raise a banner toward Zion [to mark the way for those seeking safety
        inside Jerusalem\u2019s walls]!Seek refuge, do not stand [immobile],For I
        am bringing evil from the north (the army of Babylon),And great destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'A lion has left his lair,And a destroyer of nations is on his way.He
        has gone out from his placeTo desolate your land;Your cities will be in ruinsWithout
        an inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For this reason, put on sackcloth [for mourning],Lament (mourn with
        expressions of grief for the dead) and wail,For the fierce anger of the LordHas
        not turned back from us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIt shall come about in that day,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthat
        the heart and courage of the king will fail (be paralyzed), and also the
        heart of the princes; the priests will be appalled and the prophets will
        be astounded and horrified.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAlas, Lord God! Surely You have completely deceived
        and misled this people and Jerusalem, [for the prophets represented You as]
        saying [to Your people], \u2018You will have peace,\u2019 but [in fact] a
        sword reaches to their throat.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "In that time it will be said to this people and to Jerusalem, \u201CA
        scorching wind from the barren heights in the wilderness [comes at My command]
        against the daughter of My people\u2014not [a wind] to winnow and not to
        cleanse [from chaff, as when threshing, but] "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "a wind too strong and full for this comes at My word. Now I will
        also speak judgment against My people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, the enemy comes up like clouds,His chariots like the
        whirlwind;His horses are swifter than eagles.Woe (judgment is coming) to
        us, for we are ruined!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'O Jerusalem, wash your heart from wickedness,That you may be saved.How
        long will your wicked and immoral thoughtsLodge within you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For a voice declares from Dan [far in the north],And proclaims evil
        from Mount Ephraim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWarn the [neighboring] nations now [that our enemy is coming]!Announce
        to Jerusalem,\u2018Besiegers are coming from a far country,And they lift
        their voices and shout against the cities of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Like watchmen of a field they are against her on all sides,Because
        she has rebelled against Me,\u2019 says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Lament over Judah\u2019s Devastation"
      title: "Lament over Judah\u2019s Devastation"
      number: 18
      content: "Your ways and your deedsHave brought these things on you.This is
        your tragedy and doom; how bitter,How it has touched your heart!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My soul, my soul! I writhe in anguish and pain! Oh, the walls of
        my heart!My heart is pounding and throbbing within me;I cannot be silent,For
        you have heard, O my soul,The sound of the trumpet,The alarm of war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'News of one [terrible] disaster comes close after another,For the
        whole land is devastated;Suddenly my tents are spoiled and destroyed,My [tent]
        curtains [ruined] in a moment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'How long [O Lord] must I see the banner [marking the way for flight]And
        hear the sound of the trumpet [urging the people to run for safety]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor My people are stupid and foolish,\u201D [says the Lord
        to Jeremiah];\u201CThey do not know Me;They are foolish childrenAnd have
        no understanding.They are shrewd [enough] to do evil,But they do not know
        [how] to do good.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I looked at the earth [in my vision], and behold, it was [as at the
        time of creation] formless and void;And to the heavens, and they had no light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I looked at the mountains, and behold, they were trembling,And all
        the hills moved back and forth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I looked, and behold, there was no man,And all the birds of the air
        had fled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I looked, and behold, the fertile land was a wilderness,And all its
        cities were pulled downBefore the [presence of the] Lord, before His fierce
        anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore says the Lord,\u201CThe whole land shall be a desolation,Yet
        I will not cause total destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For this reason the earth shall mournAnd the heavens above shall
        become dark,Because I have spoken, I have decided,And I will not change my
        mind (relent), nor will I turn back from it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Every city runs away at the sound of the horsemen and archers.They
        go into the thickets and climb among the rocks;Every city is deserted,And
        no man lives in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And you, O desolate one, what will you do?Though you clothe yourself
        in scarlet,Though you adorn yourself with ornaments of gold,Though you enlarge
        your eyes with paint,You make yourself beautiful in vain.Your lovers (allies)
        despise you;They seek your life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For I heard a cry like a woman in labor,The anguish as of one giving
        birth to her first child,The cry of the Daughter of Zion (Jerusalem), who
        gasps for breath,Who stretches out her hands, saying,\u201CWoe is me [my
        judgment comes]! I faint [in fear] before the murderers.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jerusalem\u2019s Godlessness"
      title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Godlessness"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CRoam back and forth through the streets of Jerusalem,And
        look now and take note.And look in her open squares  To see if you can find
        a man [as Abraham sought in Sodom],One who is just, who [has integrity and
        moral courage and] seeks truth (faithfulness);Then I will pardon Jerusalem\u2014[for
        the sake of one uncompromisingly righteous person].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And though they say, \u2018As the Lord lives,\u2019Surely they swear
        [their oaths] falsely.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O Lord, do not Your eyes look for truth?You [have seen their faithless
        heart and] have stricken them,But they did not weaken;You have consumed them,But
        they refused to take correction or instruction.They have made their faces
        harder than rock;They have refused to repent and return to You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I said, \u201C[Surely] these are only the poor (uneducated);They
        are [sinfully] foolish and have no [spiritual] understanding,For they do
        not know the way of the LordOr the ordinance of their God [and the requirements
        of His just and righteous law].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I will go to the great [men]And speak to them,For they [must] know
        the way of the Lord,The ordinance of their God.\u201DBut [I found the reverse
        to be true, that] they too had all alike broken the yoke [of God\u2019s law]And
        had burst the bonds [of obedience to Him].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore a lion from the forest will kill them,A wolf of the deserts
        will destroy them,A leopard is watching their cities.Everyone who goes out
        of them shall be torn in pieces,Because their transgressions are many,Their
        desertions of faith are countless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWhy should I [overlook these offenses and] forgive you?Your
        children have abandoned (rejected) MeAnd sworn [their oaths] by those who
        are not gods.When I had fed them until they were full [and bound them to
        Me by a promise],They committed [spiritual] adultery,Assembling in troops
        at the houses of prostitutes (idols).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They were like well-fed, lusty stallions,Each one neighing after
        his neighbor\u2019s wife.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shall I not punish them [for these things]?\u201D says the Lord;\u201CShall
        I not avenge MyselfOn a nation such as this?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGo up through the rows of Jerusalem\u2019s vineyards and destroy
        [them],But do not completely destroy everything.Strip away her branches and
        the tendrils [of her vines],For they are not the Lord\u2019s.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the house of Israel and the house of JudahHave dealt very treacherously
        (faithlessly) with Me,\u201D declares the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They have lied about and denied the LordBy saying, \u201CIt is not
        He [who speaks through His prophets];Misfortune and evil shall not come on
        us,Nor will we see war or famine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Judgment Proclaimed'
      title: Judgment Proclaimed
      number: 13
      content: "The prophets are like the wind [their prophecy will not come to pass],And
        the word [of God] is not in them.In this manner it will be done to them [as
        they prophesied, not to us].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord God of hosts,\u201CBecause you [people]
        have spoken this word,Behold, I am making My words a fire in your mouth [Jeremiah]And
        this people wood, and My words will consume them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Behold, I am bringing a nation against you from far away, O house
        of Israel,\u201D says the Lord.\u201CIt is a mighty and enduring nation,It
        is an ancient nation,A nation whose language you do not know,Whose words
        you do not comprehend.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Their quiver is [filled with the dead] like an open grave;They are
        all mighty men [heroes of their nation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They will consume your harvest and [eat up] your bread;They will
        consume your sons and your daughters;They will consume your flocks and your
        herds;They will consume your vines and your fig trees.With the sword they
        will break down and demolish your fortified cities in which you trust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut even in those days,\u201D says the Lord, \u201CI will not
        totally destroy you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "It will come about when your people say, \u2018Why has the Lord our
        God done all these things to us?\u2019 then you shall answer them, \u2018As
        you have abandoned (rejected) Me,\u2019 [says the Lord,] \u2018and have served
        strange and foreign gods in your land, so you will serve strangers in a land
        that is not yours.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CDeclare this in the house of JacobAnd proclaim it in Judah,
        saying:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018Now hear this, O foolish people without heart,Who have eyes
        but do not see,Who have ears but do not hear.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Do you not fear Me?\u2019 says the Lord.\u2018Do you not tremble
        [in awe] in My presence?For I have placed the sand as a boundary for the
        sea,An eternal decree and a perpetual barrier beyond which it cannot pass.Though
        the waves [of the sea] toss and break, yet they cannot prevail [against the
        sand ordained to hold them back];Though the waves and the billows roar, yet
        they cannot cross over [the barrier].[Is not such a God to be feared?]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But this people has a stubborn heart and a rebellious will [that
        draws them away from Me];They have turned away and have gone [into idolatry].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They do not say in their heart,\u201CLet us now fear and worship
        the Lord our God [with profound awe and reverence],Who gives rain in its
        season,Both the autumn and the spring rain,Who keeps for usThe appointed
        weeks of the harvest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Your wickedness has turned these [blessings] away,And your sins have
        withheld good [harvests] from you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For wicked men are found among My people,They watch like fowlers
        who lie in wait;They set a trap,They catch men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'As a cage is full of birds,So are their houses full of deceit and
        treachery;Therefore they have become influential and rich.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They are fat and they are sleek (prosperous),They excel in acts of
        wickedness;They do not plead the cause,The cause of the orphan, so that they
        [the wicked] may prosper,And they do not defend the rights of the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Shall I not punish them [for these things]?\u2019 says the Lord.\u2018Shall
        I not avenge MyselfOn such a nation as this?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CAn appalling and horrible thing [bringing desolation and destruction]Has
        come to pass in the land:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The prophets prophesy falsely,And the priests rule on their own authority;And
        My people love [to have] it so!But what will you do when the end comes?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Destruction of Jerusalem Impending'
      title: Destruction of Jerusalem Impending
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CRun for safety, you children of Benjamin,Out of the midst
        of Jerusalem!And blow a trumpet in Tekoa [in Judah]And raise a signal-fire
        in Beth-haccherem [near Jerusalem];For evil is looking down [with eager anticipation]
        from the north,And great destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will destroy the Daughter of Zion (Jerusalem), the lovely and delicate
        one [so like a luxurious pasture].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shepherds with their flocks will come against her;They will pitch
        their tents all around her;They will pasture, each one in his place [eating
        up all her rich grasses].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "[They shout], \u2018Prepare for war against her;Arise, let us [take
        her by surprise and] attack her at noon.But alas, the daylight pales,The
        evening shadows grow long.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Arise, let us [awaken to] attack her at nightAnd destroy her [fortified]
        palaces!\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord of hosts has said,\u201CCut down her treesAnd build
        a siege [mound] against Jerusalem.This is the city which must be punished;There
        is nothing but oppression inside her [walls].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'As a fountain springs up and pours out its fresh waters,So she [continually]
        pours out her fresh wickedness.Violence and destruction are heard inside
        her [walls];Sickness and wounds are always before Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Be wise and be warned, O Jerusalem,Or I will be alienated from you,And
        make you a desolation,An uninhabited land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts,\u201CThey will thoroughly gather like
        [fruit on] a vine what is left of Israel;Pass your hand [over the vine] again
        and again [Babylon, tool of destruction] like a grape gatherer,Over the branches
        [stripping the tendrils off the vine].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'To whom shall I (Jeremiah) speak and give warningThat they may hear?Behold,
        their ears are closed [absolutely deaf to God]And they cannot listen.Behold,
        the word of the Lord has become a reprimand and an object of scorn to them;They
        have no delight in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But I am full of the wrath (judgment) of the Lord;I am tired of restraining
        it.\u201C[I will] pour it out on the children in the streetAnd on the young
        men gathered together;For both the husband and wife shall be taken,The aged
        and the very old [though full of days they are not exempt from judgment].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Their houses shall be turned over to others,Their fields and their
        wives together;For I will stretch out My handAgainst the inhabitants of the
        land,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFor from the least of them even to the greatest of them,Everyone
        is greedy for [unfair] gain;And from the prophet even to the priestEveryone
        deals deceitfully.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They have treated superficially the [bloody] broken wound of My people,Saying,
        \u2018Peace, peace,\u2019When there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Were they ashamed because they had committed disgusting and vile
        things?No, they were not at all ashamed;They did not even know how to blush
        [at their idolatry].Therefore they will fall among those who fall;At the
        time that I punish themThey will be overthrown,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CStand by the roads and look; ask for the
        ancient paths,Where the good way is; then walk in it,And you will find rest
        for your souls.But they said, \u2018We will not walk in it!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I have set watchmen (prophets) over you,Saying, \u2018Listen and
        pay attention to the [warning] sound of the trumpet!\u2019But they said,
        \u2018We will not listen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore hear, O [Gentile] nations,And see, O congregation, what
        [vengeful act] is to be done to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hear, O earth: behold, I am bringing disaster on this people,The
        fruit of their schemes,Because they have not listened and paid attention
        to My words,And as for My law, they have rejected it also.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For what purpose does frankincense come to Me from ShebaAnd the sweet
        cane from a distant land?Your burnt offerings are not acceptableAnd your
        sacrifices are not sweet and pleasing to Me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Enemy from the North'
      title: The Enemy from the North
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord,\u201CBehold, I am laying stumbling
        blocks before this people.The fathers and the sons togetherWill stumble against
        them;The neighbor and his friend will perish.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CBehold, a people is coming from the north
        country,And a great nation shall be stirred up and put into action from the
        remote parts of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They seize bow and spear;They are cruel and inhuman and have no mercy.Their
        voice sounds like the roaring sea;They ride [in formation] on horses,Arrayed
        as a man for battleAgainst you, O Daughter of Zion (Jerusalem)!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'We have heard the report of it;Our hands become limp and helpless.Anguish
        has gripped us,Pain like that of a woman in childbirth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Do not go out into the fieldNor walk on the road,For the enemy is
        armed with the sword;Terror is on every side.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'O daughter of my people [says Jeremiah],Clothe yourself in sackcloth
        and wallow in ashes;Mourn [aloud] as for an only son,A most bitter cry [of
        sorrow and regret],For suddenly the destroyer will come upon us [on both
        prophet and people].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI [the Lord] have set you as an assayer [O Jeremiah] and as
        a tester [of the ore] of My people,That you may know and analyze their acts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They are all the worst [kind] of [stiff-necked, godless] rebels,Going
        around spreading slander.They are [not gold and silver ore, but] bronze and
        iron;They are all corrupt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The bellows blow fiercely,The lead is consumed by the fire;In vain
        they continue refining,But the wicked are not separated and removed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: They call them rejected silver [only dross, without value],Because
        the Lord has rejected them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Message at the Temple Gate'
      title: Message at the Temple Gate
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CStand in the gate of the Lord\u2019s house and proclaim there
        this word and say, \u2018Hear the word of the Lord, all you of Judah who
        enter by these gates to worship the Lord.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CChange your
        ways and your behavior, and I will let you live in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Do not trust in the deceptive and lying words [of the false prophets
        who claim that Jerusalem will be protected by God because of the temple],
        saying, \u2018This is the temple of the Lord, the temple of the Lord, the
        temple of the Lord.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For if you thoroughly change your ways and your behavior, if you
        thoroughly and honestly practice justice between a man and his neighbor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'if you do not oppress the transient and the foreigner, the orphan,
        or the widow, and do not shed innocent blood [by oppression and by unjust
        judicial murders] in Jerusalem, nor follow after other gods to your own ruin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then I will let you live in this place, in the land that I gave to
        your fathers [to live in] forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBehold, you are trusting in deceptive and useless words that
        bring no benefit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will you steal, murder, commit adultery, swear [oaths] falsely, offer
        sacrifices or burn incense to Baal, and follow after other gods that you
        have not known, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and [then dare to] come and stand before Me in this house, which
        is called by My Name, and say, \u2018We are protected and set free [by this
        act of religious ritual]!\u2019\u2014only to go on with this wickedness and
        these disgusting and loathsome things? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Has this house, which is called by My Name, become a den of robbers
        in your eyes [a place of retreat for you between acts of violence]? Behold,
        I Myself have seen it,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut go now to My place which was in Shiloh [in Ephraim], where
        I first set My Name, and see what I did to it because of the wickedness of
        My people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And now, because you have done all these things,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cand I spoke [persistently] to you, even rising up early and speaking,
        but you did not listen, and I called you but you did not answer, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'therefore, I will do to this house (the temple) which is called by
        My Name, in which you trust, and to the place which I gave you and your fathers,
        just as I did to Shiloh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will cast you out of My sight, as I have cast out all your brothers
        (relatives through Jacob), all the descendants of Ephraim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CTherefore, do not pray for this people [of Judah] or lift up
        a cry or entreaty for them or make intercession to Me, for I do not hear
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do you not see what they are doing in the cities of Judah and in
        the streets of Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The children gather wood, the fathers kindle the fire, and the women
        knead the dough to make cakes for the queen of heaven; and they pour out
        drink offerings to other gods that they may offend and provoke Me to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Do they offend and provoke Me to anger?\u201D says the Lord. \u201CIs
        it not themselves [they offend], to their own shame?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God, \u201CBehold, My anger and My wrath
        will be poured out on this place, on man and beast, on the trees of the field
        and the fruit of the ground; and it will burn and [the fire will] not be
        quenched.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CAdd your burnt
        offerings to your sacrifices and eat the meat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For in the day that I brought them out of the land of Egypt, I did
        not speak to your fathers or command them concerning burnt offerings or sacrifices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But this thing I did command them: \u2018Listen to and obey My voice,
        and I will be your God, and you shall be My people; and you will walk in
        all the way which I command you, so that it may be well with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But they did not obey Me or bend their ear [to hear Me], but followed
        the counsels and the stubbornness of their [own] evil heart (mind), and [they
        turned and] went backward instead of forward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Since the day that your fathers came out of the land of Egypt until
        this day, I have [persistently] sent you all My servants the prophets, sending
        them daily, early [and late]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Yet they did not listen to Me and obey Me or bend their ear [to hear
        Me], but stiffened their neck; they did more evil and behaved worse than
        their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CYou shall speak all these words to them, but they will not
        listen to you; and you shall [also] call to them, but they will not answer
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You shall say to them, \u2018This is the nation that did not obey
        the voice of the Lord their God or accept correction and warning; truth and
        faithfulness have perished and have completely vanished from their mouths.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Cut off your hair [your crown, O Jerusalem] and throw it away,And
        take up a mournful cry on the barren heights,For the Lord has rejected and
        abandonedThe generation of His wrath.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For the children of Judah have done evil in My sight,\u201D says
        the Lord; \u201Cthey have set their disgusting and shamefully vile things
        in the house which is called by My Name, to defile it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "They have built the high places of Topheth, which is in the Valley
        of Ben-hinnom (son of Hinnom), to burn their sons and their daughters in
        the fire [to honor Molech, the fire god]\u2014which I did not command, nor
        did it come into My heart (mind).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, the days are coming,\u201D declares the
        Lord, \u201Cwhen it will no longer be called Topheth or the Valley of Ben-hinnom,
        but the Valley of the Slaughter, for [in bloody warfare] they will bury [the
        dead] in Topheth until there is no more room. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the dead bodies of this people will be food for the birds of
        the air and for the beasts of the earth and no one will frighten them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then I will cause the voices of joy and gladness, and the voices
        of the bridegroom and the bride to vanish from the cities of Judah and from
        the streets of Jerusalem; for the land will become a ruin\u2014a wasteland."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sin and Treachery of Judah'
      title: The Sin and Treachery of Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt that time,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthey [the Babylonian
        army] will bring out from their graves the bones of the kings of Judah, the
        bones of its princes, the bones of the priests, the bones of the prophets,
        and the bones of the inhabitants of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They will [carelessly scatter and] spread them out before the sun
        and the moon and all the host of heaven, which the dead have loved and which
        they have served, and which they have walked after and which they have sought,
        and which they have worshiped. They will not be gathered or be buried; they
        will be like dung on the face of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And death will be chosen rather than life by all the remnant of those
        who remain of this evil family (nation), who remain in all the places to
        which I have driven them,\u201D says the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CMoreover [Jeremiah], you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says
        the Lord,\u201CDo men fall and not rise up again?Does one turn away [from
        God] and not repent and return [to Him]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why then has this people of JerusalemTurned away with a perpetual
        turning away [from Me]?They hold tightly to deceit (idolatry);They refuse
        to repent and return [to God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I have listened and heard,But they have spoken what is not right;No
        man repented of his wickedness,Saying, \u2018What have I done?\u2019Everyone
        turns to his [individual] course,As the horse rushes like a torrent into
        battle.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Even the stork in the skyKnows her seasons [of migration],And the
        turtledove, the swallow and the craneObserve the time of their return.But
        My people do not knowThe law of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CHow can you say, \u2018We are wise,And the law of the Lord
        is with us [and we are learned in its language and teachings]\u2019?Behold,
        [the truth is that] the lying pen of the scribesHas made the law into a lie
        [a mere code of ceremonial observances].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The wise men are shamed,They are dismayed and caught.Behold, they
        have [manipulated and] rejected the [truth in the] word of the Lord,And what
        kind of wisdom and insight do they have?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore I will give their wives to othersAnd their fields to new
        owners;Because from the least even to the greatestEveryone is greedy for
        [unjust] gain;From the prophet even to the priestEveryone practices deceit
        and deals in corruption.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For they have treated the brokenness of the daughter of My people
        superficially,Saying, \u2018Peace, peace,\u2019When there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Were they ashamed because of the extremely disgusting and shamefully
        vile things they had done?They were not at all ashamed,And they did not know
        how to blush.Therefore, they shall fall among those who fall;At the time
        of their punishment they shall be overthrown,\u201DSays the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI will gather and snatch them away [utterly consuming them],\u201D
        says the Lord.\u201CThere will be no grapes on the vine,Nor figs on the fig
        tree,And even the leaf will wither;And the things that I have given them
        will pass away [by the hand of those whom I have appointed].\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Why are we sitting still [the people wonder]?Assemble yourselves,
        and let us enter the fortified citiesAnd let us die there,For the Lord our
        God has decreed our ruinAnd given us bitter and poisonous water to drink,Because
        we have sinned against the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'We waited for peace and salvation, but no good came,And for a time
        of healing, but behold, terror!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The snorting of [Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s] horses is heard from Dan
        [on Palestine\u2019s northern border].At the sound of the neighing of his
        strong stallionsThe whole land quakes;For they come and devour the land and
        all that is in it,The city and those who live in it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CFor behold, I am sending serpents among you,Vipers which cannot
        be charmed,And they will bite you,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Oh, that I (Jeremiah) could find comfort from my sorrow [for my grief
        is beyond healing],My heart is sick and faint within me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Behold, [hear the sound of] the cry of the daughter of my people
        from the distant land [of Babylon]:\u201CIs not the Lord in Zion? Is not
        her King within her?\u201D[But the Lord answers] \u201CWhy have they provoked
        Me to anger with their carved images and with foreign idols?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe harvest is past, the summer has ended and the gathering
        of fruit is over,But we are not saved,\u201D [comes the voice of the people
        again].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the brokenness of the daughter of my people I (Jeremiah) am broken;I
        mourn, anxiety has gripped me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Is there no balm in Gilead?Is there no physician there?Why then has
        not the [spiritual] health of the daughter of my people been restored?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Lament over Zion'
      title: A Lament over Zion
      number: 1
      content: '  Oh that my head were watersAnd my eyes a fountain of tears,That
        I might weep day and nightFor the slain of the daughter of my people!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Oh that I had in the wildernessA lodging place (a mere shelter) for
        wayfaring men,That I might leave my peopleAnd go away from them!For they
        are all adulterers [worshiping idols instead of the Lord],[They are] an assembly
        of treacherous men [of weak character, men without integrity].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CThey bend their tongue like their bow;[Their] lies and not
        truth prevail and grow strong in the land;For they proceed from evil to evil,And
        they do not know and understand and acknowledge Me,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CLet everyone beware of his neighborAnd do not trust any brother.For
        every brother is a supplanter [like Jacob, a deceiver, ready to grab his
        brother\u2019s heel],And every neighbor goes around as a slanderer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Everyone deceives and mocks his neighborAnd does not speak the truth.They
        have taught their tongue to speak lies;They exhaust themselves with sin and
        cruelty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Your dwelling is in the midst of deceit [oppression upon oppression
        and deceit upon deceit];Through deceit they refuse to know (understand) Me,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord of hosts,\u201CBehold, I will refine
        them [through suffering] and test them;For how else should I deal with the
        daughter of My people?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their tongue is a murderous arrow;It speaks deceit;With his mouth
        one speaks peace to his neighbor,But in his heart he lays traps and waits
        in ambush for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shall I not punish them for these things?\u201D says the Lord.\u201CShall
        I not avenge MyselfOn such a nation as this?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CI will take up a weeping and wailing for the mountains,And
        a [funeral] dirge for the pastures of the wilderness,Because they are burned
        up and desolated so that no one passes through [them];Nor can anyone hear
        the lowing of cattle.Both the birds of the air and the beasts have fled;
        they are gone.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I will make Jerusalem a heap of ruins,A haunt and dwelling place
        of jackals;And I will make the cities of Judah a desolation, without inhabitant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Who is the wise man who may understand this [without any doubt]?
        To whom has the mouth of the Lord spoken, so that he may declare it? Why
        is the land ruined, laid waste like a wilderness, so that no one passes through? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The Lord said, \u201CBecause they have turned away from My law which
        I set before them, and have not listened to and obeyed My voice nor walked
        in accordance with it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "but have walked stubbornly after their [own] heart and after the
        Baals, as their fathers taught them,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201Cbehold,
        I will feed them, this people, with wormwood and give them bitter and poisonous
        water to drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will [also] scatter them among nations that neither they nor their
        fathers have known, and I will send the sword after them until I have annihilated
        them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts,\u201CConsider and call for the mourning
        women to come;Send for the wailing women to come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Let them hurry and take up a wailing for us,That our eyes may shed
        tearsAnd our eyelids flow with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For a sound of wailing is heard [coming] from Zion:\u2018How we are
        ruined!We are greatly perplexed and utterly shamed,Because we have left the
        land,Because they have torn down our dwellings.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now hear the word of the Lord, O you women,And let your ear hear
        the word of His mouth;Teach your daughters a song of mourning,And each one
        [teach] her neighbor a dirge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For death has come up through our windows;It has entered our palaces,Cutting
        off the children from the streetsAnd the young men from the town squares.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Speak, \u201CThus says the Lord,\u2018The dead bodies of men will
        fall like dung on the open field,And like sheaves [of grain] behind the reaper,And
        no one will gather them.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u201CLet not the one who is wise and skillful
        boast in his insight; let not the one who is mighty and powerful boast in
        his strength; let not the one who is rich boast in his [temporal satisfactions
        and earthly] abundance; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "but let the one who boasts boast in this, that he understands and
        knows Me [and acknowledges Me and honors Me as God and recognizes without
        any doubt], that I am the Lord who practices lovingkindness, justice and
        righteousness on the earth, for in these things I delight,\u201D says the
        Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cwhen
        I will punish all who are circumcised [physically] and yet uncircumcised
        [spiritually]\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Egypt and Judah, and Edom and the sons of Ammon, and Moab and all
        those who live in the desert who clip off the hair on their temples; for
        all these nations are uncircumcised (sinful, impure), and all the house of
        Israel are uncircumcised in heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Satire on Idolatry'
      title: A Satire on Idolatry
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear the word which the Lord speaks to you, O house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CDo not learn the way of the [pagan] nations,And
        do not be terrified and distressed by the signs of the heavensAlthough the
        pagans are terrified by them;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the customs and decrees of the peoples are [mere] delusion [exercises
        in futility];It is only wood which one cuts from the forest [to make a god],The
        work of the hands of the craftsman with the axe or cutting tool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They adorn the idol with silver and with gold;They fasten it with
        hammers and nailsSo that it will not fall apart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They are like scarecrows in a cucumber field;They cannot speak;They
        have to be carried,Because they cannot walk!Do not be afraid of them,For
        they can do no harm or evil,Nor can they do any good.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There is none like You, O Lord;You are great, and great is Your mighty
        and powerful name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who would not fear You, O King of the nations?For it is appropriate
        and it is Your due!For among all the wise men of the nationsAnd in all their
        kingdoms,There is none like You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But they are altogether irrational and stupid and foolish  In their
        discipline of delusion\u2014their idol is [only] wood [it is ridiculous,
        empty and worthless]!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Silver that has been beaten [into plates] is brought from Tarshish,And
        gold from Uphaz,The work of the craftsman and of the hand of the goldsmith;Violet
        and purple are their clothing;They are all the work of skilled men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the Lord is the true God and the God who is Truth;He is the living
        God and the everlasting King.The earth quakes and shudders at His wrath,And
        the nations are not able to endure His indignation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "In this manner you shall say to them, \u201CThe gods that did not
        make the heavens and the earth will perish from the earth and from under
        the heavens.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'God made the earth by His power;He established the world by His wisdomAnd
        by His understanding and skill He has stretched out the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When He utters His voice, there is a tumult of waters in the heavens,And
        He causes the clouds and the mist to ascend from the end of the earth;He
        makes lightning for the rain,And brings out the wind from His treasuries
        and from His storehouses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Every man has become [like a brute] irrational and stupid, without
        knowledge [of God];Every goldsmith is shamed by his carved idols;For his
        molten images are frauds and lies,And there is no breath in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They are worthless and devoid of promise, a work of delusion and
        mockery;In their time of [trial and] punishment they will perish [without
        hope].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The Portion of Jacob [the true God on whom Israel has a claim] is
        not like these;For He is the Designer and Maker of all things,And Israel
        is the tribe of His inheritance [and He will not fail them]\u2014The Lord
        of hosts is His name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Gather up your bundle [of goods] from the ground,You who live under
        siege.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For thus says the Lord;\u201CBehold, I am slinging out at this time
        the people of this land,And will cause them [great] distress,That they may
        find it [to be as I have said].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWoe to me because of my [spiritual] brokenness!\u201D [says
        Jeremiah, speaking for the nation.]\u201CMy wound is incurable.\u201DBut
        I said, \u201CSurely this sickness and suffering and grief are mine,And I
        must bear it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My tent is destroyed,And all my [tent] cords are broken;My children
        have been taken from me [as captives] and are no more.There is no one to
        stretch out my tent againAnd to set up my [tent] curtains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the shepherds [of the people] have become [like brutes,] irrational
        and stupid,And have not searched for the Lord  or asked about Him or realized
        their need for Him;Therefore they have not been wise and have not prospered,And
        all their flocks are scattered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The sound of a report! Behold, [the invader] comes\u2014A great commotion
        from the country of the north (Babylonia)\u2014To make the cities of JudahA
        desolation, a haunt and dwelling place of jackals.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'O Lord, I know that the path of [life of] a man is not in himself;It
        is not within [the limited ability of] man [even one at his best] to choose
        and direct his steps [in life].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "O Lord, correct me [along with Your people], but with mercy and in
        just measure\u2014Not in Your anger, or You will crush me and bring me to
        nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Pour out Your wrath on the nations that do not know nor recognize
        YouAnd on the families that do not call Your name.For they have devoured
        Jacob;They have devoured him and consumed himAnd made his land a desolate
        waste.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Broken Covenant'
      title: The Broken Covenant
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHear the words of this [solemn] covenant, and speak to the
        men of Judah and to the people of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u201CCursed
        is the man who does not heed the words of this covenant "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "which I commanded your fathers at the time that I brought them out
        of the land of Egypt, from the iron furnace, saying, \u2018Listen to My voice
        and do according to all that I command you. So you shall be My people, and
        I will be your God,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "that I may complete the oath which I swore to your fathers, to give
        them a land [of plenty] flowing with milk and honey, as it is this day.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D
        Then I answered, \u201CAmen (so be it), O Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u201CProclaim all these words in the cities
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem: \u2018Hear the words of this [solemn]
        covenant and do them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For I solemnly warned your fathers at the time that I brought them
        up from the land of Egypt, even to this day, warning them persistently, saying,
        \u201CObey My voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Yet they did not obey or incline their ear [to listen to Me], but
        everyone walked in the stubborn way of his [own] evil heart. Therefore I
        brought on them all [the suffering threatened in] the words of this covenant,
        which I commanded them to do, but they did not.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CA conspiracy has been found among
        the men of Judah and among the people of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They have returned to the wickedness of their ancestors who refused
        to hear My words; they have followed other gods [in order] to serve them.
        The house of Israel and the house of Judah have broken My [solemn] covenant
        which I made with their fathers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord, \u201CBehold I am bringing disaster
        and suffering on them which they will not be able to escape; though they
        cry to Me, I will not listen to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the cities of Judah and the people of Jerusalem will go and
        cry to the [man-made] gods to whom they burn incense, but they cannot save
        them in the time of their disaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For [as many as] the number of your cities are your gods, O Judah;
        and [as many as] the number of the streets of Jerusalem are the altars you
        have set up to the shameful thing, altars to burn incense to Baal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTherefore do not pray for this people, nor lift up a cry or
        prayer for them, for I shall not listen when they cry to Me in the time of
        their disaster.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "What right has My beloved [to be] in My houseWhen she has done many
        vile things and acted treacherously [over and over again]?Can vows and the
        meat of your sacrifices remove your wickedness from you and cancel the consequences
        of your sin,So that you can [escape your judgment and] rejoice?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The Lord [acknowledged you once as worthy and] called your name,\u201CA
        green olive tree, fair and beautiful in fruit and form\u201D;But with the
        roar of a great tempestHe has set fire to it,And its branches are worthless.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Plots against Jeremiah'
      title: Plots against Jeremiah
      number: 17
      content: 'For the Lord of hosts, who planted you, has pronounced evil and horror
        against you because of the evil of the house of Israel and of the house of
        Judah, which they have done to provoke Me [to anger] by offering sacrifices
        and burning incense to Baal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the Lord gave me knowledge [of their plot], and I knew it;So
        You [O Lord] revealed their deeds to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But I was like a gentle and tame lamb brought to the slaughter;And
        I did not know that they had devised plots and schemes against me, saying,\u201CLet
        us destroy the tree with its fruit;Let us cut him off from the land of the
        living,That his name be remembered no longer.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But, O Lord of hosts, who judges righteously,Who tests the feelings
        and the heart (mind),Let me see Your vengeance on them,For to You I have
        committed my cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord regarding the men of Anathoth, who seek
        your life, saying, \u201CDo not prophesy in the name of the Lord, so that
        you will not die by our hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord of hosts, \u201CBehold, I am about
        to punish them. Their young men will die by the sword, their sons and their
        daughters will die by famine; "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and there will be no remnant [of the conspirators] left, for I will
        bring disaster and horror on the men of Anathoth in the year of their punishment.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 1
      content: '  You, O Lord are [uncompromisingly] righteous and consistently just
        when I plead my case with You;Yet let me discuss issues of justice with You:Why
        has the way of the wicked prospered?Why are those who deal in treachery (deceit)
        at ease and thriving?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You have planted them, they have also taken root;They grow, they
        have even produced fruit.You are honored by their [hypocritical] lipsBut
        [You are] far from their heart and mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But You, O Lord, know me [and understand my devotion to You];You
        see me;And You examine the attitude of my heart toward You.Drag out the faithless
        like sheep for the slaughter [O Lord]And set them apart for the day of slaughter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "How long must the land mournAnd the grass of the countryside wither?Because
        of the wickedness and hypocrisy of those who live in it,The beasts and the
        birds are consumed and are swept away [by the drought],Because men [mocking
        me] have said, \u201CHe will not [live long enough to] see [what happens
        at] our final end.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "[The Lord rebukes Jeremiah for his impatience, saying] \u201CIf you
        have raced with men on foot and they have tired you out,Then how can you
        compete with horses?If you fall down in a land of peace [where you feel secure],Then
        how will you do [among the lions] in the [flooded] thicket beside the Jordan?  "
      comments: []
    - name: "6: God\u2019s Answer"
      title: "God\u2019s Answer"
      number: 6
      content: "For even your [tribal] brothers and the household of your father,Even
        they have dealt treacherously (unfaithfully) with you;Indeed they are [like
        a pack of hounds] howling after you.Do not believe them, although they may
        say kind words and promise you good things.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI have abandoned My house,I have given up My [precious] inheritance
        (Judah);I have given the [dearly] beloved of My lifeInto the hands of her
        enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My inheritance has become to MeLike a lion in the forest;She has
        raised her voice and roared against Me;So I have come to [treat her as if
        I] hate her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Is My inheritance like a speckled bird of prey to Me [unlike the
        others]?Are the birds of prey (enemies) surrounding her on every side?Go,
        gather all the [wild] beasts of the field;Bring them to devour [her]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Many shepherds (invaders) have destroyed My vineyard (Judah),They
        have trampled My field underfoot;They have made My pleasant fieldA desolate
        wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They have made it a wasteland,Desolate, it mourns before Me;The whole
        land has been made a wasteland,Because no man takes it to heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Destroyers have comeOn all the caravan roads in the desert,For the
        sword of the Lord (Babylon) is devouringFrom one end of the land even to
        the other;No one has peace or a way of escape.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They have planted wheat but have reaped thorns;They have exhausted
        themselves but without profit.So be ashamed of your harvestBecause of the
        fierce and raging anger of the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the Lord regarding all My evil neighbors (Gentile nations)
        who strike at the inheritance which I have granted to My people Israel, \u201CBehold,
        I will uproot them from their land and I will uproot the house of Judah from
        among them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And it shall come about that after I have uprooted them, I will return
        and have compassion on them; and I will bring them back again, each one to
        his inheritance and each one to his land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And if these [neighboring nations] will diligently learn the ways
        of My people, to swear by My Name, saying, \u2018As the Lord lives\u2019\u2014even
        as they taught My people to swear by Baal, then they will be built up among
        My people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if [any nation] will not listen and obey, I will [completely]
        uproot and destroy that nation, says the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ruined Waistband'
      title: The Ruined Waistband
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus the Lord said to me, \u201CGo and buy yourself a linen waistband
        and put it on your loins, but do not put it in water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought the waistband according to the word of the Lord and put
        it on my loins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me a second time, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGet up and take the waistband that you have bought, which is
        [wrapped] around your loins, and go to the [river] Euphrates and hide it
        there in a crevice of the rock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So I went and hid it by the Euphrates, as the Lord had commanded
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And after many days the Lord said to me, \u201CGet up, go to the
        Euphrates and get the waistband which I commanded you to hide there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then I went to the Euphrates and dug, and I took the waistband from
        the place where I had hidden it. And behold, the waistband was decayed and
        ruined; it was completely worthless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, \u2018In this same way I shall destroy
        the pride of Judah and the great pride of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "These wicked and malevolent people, who refuse to listen to My words,
        who walk in the stubborn way of their heart and have followed other gods
        [which are nothing\u2014just man-made carvings] to serve them and to worship
        them, let them be just like this waistband which is completely worthless. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Captivity Threatened'
      title: Captivity Threatened
      number: 11
      content: "For as the waistband clings to the body of a man, so I caused the
        whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah to cling to Me,\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018that they might be for Me a people, a name, a praise,
        and a glory; but they did not listen and obey.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore you are to speak this word to them, \u2018Thus says
        the Lord, the God of Israel, \u201CEvery jar should be filled with wine.\u201D\u2009\u2019
        The people will say to you, \u2018Do we not already know that every jar should
        be filled with wine?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CBehold, I am about
        to fill with drunkenness all the people of this land, even the kings who
        sit on David\u2019s throne, the priests, the prophets and all the people
        of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will smash them one against another, both the fathers and the sons
        together,\u201D says the Lord. \u201CI shall destroy them [nothing will restrain
        Me]; I will not show pity nor be sorry nor have compassion.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Listen and pay close attention, do not be haughty and overconfident,For
        the Lord has spoken [says Jeremiah].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Give glory to the Lord your God,Before He brings darknessAnd before
        your feet stumbleOn the dark and shadowy mountains,And while you are longing
        for lightHe turns it into the shadow of death,And makes it into thick darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if you will not listen and obey,My soul will weep in secret for
        your pride;My eyes will weep bitterlyAnd flow with tears,Because the Lord\u2019s
        flock has been taken captive.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Say to the king and the queen mother,\u201CHumble yourselves and
        take a lowly seat,For your beautiful crown [the crown of your glory]Has come
        down from your head.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The cities of the South (the Negev) have been closed up,And there
        is no one to open them;All Judah has been carried into exile,Completely carried
        away into exile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CLift up your eyes and seeThose coming from the north.Where
        is the flock that was given to you [to shepherd],Your beautiful flock?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "What will you say [O Jerusalem] when the Lord appoints [foreign nations
        to rule] over you\u2014Those former friends and allies whom you have encouraged
        [to be your companions]\u2014Will not pain seize youLike [that of] a woman
        in childbirth?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And if you [wonder and] say in your heart,\u2018Why have these things
        happened to me?\u2019It is because of the greatness and nature of your sinThat
        your skirts have been pulled away [subjecting you to public disgrace]And
        [like a barefoot slave] your heels have been wounded.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Can the Ethiopian change his skinOr the leopard his spots?Then you
        also can do goodWho are accustomed to evil and even trained to do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Therefore I will scatter you like drifting straw[Driven away] by
        the desert wind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "This is your destiny, the portion [of judgment] measured to youFrom
        Me,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CBecause you have forgotten MeAnd trusted in
        [pagan] lies [the counterfeit gods, and the pretense of alliance].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CSo I Myself will throw your skirts up over your face,That your
        shame may be exposed [publicly].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "I have seen your vile and detestable acts,Even your adulteries and
        your lustful neighings [after idols],And the lewdness of your prostitutionOn
        the hills in the fields.Woe (judgment is coming) to you, O Jerusalem!How
        long will you remain unclean [by ignoring My precepts]?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Drought and a Prayer for Mercy'
      title: Drought and a Prayer for Mercy
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah concerning the drought:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CJudah mournsAnd her gates languish;Her people sit on the ground
        in mourning clothesAnd the cry of Jerusalem has gone up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Their nobles have sent their servants for water;They have come to
        the cisterns and found no water.They have returned with empty vessels;They
        have been shamed and humiliated,And they cover their heads.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The ground is crackedBecause there has been no rain on the land;The
        farmers are distressed,And they have covered their heads [in shame].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The doe in the field has given birth only to abandon her youngBecause
        there is no grass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the wild donkeys stand on the barren heights;They pant for air
        like jackals,Their eyesight failsBecause there is no grass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "O Lord, though our many sins testify against us\u201D [prays Jeremiah],\u201CAct
        now [for us and] for Your name\u2019s sake [so that the faithless may witness
        Your faithfulness]!For our backslidings are countless;We have sinned against
        You.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Hope of Israel,Her Savior in time of distress and trouble,Why should
        You be like a sojourner (temporary resident) in the landOr like a traveler
        who turns aside and spreads his tent to linger [only] for a night?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Why should You be [hesitant and inactive] like a man astounded and
        perplexed,Like a mighty man unable to save?Yet You, O Lord, are among us,And
        we are called by Your name;Do not leave us!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Thus says the Lord to this people [Judah], \u201CIn the manner and
        to the degree [already pointed out] they have loved to wander; they have
        not restrained their feet. Therefore the Lord does not accept them; He will
        now remember [in detail] their wickedness and punish them for their sins.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Lord said to me, \u201CDo not pray for good things for this
        people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: False Prophets'
      title: False Prophets
      number: 12
      content: "Though they fast, I will not hear their cry; and though they offer
        burnt offerings and grain offerings, I will not accept them [because they
        are done as obligations, and not as acts of loving obedience]. Instead I
        will consume them by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But I said, \u201CAlas, Lord God! Behold, the [false] prophets are
        telling them, \u2018You will not see the sword nor will you have famine,
        but I [the Lord] will give you lasting peace in this place.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CThe [counterfeit] prophets are prophesying
        lies in My Name. I have neither sent them nor authorized them nor spoken
        to them. They are prophesying to you made-up visions [pretending to call
        forth responses from handmade gods], a worthless divination and the deceit
        of their own mind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord concerning the [false] prophets who
        are prophesying in My Name, although I did not send them\u2014yet they keep
        saying, \u2018Sword and famine shall not be in this land\u2019: by sword
        and famine those prophets shall meet their end and be consumed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the people to whom they are prophesying will be thrown out into
        the streets of Jerusalem, victims of famine and sword; and they will have
        no one to bury them\u2014neither them, nor their wives, nor their sons, nor
        their daughters. For I will pour out their [own] wickedness on them [and
        not only on the imposters posing as prophets, for the people could not have
        been deceived without their own consent].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore [Jeremiah] you will say this word to them,\u2018Let my
        eyes flow with tears night and day,And let them never cease;For the virgin
        daughter of my people has been crushed with a great blow,With a very serious
        and severely infected wound.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If I go out into the field,Then I gaze on those slaughtered with
        the sword!And if I enter the city,Then I gaze on [those tormented with] the
        diseases of famine!For both prophet and priest [who should have guided the
        people]Go about [bewildered and exiled] in a land (Babylon) that they do
        not know or understand.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Have You [O Lord] completely rejected Judah?Do You loathe Zion?Why
        have You stricken us so that there is no healing for us?We looked for peace
        and completeness, but nothing good came;And [we hoped] for a time of healing,
        but behold, terror!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'We know and acknowledge, O Lord,Our wickedness and the iniquity of
        our fathers; for we have sinned against You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Do not treat us with contempt and condemn us, for Your own name\u2019s
        sake;Do not disgrace Your glorious throne;Remember [with consideration] and
        do not break Your [solemn] covenant with us.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Are there any among the idols of the nations who can send rain?Or
        can the heavens [of their own will] give showers?Is it not You, O Lord our
        God?Therefore we will wait and hope [confidently] in You,For You are the
        one who has made all these things [the heavens and the rain].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment Must Come'
      title: Judgment Must Come
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to me, \u201CEven though Moses and Samuel were
        to stand before Me [interceding for them], My heart would still not be [turned
        with favor] toward this people [Judah]. Send them away from My presence and
        out of My sight and let them go! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it shall be that when they say to you, \u2018Where should we
        go?\u2019 then tell them, \u2018Thus says the Lord:\u201CThose [destined]
        for death, to death;Those for the sword, to the sword;Those for famine, to
        famine;Those for captivity, to captivity.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I will appoint four kinds of destroyers over them,\u201D says the
        Lord, \u201Cthe sword to slay, the dogs to tear and drag away, and the birds
        of the air and the beasts of the earth to devour and to destroy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will make them an object of horror to all nations of the earth
        because of Manasseh [the despicable] son of Hezekiah, king of Judah, for
        the [evil and detestable] things which he did in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor who will have pity on you, O Jerusalem,Or who will mourn
        for you,Or who will turn aside to ask about your welfare?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You have abandoned (rejected) Me,\u201D says the Lord.\u201CYou keep
        going backward.Therefore I shall stretch out My hand against you and destroy
        you;I am tired of delaying [your punishment]!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will winnow (sort, separate) them with a winnowing forkAt the gates
        of the land;I will deprive them of children, I will destroy My people;They
        did not repent and turn from their [evil] ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will make their widows more numerous before MeThan the sand of
        the seas;I will bring against them, against the mother of the young men,A
        destroyer at noonday;I will suddenly cause anguish and terrorTo fall on her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She who has borne seven [sons] languishes;She has breathed out her
        soul.Her sun has set while it was still day;She has been shamed and humiliated.So
        I will hand over [the rest of] the survivors to the swordBefore their enemies,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Woe to me, my mother, that you have given birth to meTo be a man
        of strife and a man of contention to all the earth!I have not loaned, nor
        have men lent money to me,Yet everyone curses me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Lord said, \u201CSurely [it will go well for Judah\u2019s obedient
        remnant for] I will set you free for good purposes;Surely [Jeremiah] I will
        [intercede for you with the enemy and I will] cause the enemy to plead with
        you [for help]In a time of disaster and a time of distress.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CCan anyone crush iron,The iron from the north, or bronze?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Your [nation\u2019s] riches and your treasuresI will give as plunder
        without price [to the Babylonians],Because of all your sinsAnd within all
        your territories.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer and God\u2019s Answer"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer and God\u2019s Answer"
      number: 14
      content: "Then I will make your enemies bring [you along with] your possessionsInto
        a land which you do not know [for there you will serve your conquerors];For
        a fire has been kindled in My anger,Which will burn upon you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'O Lord, You know and understand;Remember me [thoughtfully], take
        notice of me,take vengeance for me on my persecutors.Do not, in view of Your
        patience, take me away;Know that for Your sake I endure [continual] rebuke
        and dishonor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Your words were found and I ate them,And Your words became a joy
        to me and the delight of my heart;For I have been called by Your name,O Lord
        God of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I did not sit with the group of those who celebrate,Nor did I rejoice;I
        sat alone because Your [powerful] hand was upon me,For You had filled me
        with indignation [at their sin].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Why has my pain been perpetualAnd my wound incurable, refusing to
        be healed?Will you indeed be to me like a deceptive brookWith water that
        is unreliable?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord [to Jeremiah],\u201CIf you repent [and
        give up this mistaken attitude of despair and self-pity], then I will restore
        you [to a state of inner peace]So that you may stand before Me [as My obedient
        representative];And if you separate the precious from the worthless [examining
        yourself and cleansing your heart from unwarranted doubt concerning My faithfulness],You
        will become My spokesman.Let the people turn to you [and learn to value My
        values]\u2014But you, you must not turn to them [with regard for their idolatry
        and wickedness].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And I will make you to this peopleA fortified wall of bronze;They
        will fight against you,But they will not prevail over you,For I am with you
        [always] to save youAnd protect you,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CSo I will rescue you out of the hand of the wicked,And I will
        redeem you from the [grasping] palm of the terrible and ruthless [tyrant].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Distresses Foretold'
      title: Distresses Foretold
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the Lord also came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CYou shall not take a wife or have sons and daughters in this
        place (Jerusalem).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For thus says the Lord concerning the sons and daughters who are
        born in this place, and concerning the mothers who give birth to them, and
        the fathers who father them in this land: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThey will die of deadly diseases. They will not be mourned
        or buried; they will be like dung on the surface of the ground and come to
        an end by sword and famine, and their dead bodies will be food for the birds
        of the air and for the beasts of the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For thus says the Lord, \u201CDo not enter a house of mourning, nor
        go to lament (express grief) or bemoan [the dead], for I have taken My peace
        away from this people,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Ceven My lovingkindness
        and compassion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Both great men and small will die in this land; they will not be
        buried, nor will they be lamented (mourned over with expressions of grief
        in death), nor will anyone cut himself or shave his head for them [in mourning]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "People will not offer food to the mourners, to comfort anyone [as
        they grieve] for the dead, nor give them a cup of consolation to drink for
        anyone\u2019s father or mother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And you [Jeremiah] shall not go into a house of feasting to sit with
        them to eat and drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CBehold,
        I will remove from this place, before your very eyes and in your time, the
        sound of joy and the shout of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the
        voice of the bride.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CNow when you tell these people all these words and they ask
        you, \u2018Why has the Lord decreed all this great tragedy against us? And
        what is our iniquity, what is the sin which we have committed against the
        Lord our God?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then you are to say to them, \u2018It is because your fathers have
        abandoned (rejected) Me,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018and have walked after
        other gods and have served them and bowed down to the handmade idols and
        have abandoned (rejected) Me and have not kept My law, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and because you have done worse [things] than your fathers. Just
        look, every one of you walks in the stubbornness of his own evil heart, so
        that you do not listen [obediently] to Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: God Will Restore Them'
      title: God Will Restore Them
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore I will hurl you out of this land [of Judah] into the land
        [of the Babylonians] which neither you nor your fathers have known, and there
        you will serve other gods day and night, for I will show you no compassion.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cwhen it will no longer be said, \u2018As the Lord lives, who brought
        up the sons of Israel out of the land of Egypt,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but, \u2018As the Lord lives, who brought up the sons of Israel from
        the land of the north and from all the countries to which He had driven them.\u2019
        And I will bring them back to their land which I gave to their fathers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBehold (listen carefully), I will send for many fishermen,\u201D
        says the Lord, \u201Cand they will fish for them; and afterward I will send
        for many hunters, and they will hunt them from every mountain and from every
        hill and out of the clefts of the rocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For My eyes are on all their ways; they are not hidden from My face,
        nor is their wickedness concealed from My eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I will first doubly repay and punish them for their wickedness and
        their sin [before I return them to their land], because they have profaned
        My land; they have filled My inheritance with the carcasses of their detestable
        idols and with their abominations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "[Then said Jeremiah] \u201CO Lord, my Strength and my Stronghold,And
        my Refuge in the day of distress and need,The nations will come to YouFrom
        the ends of the earth and say,\u2018Our fathers have inherited nothing but
        lies and illusion,[Worthless] things in which there is no benefit!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Can a man make gods for himself?Such [things] are not gods!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CTherefore,\u201D [says the Lord] \u201Cbehold, I will make
        them know\u2014This time I will make them knowMy power and My might;And they
        will know and recognize [without any doubt] that My Name is the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Deceitful Heart'
      title: The Deceitful Heart
      number: 1
      content: '  The sin of Judah is written down with an iron stylus;With a diamond
        point it is engraved upon the tablet of their heartAnd on the horns of their
        altars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'As they remember their children,So they remember [in detail] their
        [pagan] altars and their AsherimBeside green trees on the high hills.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O [Jerusalem] My mountain in the countryside,I will give [to the
        Babylonians, as the cost of your sin] your wealth and all your treasures
        as plunder,And throughout your territory, your high places of sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And you will, through your own fault, let go of your [grip on your]
        inheritanceThat I gave you;And I will make you serve your enemiesIn a land
        which you do not know;For you have kindled a fire in My angerWhich will burn
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CCursed is the man who trusts in and relies
        on mankind,Making [weak, faulty human] flesh his strength,And whose mind
        and heart turn away from the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For he will be like a shrub in the [parched] desert;And shall not
        see prosperity when it comes,But shall live in the rocky places of the wilderness,In
        an uninhabited salt land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Blessed [with spiritual security] is the man who believes and trusts
        in and relies on the LordAnd whose hope and confident expectation is the
        Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For he will be [nourished] like a tree planted by the waters,That
        spreads out its roots by the river;And will not fear the heat when it comes;But
        its leaves will be green and moist.And it will not be anxious and concerned
        in a year of droughtNor stop bearing fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe heart is deceitful above all thingsAnd it is extremely
        sick;Who can understand it fully and know its secret motives?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I, the Lord, search and examine the mind,I test the heart,To give
        to each man according to his ways,According to the results of his deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Like the partridge that hatches eggs which she has not laid,So is
        he who makes a fortune in ways that are unjust.It will be lost to him before
        his days are over,And in the end he will be [nothing but] a fool.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A glorious throne, set on high from the beginning,Is the place of
        our sanctuary (the temple).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O Lord, the hope of Israel,All who abandon You will be shamed.Those
        who turn away on earth will be written down,Because they have abandoned the
        Lord, the fountain of living waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Heal me, O Lord, and I will be healed;Save me and I will be saved,For
        You are my praise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Behold, they keep saying to me,\u201CWhere is the word of the Lord
        [that is, the disaster that you prophesied]?Let it come now!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But as for me, I have not tried to escape from being a shepherd [walking]
        after You,Nor have I longed for the woeful day [of judgment];You know that,
        whatever I saidWas [spoken] in Your presence and was from You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not be a terror to me;You are my refuge and my hope in the day
        of disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Sabbath Must Be Kept'
      title: The Sabbath Must Be Kept
      number: 18
      content: 'Let those who persecute me be shamed, but as for me, protect me from
        shame;Let them lose courage, but let me be undaunted.Bring on them a day
        of tragedy,And destroy them with double destruction!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Thus the Lord said to me, \u201CGo and stand in the public gate,
        through which the kings of Judah come in and go out, and [stand] also in
        all the gates of Jerusalem; "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Listen to the word of the Lord, kings of Judah,
        and all Judah, and all the people of Jerusalem who enter through these gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u201CPay attention for your own good, [and for
        the sake of your future] do not carry any load on the Sabbath day or bring
        anything in through the gates of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You shall not carry a load out of your houses on the Sabbath day
        nor do any work, but keep the Sabbath day holy [by setting it apart as a
        day of worship], as I commanded your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Yet they would not listen and obey and control their behavior; but
        they were stiff-necked in order not to hear and take instruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But it will come about, if you listen diligently to Me,\u201D says
        the Lord, \u201Cto bring no load in through the gates of this city on the
        Sabbath day, but keep the Sabbath day holy by doing no work on it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "then kings and princes who will sit on the throne of David will enter
        through the gates of this city, riding in chariots and on horses\u2014the
        kings and their princes, the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem;
        and this city will be inhabited and endure throughout the ages. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'People will come from the cities of Judah and the places all around
        Jerusalem, from the land of Benjamin, from the lowland, from the hill country
        and from the South (the Negev), bringing burnt offerings and sacrifices,
        grain offerings and incense, and bringing sacrifices of thanksgiving to the
        house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But if you will not listen to Me and keep the Sabbath day holy by
        not carrying a load as you come in the gates of Jerusalem on the Sabbath
        day, then I will kindle a fire in her gates that cannot be extinguished,
        and it will devour the palaces of Jerusalem.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Potter and the Clay'
      title: The Potter and the Clay
      number: 1
      content: '  The word which came to Jeremiah from the Lord: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CArise and go down to the potter\u2019s house, and there I will
        make you hear My words.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then I went down to the potter\u2019s house, and saw that he was
        working at the wheel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the vessel that he was making from clay was spoiled by the potter\u2019s
        hand; so he made it over, reworking it and making it into another pot that
        seemed good to him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CO house of Israel, can I not do with you as this potter does?\u201D
        says the Lord. \u201CLook carefully, as the clay is in the potter\u2019s
        hand, so are you in My hand, O house of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'At one moment I might [suddenly] speak concerning a nation or kingdom,
        that I will uproot and break down and destroy; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'if that nation against which I have spoken turns from its evil, I
        will relent and reverse My decision concerning the devastation that I intended
        to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Or at another time I might [suddenly] speak about a nation or kingdom
        that I will build up or establish; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and if they do evil in My sight by not obeying My voice, then I will
        reverse My decision concerning the good with which I had promised to bless
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now then, say to the men of Judah and to the citizens of Jerusalem,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CBehold, I am shaping a disaster and working
        out a plan against you. Turn back, each of you from his evil way; correct
        your habits and change your actions for the better.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But they will say, \u2018That is hopeless! For we are going to follow
        our own plans, and each of us will act in accordance with the stubbornness
        of his evil heart.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord,\u2018Ask now among the nations,Who
        has heard of such things?The virgin IsraelHas done a very vile and horrible
        thing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Will the snow of [Mount] Lebanon melt and vanish from its rocks [which
        tower above Israel]?Will the cold, rushing waters of foreign lands [that
        flow down from the distant land] be dried up?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Yet My people have forgotten Me;They burn incense to worthless gods,They
        have stumbled from their waysFrom the ancient roads,To walk in pathways,Not
        on a highway,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Making their land a desolation and a horror,  A thing to be hissed
        at perpetually;Everyone who passes by will be astoundedAnd shake his head
        [in scorn].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I will scatter them like an east windBefore the enemy;I will show
        them My back and not My faceIn the day of their disaster [says the Lord].\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then [my enemies] said, \u201CCome and let us work out schemes against
        Jeremiah. Surely the law is not going to be lost to the priest [as Jeremiah
        predicts], nor the counsel from the wise, nor the word from the prophet.
        Come and let us strike him with our tongue [by making charges against him
        before the king], and let us ignore anything he says.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Pay attention to me, O Lord [and intercede];Listen to what my adversaries
        are saying [and are plotting against me]\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Should good be repaid with evil?Yet they have dug a pit for me.Remember
        [with compassion] that I stood before YouTo speak good on their behalf,To
        turn Your anger away from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore, give their children over to the famine;Give them over
        to the power of the sword.And let their wives become childless and widowed;Let
        their men meet death [by virulent disease],Their young men be struck down
        by the sword in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Let an outcry be heard from their housesWhen You suddenly bring [a
        troop of] raiders upon them,For they have dug a pit to capture meAnd have
        hidden snares for my feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Yet You, O Lord, knowAll their deadly plotting against me;Do not forgive
        their wickednessOr blot out their sin from Your sight.But let them be overthrown
        before You;Deal with them in the time of Your anger.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Broken Jar'
      title: The Broken Jar
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the Lord, \u201CGo and buy a potter\u2019s earthenware
        jar, and take some of the elders of the people and some of the senior priests "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and go out to the Valley of Ben-hinnom (son of Hinnom), which is
        near the entrance of the Potsherd Gate; and proclaim there the words that
        I tell you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say, \u2018Hear the word of the Lord, O kings of Judah and inhabitants
        of Jerusalem. Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CBehold
        (listen carefully), I am going to bring such disaster on this place that
        the ears of everyone who hears about it will tingle [in shock]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because the people [of Jerusalem] have abandoned (rejected) Me and
        have made this an alien and profaned place by burning sacrifices and incense
        in it to other gods, that neither they nor their fathers nor the kings of
        Judah ever knew, and because they have filled this place with the blood of
        the innocent '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and have built the high places of Baal to burn their sons in the
        fire as burnt offerings to Baal, which I never commanded or spoke of, nor
        did it ever enter My mind (heart); '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "therefore, listen very closely, the days are coming,\u201D says the
        Lord, \u201Cwhen this place shall no longer be called Topheth or the Valley
        of Ben-hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will pour out and nullify the counsel (plans) of [the men of] Judah
        and Jerusalem in this place, and I will make their people fall by the sword
        before their enemies and by the hand of those who seek their lives; and I
        will give their dead bodies as food for the birds of the air and for the
        beasts of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will make this city a desolation and an object of hissing; everyone
        who passes by it will be amazed and will hiss [in scorn] because of all its
        plagues and disasters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And I will make them eat the flesh of their sons and their daughters,
        and each one will eat one another\u2019s flesh during the siege and distress
        brought by their enemies and those who seek their lives.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThen you are to break the jar in the sight of the men who accompany
        you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u201CThis is
        the way I will break this people and this city as one breaks a potter\u2019s
        vessel, so that it cannot be mended. They will bury [corpses] in Topheth
        until there is no more room left [in that place] to bury [the dead]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "This I will do to this place,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cand to its
        inhabitants; and I will even make this city like Topheth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The houses of Jerusalem and the houses of the kings of Judah will
        be defiled like this place, Topheth, all the houses on whose rooftops incense
        has been burned to all the host of heaven (sun, moon, stars), and where drink
        offerings have been poured out to other gods.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Jeremiah came from Topheth, where the Lord had sent him to prophesy;
        and he stood in the court of the Lord\u2019s house and said to all the people: "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Behold,
        I am going to bring on this city and on all its towns, all the devastation
        that I have declared against it, because they have become stiff-necked and
        refused to hear and obey My words.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Pashhur Persecutes Jeremiah'
      title: Pashhur Persecutes Jeremiah
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Pashhur the son of Immer, the priest, who was [also] chief
        officer in the house of the Lord, heard Jeremiah prophesying these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Pashhur beat Jeremiah the prophet and put him in the stocks
        that were at the upper Benjamin Gate by the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the next day Pashhur brought Jeremiah out of the stocks. Then
        Jeremiah said to him, \u201CThe Lord does not call your name Pashhur, but
        Magor-missabib (terror on every side). "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the Lord, \u2018Behold, I will make you a terror to
        yourself and to all your friends; they will fall by the sword of their enemies
        while you look on. And I will give all Judah into the hand of the king of
        Babylon; he will carry them away to Babylon as captives and will slaughter
        them with the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Moreover, I will hand over all the riches of this city, all the result
        of its labor, all its precious things; even all the treasures of the kings
        of Judah I will hand over to their enemies, and they will plunder them, and
        take them away and carry them to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      number: 6
      content: "And you, Pashhur, and all who live in your house will go into captivity;
        you will go to Babylon, and there you will die and be buried, you and all
        your friends to whom you have falsely prophesied.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '[Jeremiah said,] O Lord, You have persuaded me and I was deceived;You
        are stronger than I and You have prevailed.I am a laughingstock all day long;Everyone
        mocks me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For whenever I speak, I must shout out;I shout violence and destruction,Because
        the word of the Lord has become to meA reprimand and a mockery and has brought
        me insult all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If I say, \u201CI will not remember HimOr speak His name anymore,\u201DThen
        my heart becomes a burning fireShut up in my bones.And I am weary of enduring
        and holding it in;I cannot endure it [nor contain it any longer].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For I have heard the whispering and defaming words of many,\u201CTerror
        on every side!Denounce him! Let us denounce him!\u201DAll my familiar and
        trusted friends,[Those who are] watching for my fall, say,\u201CPerhaps he
        will be persuaded and deceived; then we will overcome him,And take our revenge
        on him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the Lord is with me as a dread champion [one to be greatly feared];Therefore
        my persecutors will stumble and not overcome [me].They will be completely
        shamed, for they have not acted wisely and have failed [in their schemes];Their
        eternal dishonor will never be forgotten.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But, O Lord of hosts, You who examine the righteous,Who see the heart
        and the mind,Let me see Your vengeance on them;For to You I have committed
        my cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Sing to the Lord! Praise the Lord!For He has rescued the life of
        the needy oneFrom the hand of evildoers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Cursed be the day on which I was born;Do not bless the day on which
        my mother gave birth to me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Cursed be the man who brought the newsTo my father, saying,\u201CA
        son has been born to you!\u201DMaking him very glad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And let that man be like the citiesWhich the Lord overthrew without
        regret.Let him hear an outcry in the morningAnd a shout of alarm at noon;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Because he did not kill me before my birth,So that my mother might
        have been my grave,And her womb always pregnant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Why did I come out of the wombTo see trouble and sorrow,So that my
        days have been filled with shame?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Message for Zedekiah"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Message for Zedekiah"
      number: 1
      content: '  The word which came to Jeremiah from the Lord when King Zedekiah
        sent to him Pashhur the son of Malchijah, and Zephaniah the priest the son
        of Maaseiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CPlease inquire of the Lord for us, because Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon is making war against us. Perhaps the Lord will deal [favorably]
        with us according to all His wonderful works and force him to withdraw from
        us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to them, \u201CSay this to Zedekiah: "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u201CBehold, I will
        turn back and dull the edge of the weapons of war that are in your hands,
        [those] with which you fight against the king of Babylon and the Chaldeans
        who are besieging you outside the walls; and I will bring them into the center
        of this city (Jerusalem). "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I Myself will fight against you with an outstretched hand and with
        a strong arm in anger, in fury, and in great indignation and wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will also strike the inhabitants of this city, both man and beast;
        they will die of a great virulent disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then afterward,\u201D says the Lord, \u201CI will hand over Zedekiah
        king of Judah and his servants and the people in this city who survive the
        virulent disease, the sword, and the famine, to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon,
        and into the hand of their enemy, into the hand of those who seek their lives.
        And he will strike them with the edge of the sword; he will not spare them
        nor have mercy and compassion on them.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd to this people you (Jeremiah) shall also say, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord, \u201CBehold, I set before you the way of life and the way
        of death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who remains in this city [of Jerusalem] will die by the sword
        and by famine and by virulent disease. But he who goes outside and surrenders
        to the Chaldeans who are besieging you will live, and his life will be like
        a prize of war to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For I have set My face against this city to do harm and not good,\u201D
        says the Lord. \u201CIt shall be given into the hand of the king of Babylon
        and he will burn it with fire.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAnd concerning the royal house of the king of Judah [you shall
        say], \u2018Hear the word of the Lord, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O house of David, thus says the Lord:\u201CAdminister justice in
        the morning,And rescue the one who has been robbed from the hand of his oppressor,That
        My wrath will not roar up like fireAnd burn so [hotly] that none can extinguish
        it,Because of the evil of their deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CUnderstand this, I am against you, O inhabitant of the valley,O
        rock of the plain,\u201D says the Lord\u2014\u201CYou who say, \u2018Who
        will come down against us?Or who will enter into our dwelling places?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But I will punish you in accordance with the [appropriate] consequences
        of your decisions and your actions,\u201D says the Lord.\u201CI will kindle
        a fire in your forest,And it will devour all that is around you.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Warning of Jerusalem\u2019s Fall"
      title: "Warning of Jerusalem\u2019s Fall"
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the Lord, \u201CGo down to the house of the king of Judah
        and speak this word there: "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u2018Hear the word of the Lord, O king of Judah, you who sit on
        the throne of David\u2014you and your servants and your people who enter
        by these gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u201CExecute justice and righteousness, and
        rescue the one who has been robbed from the hand of his oppressor. And do
        no wrong; do no violence to the stranger, the fatherless, or the widow, nor
        shed innocent blood in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For if you will indeed obey this word, then kings will enter through
        the gates of this palace, sitting in David\u2019s place on his throne, riding
        in chariots and on horses, even the king himself and his servants and his
        people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if you will not hear and obey these words, I swear [an oath]
        by Myself,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthat this house will become a desolation.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus says the Lord in regard to the house of the king of Judah:\u201CYou
        are [as valuable] to Me as [the green pastures of] Gilead [east of the Jordan]Or
        as the [plentiful] summit of Lebanon [west of the Jordan],Yet most certainly
        [if you will not listen to Me] I will make you a wilderness,And uninhabited
        cities.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For I will prepare and appoint destroyers [to execute My judgments]
        against you,Each with his weapons;And they will cut down your [palaces built
        of] choicest cedarsAnd throw them in the fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CMany nations will pass by this city; and each man will say
        to another, \u2018Why has the Lord done this to this great city?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they will answer, \u2018Because the people ignored and abandoned
        the [solemn] covenant with the Lord their God and worshiped other gods and
        served them.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Do not weep for the dead or mourn for him;But weep bitterly for the
        one who goes away [into exile],For he will never returnAnd see his native
        country [again].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For thus says the Lord in regard to Shallum (Jehoahaz) the [third]
        son of Josiah, king of Judah, who reigned instead of Josiah his father and
        who went from this place, \u201CShallum will not return here anymore; "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Messages about the Kings'
      title: Messages about the Kings
      number: 12
      content: 'he will die in the place where they led him captive and not see this
        land again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CWoe (judgment is coming) to him who builds his house by [acts
        of] unrighteousnessAnd his upper chambers by injustice,Who uses his neighbor\u2019s
        service without payAnd does not give him wages [for his work],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Who says, \u2018I will build myself a spacious houseWith large upper
        rooms,And cut out its [wide] windows,And panel it with cedar and paint it
        vermilion.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Do you think that you become a king because you have much more cedar
        [in your palace than Solomon]?Did not your father [Josiah], as he ate and
        drank,Do just and righteous acts [being upright and in right standing with
        God]?Then all was well with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He defended the cause of the afflicted and needy;Then all was well.Is
        that not what it means to know Me?\u201DSays the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut your eyes and your heartAre only intent on your own dishonest
        gain,On shedding innocent blood,On oppression and extortion and violence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord in regard to Jehoiakim the [second]
        son of Josiah, king of Judah,\u201CThe relatives will not lament (mourn over
        with expressions of grief) for him:\u2018Alas, my brother!\u2019 or, \u2018Alas,
        sister,\u2019 [how great our loss]!The subjects will not lament for him:\u2018Alas,
        master!\u2019 or \u2018Alas, majesty [how great was his glory]!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  He shall be buried with the burial of a donkey\u2014Dragged off
        and thrown out beyond the gates of Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Go up [north] to Lebanon and cry out,And raise your voice in [the
        hills of] Bashan [across the Jordan];Cry out also from Abarim,For all your
        lovers (allies) have been destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I spoke to you in your [times of] prosperity,But you said, \u2018I
        will not listen!\u2019This has been your attitude and practice from your
        youth;You have not obeyed My voice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The wind [of adversity] will carry away all your shepherds (rulers,
        statesmen),And your lovers (allies) will go into exile.Surely then you will
        be ashamed and humiliated and disgracedBecause of all your wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'O inhabitant of [Jerusalem, whose palaces are made from the cedars
        of] Lebanon,You who nest in the cedars,How you will groan and how miserable
        you will be when pains come on you,Pain like a woman in childbirth!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAs I live,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthough Coniah the son
        of Jehoiakim king of Judah were the signet [ring] on My right hand, yet would
        I pull you (Coniah) off. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And I will place you in the hand of those who seek your life and
        in the hand of those whom you fear, even into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon and into the hand of the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I will hurl you and the mother who gave you birth into another country
        where you were not born, and there you will die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But as for the land to which they long to return, they will not return
        to it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Is this man [King] Coniah a despised, broken jar?Is he a vessel in
        which no one takes pleasure?Why are he and his [royal] descendants hurled
        outAnd cast into a land which they do not know or understand?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'O land, land, land,Hear the word of the Lord!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u2018Write this man [Coniah] down as childless,A
        man who will not prosper (succeed) in his lifetime;For not one of his descendants
        will succeedIn sitting on the throne of DavidOr ruling again in Judah.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming Messiah: the Righteous Branch'
      title: 'The Coming Messiah: the Righteous Branch'
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWoe to the shepherds (civil leaders, rulers) who are destroying
        and scattering the sheep of My pasture!\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord, the God of Israel, in regard to the
        shepherds who care for and feed My people: \u201CYou have scattered My flock
        and driven them away, and have not attended to them; hear this, I am about
        to visit and attend to you for the evil of your deeds,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CThen I will gather the remnant of My flock out of all the countries
        to which I have driven them and bring them back to their folds and pastures;
        and they will be fruitful and multiply. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I will set up shepherds over them who will feed them. And they will
        not be afraid any longer, nor be terrified, nor will any be missing,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBehold (listen closely), the days are coming,\u201D says the
        Lord,\u201CWhen I will raise up for David a righteous Branch;And He will
        reign as King and act wiselyAnd will do [those things that accomplish] justice
        and righteousness in the land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In His days Judah will be saved,And Israel will dwell safely;Now
        this is His name by which He will be called;\u2018The Lord Our Righteousness.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cwhen they will no longer say, \u2018As the Lord lives, who brought
        up the children of Israel from the land of Egypt,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: False Prophets Denounced'
      title: False Prophets Denounced
      number: 8
      content: "but [they will say], \u2018As the Lord lives, who brought up and
        led back the descendants of the house of Israel from the north country and
        from all the countries to which I had driven them.\u2019 Then they will live
        in their own land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Concerning the prophets:My heart [says Jeremiah] is broken within
        me,All my bones shake;I have become like a drunken man,A man whom wine has
        overcome,Because of the LordAnd because of His holy words [declared against
        unfaithful leaders].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the land is full of adulterers (unfaithful to God);The land mourns
        because of the curse [of God upon it].The pastures of the wilderness have
        dried up.The course of action [of the false prophets] is evil and they rush
        into wickedness;And their power is not right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CFor both [false] prophet and priest are ungodly (profane, polluted);Even
        in My house I have found their wickedness,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore their way will be to them like slippery pathsIn the
        dark; they will be pushed and fall into them;For I will bring disaster on
        them,In the year of their punishment,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAnd I have seen a foolish and an offensive thing in the prophets
        of Samaria:They prophesied by Baal and caused My people Israel to go astray.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Also I have seen a horrible thing in the prophets of Jerusalem:They
        commit adultery and walk in lies;They encourage and strengthen the hands
        of evildoers,So that no one has turned back from his wickedness.All of them
        have become like Sodom to Me,And her inhabitants like Gomorrah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord of hosts in regard to the prophets,\u2018Behold,
        I am going to feed them [the bitterness of] wormwoodAnd make them drink the
        poisonous water [of gall],For from the [counterfeit] prophets of JerusalemProfaneness
        and ungodliness have spread into all the land.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts,\u201CDo not listen to the words of the
        [false] prophets who prophesy to you.They are teaching you worthless things
        and are leading you into futility;They speak a vision of their own mind and
        imaginationAnd not [truth] from the mouth of the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They are continually saying to those who despise Me [and My word],\u2018The
        Lord has said, \u201CYou will have peace\u201D\u2009\u2019;And they say to
        everyone who walks after the stubbornness of his own heart,\u2018No evil
        will come on you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But who [among them] has stood in the council of the Lord,That he
        would perceive and hear His word?Who has marked His word [noticing and observing
        and paying attention to it] and has [actually] heard it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, the tempest of the Lord has gone forth in wrath,A whirling
        tempest;It will whirl and burst on the heads of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The anger of the Lord will not turn backUntil He has set in motion
        and accomplished the thoughts and intentions of His heart;In the last days
        you will clearly understand it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I did not send [these counterfeit] prophets,Yet they ran;I did not
        speak to them,Yet they prophesied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But if they had stood in My council,Then they would have caused My
        people to hear My words,Then they would have turned My people from their
        evil wayAnd from the evil of their decisions and deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAm I a God who is at hand,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAnd not
        a God far away?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CCan anyone hide himself in secret placesSo that I cannot see
        him?\u201D says the Lord.\u201CDo I not fill heaven and earth?\u201D says
        the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI have heard what the prophets have said who prophesy lies
        in My Name, saying, \u2018I have dreamed, I have dreamed [visions when on
        my bed at night].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'How long [shall this state of affairs continue]? Is there anything
        in the hearts of the prophets who prophesy falsehood, even these prophets
        of the deception of their own heart, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'who think that they can make My people forget My Name by their [contrived]
        dreams which each one tells another, just as their fathers forgot My Name
        because of Baal? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The prophet who has a dream may tell his dream; but he who has My
        word, let him speak My word faithfully. What has straw in common with wheat
        [for nourishment]?\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIs not My word like fire [that consumes all that cannot endure
        the test]?\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cand like a hammer that breaks the [most
        stubborn] rock [in pieces]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore behold (hear this), I am against the [counterfeit] prophets,\u201D
        says the Lord, \u201C[I am descending on them with punishment, these prophets]
        who steal My words from one another [imitating the words of the true prophets]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Hear this, I am against the prophets,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cwho
        use their [own deceitful] tongues and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Hear this, I am against those who have prophesied false and made-up
        dreams,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cand have told them and have made My people
        err and go astray by their lies and by their reckless boasting; yet I did
        not send them or command them nor do they benefit and enhance [the life of]
        these people in the slightest way,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CNow when this people or a prophet or a priest asks you [in
        jest], \u2018What is the oracle of the Lord [the burden to be lifted up and
        carried]?\u2019 Then you shall say to them, \u2018What oracle [besides the
        one that declares you people to be the burden]!\u2019 The Lord says, \u2018I
        will unburden Myself and I will abandon you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And as for the prophet, the priest, or [any of] the people, whoever
        says, \u2018The oracle of the Lord,\u2019 [as if he knows God\u2019s will],
        I will punish that man and his household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "[For the future, in speaking of the words of the Lord] thus each
        of you shall say to his neighbor and to his brother, \u2018What has the Lord
        answered?\u2019 or, \u2018What has the Lord spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "For you will no longer remember the oracle of the Lord, because every
        man\u2019s own word will become the oracle, [for as they mockingly call all
        prophecies oracles, whether good or bad, so will it prove to be to them;
        God will take them at their own word]; and you have perverted the words [not
        of a lifeless idol, but] of the living God, the Lord of hosts, our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Thus you will [reverently] say to the prophet, \u2018What has the
        Lord answered you?\u2019 and, \u2018What has the Lord spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "For if you say, \u2018The oracle of the Lord!\u2019 surely thus says
        the Lord, \u2018Because you said this word, \u201CThe oracle of the Lord!\u201D
        when I have also sent to you, saying, \u201CYou shall not say, \u2018The
        oracle of the Lord!\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Therefore behold, I, even I, will assuredly forget you and send you
        away from My presence, you and the city (Jerusalem) which I gave to you and
        to your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And I will bring an everlasting disgrace on you and a perpetual humiliation
        (shame) which will not be forgotten.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Baskets of Figs and the Returnees'
      title: Baskets of Figs and the Returnees
      number: 1
      content: '  After Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had taken Jeconiah [who was
        also called Coniah and Jehoiachin] the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, and
        the princes of Judah [along] with the craftsmen and smiths into exile from
        Jerusalem to Babylon, the Lord showed me [in a vision] two baskets of figs
        set before the temple of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'One basket had very good figs, like the figs that are the first to
        ripen; but the other basket had very bad figs, so rotten that they could
        not be eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CWhat do you see, Jeremiah?\u201D
        And I said, \u201CFigs, the good figs, very good; and the bad figs, very
        bad, so rotten that they cannot be eaten.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u2018Like these good
        figs, so I will regard as good the captives of Judah, whom I have sent from
        this place into the land of the Chaldeans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I will set My eyes on them for good, and I will bring them again
        to this land; and I will build them up and not overwhelm them, and I will
        plant them and not uproot them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will give them a heart to know Me, [understanding fully] that I
        am the Lord; and they will be My people, and I will be their God, for they
        will return to Me with their whole heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018And as for the bad figs, which are so rotten that they cannot
        be eaten,\u2019 surely thus says the Lord, \u2018so I will abandon Zedekiah
        king of Judah and his princes, and the remnant of Jerusalem who remain in
        this land and those who live in the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will make them a focus of ridicule and disappointment [tossed back
        and forth] among all the kingdoms of the earth, a [notorious] disgrace, a
        byword, a taunt and a curse in all places where I will scatter them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I will send the sword, famine and virulent disease among them until
        they are consumed from the land which I gave to them and to their fathers.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy of the Captivity'
      title: Prophecy of the Captivity
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah in regard to all the people of Judah
        in the fourth year of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah
        (that was the first year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'which Jeremiah the prophet spoke to all the people of Judah and to
        all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CFor these twenty-three years\u2014from the thirteenth year
        of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah, even to this day\u2014the word
        of the Lord has come to me and I have spoken to you over and over again,
        but you have not listened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Although the Lord has persistently sent to you all His servants the
        prophets, you have not listened nor [even] inclined your ear to hear [His
        message], '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "saying, \u2018Turn now everyone from his evil way and the evil of
        your actions [that you may not forfeit the right to] live in the land that
        the Lord has given to you and your forefathers forever and ever; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and do not go after other gods to serve them and to worship them,
        and do not provoke Me to anger with the work of your hands, and I will do
        you no harm.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Yet you have not listened to Me,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cso that
        you have provoked Me to anger with the work (idols) of your hands to your
        own harm.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018Because you have
        not obeyed My words, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "behold (hear this), I will send for all the families of the north,\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018and I will send for Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon,
        My servant [to enact My plan], and I will bring them against this land and
        against its inhabitants and against all these surrounding nations; and I
        will utterly destroy them and make them a horror and a hissing [that is,
        an object of warning and ridicule] and an everlasting desolation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Moreover, I will take from them the voice of joy and the voice of
        gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride, the sound
        of the millstones [grinding meal] and the light of the lamp [to light the
        night]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Babylon Will Be Judged'
      title: Babylon Will Be Judged
      number: 11
      content: 'This whole land will be a waste and a horror, and these nations will
        serve the king of Babylon seventy years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u2018Then when seventy years are completed, I will punish the king
        of Babylon and that nation, the land of the Chaldeans (Babylonia),\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018for their wickedness, and will make the land [of the
        Chaldeans] a perpetual waste. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will bring on that land all My words which I have pronounced against
        it, all that is written in this book which Jeremiah has prophesied against
        all the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "(For many nations and great kings will make slaves of them, even
        the Chaldeans [who enslaved other nations]; and I will repay [all of] them
        according to their deeds and according to the work of their [own] hands.)\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the Lord, the God of Israel, to me, \u201CTake this
        cup of the wine of wrath from My hand and cause all the nations to whom I
        send you to drink it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "They will drink and stagger and go mad because of the sword that
        I will send among them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I (Jeremiah) took the cup from the Lord\u2019s hand and made
        all the nations to whom the Lord had sent me drink it: "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jerusalem and the cities of Judah [being most guilty because their
        privileges were greatest], its kings and princes, to make them a horror,
        a ruin, a hissing and a curse, as it is to this day; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pharaoh king of Egypt, his servants, his princes, all his people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and all the foreign (mixed) population, all the kings of the land
        of Uz, and all the kings of the land of the Philistines (and [their cities
        of] Ashkelon, Gaza, Ekron, and the remnant of Ashdod); '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Edom, Moab, and the children of Ammon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'all the kings of Tyre, all the kings of Sidon, and the kings of the
        islands and the coastlands across the [Mediterranean] Sea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Dedan, Tema, Buz [the neighboring tribes north of Arabia], and all
        who clip off the side-growth of their hair;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'all the kings of Arabia and all the kings of the foreign population
        who live in the desert; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'all the kings of Zimri, all the kings of Elam (Persia), and all the
        kings of Media; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "all the kings of the north, far and near, one after another\u2014and
        all the kingdoms of the world which are on the face of the earth. And the
        king of Sheshach (Babylon) shall drink after them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CThen you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts,
        the God of Israel, \u201CDrink, be drunk, vomit, and fall to rise no more
        because of the sword which I will send among you.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And if they refuse to take the cup from your hand to drink, then
        you will say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u201CYou shall
        surely drink! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For behold, I am beginning to work disaster in the city which is
        called by My Name, and shall you go unpunished? You will not be exempt from
        punishment, for I am calling for a sword against all the inhabitants of the
        earth,\u201D says the Lord of hosts.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CTherefore prophesy all these words against them and say to
        them:\u2018The Lord will roar from on highAnd utter His voice from His holy
        dwelling;He will roar mightily against His fold and pasture.He will jubilantly
        shout like those who tread the grapes [in the wine press],Against all the
        inhabitants of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "A noise has come to the end of the earth,For the Lord has a controversy
        with and an indictment against the nations.He is entering into judgment with
        all mankind;As for the wicked, He has given them to the sword,\u2019 says
        the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts,\u201CBehold, evil is going forthFrom
        nation to nation,And a great whirling tempest is risingFrom the remotest
        part of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CAnd those slain by the Lord on that day will be from one end
        of the earth to the other end of the earth. They will not be lamented (mourned
        over with expressions of grief) or gathered or buried; they will be like
        dung on the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Wail, you shepherds, and cry;And roll in ashes, you masters of the
        flock.For the days of your slaughter and of your dispersions have come in
        full,And you will fall and be broken into pieces like a choice vessel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The shepherds will have no way to flee,Nor the masters of the flock
        any [way of] escape.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'A voice! The cry of the shepherdsAnd the wailing of the masters of
        the flock!For the Lord is destroying their pasture,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And the peaceful folds are devastated and made silentBecause of the
        fierce anger of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "He has left His lair like the lion;For their land has become a horrorBecause
        of the fierceness of the oppressorAnd because of the Lord\u2019s fierce anger.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cities of Judah Warned'
      title: Cities of Judah Warned
      number: 1
      content: '  In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king
        of Judah, this word came from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, \u2018Stand in the court of the Lord\u2019s
        house [Jeremiah], and speak to all [the people of] the cities of Judah who
        have come to worship in the Lord\u2019s house all the words that I have commanded
        you to speak to them. Do not omit a word! "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "It may be that they will listen and everyone will turn from his wickedness,
        so that I may relent and reverse [My decision concerning] the disaster which
        I am planning to do to them because of their malevolent deeds.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you will say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CIf you
        will not listen to Me and obey My law which I have set before you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and listen and follow [carefully] the words of My servants the prophets,
        whom I have been sending to you repeatedly\u2014though you have not listened\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: A Plot to Murder Jeremiah'
      title: A Plot to Murder Jeremiah
      number: 6
      content: "then I will make this house [the temple] like Shiloh, and I will
        make this city [subject to] the curse of all nations of the earth [because
        it will be so vile in their sight].\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The priests and the [false] prophets and all the people heard Jeremiah
        speaking these words in the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now when Jeremiah finished proclaiming everything that the Lord had
        commanded him to speak to all the people, the priests and the [false] prophets
        and all the people seized him, saying, \u201CYou must die! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Why have you prophesied in the name of the Lord saying, \u2018This
        house will be like Shiloh [after the ark of the Lord had been taken by our
        enemies] and this city [Jerusalem] will be desolate, without inhabitant\u2019?\u201D
        And all the people were gathered around Jeremiah in the [outer area of the]
        house of the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When the princes (court officials) of Judah heard these things, they
        came up from the king\u2019s house to the house of the Lord and sat in the
        entrance of the New Gate of the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the priests and the [false] prophets said to the princes and
        to all the people, \u201CThis man is deserving of death, for he has prophesied
        against this city as you have heard with your own ears.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jeremiah spoke to all the princes and to all the people, saying,
        \u201CThe Lord sent me to prophesy against this house and against this city
        all the words that you have heard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore, now change your ways and your deeds and obey the voice
        of the Lord your God; then the Lord will relent and reverse His decision
        concerning the misfortune which He has pronounced against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As for me, behold, I am in your hands; do with me as seems good and
        suitable to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jeremiah Is Spared'
      title: Jeremiah Is Spared
      number: 15
      content: "But know for certain that if you put me to death, you will bring
        innocent blood on yourselves and on this city and on its inhabitants, for
        in truth the Lord has sent me to you to speak all these words in your hearing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the princes and all the people said to the priests and to the
        [false] prophets, \u201CThis man is not deserving of death, for he has spoken
        to us in the name of the Lord our God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then some of the elders of the land stood up and spoke to all the
        assembly of the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CMicah of Moresheth prophesied in the days of Hezekiah king
        of Judah; and he spoke to all the people of Judah, saying, \u2018Thus says
        the Lord of hosts,\u201CZion will be plowed like a field,And Jerusalem will
        become [heaps of] ruins,And the mountain of the house [of the Lord\u2014Mount
        Moriah, on which stands the temple, shall become covered not with buildings,
        but] like a densely wooded height.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Did Hezekiah king of Judah and all Judah put Micah to death? Did
        he not [reverently] fear the Lord and entreat the favor of the Lord? And
        did not the Lord relent and reverse His decision concerning the misfortune
        which He had pronounced against them? But [here] we are [thinking of] committing
        a great evil against ourselves.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And there was also a man who prophesied in the name of the Lord,
        Uriah the son of Shemaiah of Kiriath-jearim, who prophesied against this
        city and against this land in words similar to all those of Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when Jehoiakim the king, with all his mighty men and all the
        princes, heard his words, the king sought to put Uriah to death; but when
        Uriah heard of it, he was afraid and fled and escaped to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Jehoiakim the king sent men to Egypt: Elnathan the son of Achbor
        and certain [other] men with him [went] to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And they brought Uriah [God\u2019s spokesman] from Egypt and led
        him to King Jehoiakim, who executed him with a sword and threw his dead body
        among the graves of the common people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: But the hand of Ahikam the son of Shaphan was with Jeremiah, so that
        he was not given into the hands of the people to put him to death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Nations to Submit to Nebuchadnezzar'
      title: The Nations to Submit to Nebuchadnezzar
      number: 1
      content: '  In the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah the son of Josiah, king
        of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the Lord: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord to me, \u201CMake for yourself bonds and yokes
        and put them on your neck, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and send word to the king of Edom, to the king of Moab, to the king
        of the sons of Ammon, to the king of Tyre, and to the king of Sidon by the
        messengers who come to Jerusalem to Zedekiah king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Command them to go to their masters, saying, \u2018Thus says the
        Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, you shall say this to your masters: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI have made the earth, the men and the animals that are on
        the face of the earth by My great power and by My outstretched arm, and I
        will give it to whomever pleases Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now I have given all these lands into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon, My servant and instrument, and I have also given the wild
        animals of the field to serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All nations shall serve him and his son and his grandson until the
        [appointed] time [of punishment] for his own land comes; then many nations
        and great kings shall make him their servant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut any nation or kingdom that will not serve this same Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon and put its neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon, that
        nation I will punish,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cwith the sword, with famine
        and with pestilence (virulent disease), until I have destroyed it by Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s
        hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And as for you, do not listen to your [counterfeit] prophets, your
        diviners, your dreams and dreamers, your soothsayers or your sorcerers, who
        say to you, \u2018You will not serve the king of Babylon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For they prophesy a lie to you which will cause you to be removed
        far from your land; and I will drive you out and you will perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the nation which will bow its neck under the yoke of the king
        of Babylon and serve him, that nation I will let remain on its own land,\u201D
        says the Lord, \u201Cto cultivate it and live in it.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I spoke to Zedekiah king of Judah in the same way, saying, \u201CBring
        your necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon and serve him and his people,
        and live! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Why will you die, you and your people, by the sword, by famine and
        by virulent disease, as the Lord has spoken to any nation which will not
        serve the king of Babylon? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Do not listen to and believe the words of the [false] prophets who
        are saying to you, \u2018You will not serve the king of Babylon,\u2019 for
        they prophesy a lie to you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "for I have not sent them,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cbut they are
        prophesying falsely in My Name, in order that I may drive you out and that
        you may perish, you [together] with the [false] prophets who prophesy to
        you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then I said to the priests and to all these people, saying, \u201CThus
        says the Lord: Do not listen to the words of your [false] prophets who are
        prophesying to you, saying, \u2018Behold, the articles of the Lord\u2019s
        house will now shortly be brought back from Babylon\u2019; for they are prophesying
        a lie to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not listen to them; serve the king of Babylon, and live! Why should
        this city become a ruin? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But if they are [true] prophets, and if the word of the Lord is [really
        spoken] by them, let them now entreat the Lord of hosts that the articles
        which are [still] left in the house of the Lord, in the house of the king
        of Judah and in Jerusalem may not go to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts concerning the [bronze] pillars,
        the [bronze] Sea, the [bronze] bases [of the ten basins in Solomon\u2019s
        temple used for washing sacrificial animals], and the rest of the articles
        that are left in this city (Jerusalem), "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon did not take when he carried
        Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, into exile from Jerusalem to
        Babylon, along with all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yes, thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, concerning the
        articles which remain in the house of the Lord, in the house of the king
        of Judah and in Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018They will be carried to Babylon and they will be there until
        the day that I visit them [with My favor],\u2019 says the Lord. \u2018Then
        I will bring them back and restore them to this place.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hananiah\u2019s False Prophecy"
      title: "Hananiah\u2019s False Prophecy"
      number: 1
      content: "  In the same year, in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king
        of Judah, in the fourth year and the fifth month, the [false] prophet Hananiah
        the son of Azzur, who was from Gibeon [one of the priests\u2019 cities],
        spoke [without godly authority] to me in the house of the Lord in the presence
        of the priests and all the people, saying: "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018I have
        broken the yoke of the king of Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Within two years I am going to bring back to this place all the articles
        of the Lord\u2019s house, which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon took away
        from this place and carried to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I will also bring back to this place Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim,
        king of Judah, along with all the exiles from Judah who went to Babylon,\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018for I will break the yoke of the king of Babylon.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the prophet Jeremiah spoke to the prophet Hananiah in the presence
        of the priests and all the people who stood in the house of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and the prophet Jeremiah said, \u201CAmen! May the Lord do so; may
        the Lord confirm and fulfill your words which you have prophesied to bring
        back the articles of the Lord\u2019s house and all the captives, from Babylon
        to this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nevertheless, listen now to this word which I am about to speak in
        your hearing and in the hearing of all the people! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The prophets who were before me and before you from ancient times
        prophesied against many lands and against great kingdoms, of war and of disaster
        and of virulent disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But as for the prophet who [on the contrary] prophesies of peace,
        when that prophet\u2019s word comes to pass, [only] then will it be known
        that the Lord has truly sent him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Hananiah the [false] prophet took the yoke off the neck of the
        prophet Jeremiah and smashed it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Hananiah spoke in the presence of all the people, saying, \u201CThus
        says the Lord, \u2018Even so within two full years I will break the yoke
        of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon from the neck of all the nations.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        Then the prophet Jeremiah went his way.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The word of the Lord came to Jeremiah [some time] after Hananiah
        the prophet had broken the yoke off the neck of the prophet Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo and tell Hananiah, \u2018The Lord says this, \u201CYou have
        broken yokes of wood, but you have made in their place bars of iron.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CI have
        put the iron yoke [of servitude] on the neck of all these nations, that they
        may serve Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon; and they will serve him. And I
        have even given him the beasts of the field.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the prophet Jeremiah said to Hananiah the prophet, \u201CListen
        now, Hananiah, the Lord has not sent you, and you have made this people trust
        in a lie. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord, \u2018Behold, I am about to send you
        away from the face of the earth. This year you will die, because you have
        spoken and counseled rebellion against the Lord.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So Hananiah the [false] prophet died [two months later], the same
        year, in the seventh month.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Message to the Exiles'
      title: Message to the Exiles
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the words of the letter which Jeremiah the prophet
        sent from Jerusalem to the rest of the elders in exile and to the priests,
        the prophets and all the people whom Nebuchadnezzar had taken into captivity
        from Jerusalem to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '(This was after King Jeconiah and the queen mother, the eunuchs,
        the princes (court officials) of Judah and Jerusalem, the craftsmen and the
        smiths had departed from Jerusalem.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The letter was hand-carried by Elasah the son of Shaphan and Gemariah
        the son of Hilkiah, whom Zedekiah king of Judah sent to Babylon to Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CSo says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, to all the captives
        whom I have sent into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018Build houses and live in them; plant gardens and eat their
        fruit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Take wives and have sons and daughters; take wives for your sons
        and give your daughters in marriage, that they may bear sons and daughters;
        multiply there and do not decrease [in number]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Seek peace and well-being for the city where I have sent you into
        exile, and pray to the Lord on its behalf; for in its peace (well-being)
        you will have peace.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Do not
        let your [false] prophets who are among you and your diviners deceive you;
        pay no attention and attach no significance to the dreams which they dream
        or to yours, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "for they prophesy falsely to you in My Name. I have not sent them,\u2019
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord, \u2018When seventy years [of exile]
        have been completed for Babylon, I will visit (inspect) you and keep My good
        promise to you, to bring you back to this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For I know the plans and thoughts that I have for you,\u2019 says
        the Lord, \u2018plans for peace and well-being and not for disaster, to give
        you a future and a hope. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then you will call on Me and you will come and pray to Me, and I
        will hear [your voice] and I will listen to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then [with a deep longing] you will seek Me and require Me [as a
        vital necessity] and [you will] find Me when you search for Me with all your
        heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will be found by you,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018and I will restore
        your fortunes and I will [free you and] gather you from all the nations and
        from all the places where I have driven you,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018and
        I will bring you back to the place from where I sent you into exile.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBecause you [who have remained in Jerusalem] have said, \u2018The
        Lord has raised up prophets for us in Babylon,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "thus says the Lord concerning the king who sits on the throne of
        David, and concerning all the people who live in this city, your brothers
        (fellow people of Judah) who did not go with you into captivity\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "thus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018Behold (listen very carefully),
        I am sending the sword, famine, and virulent disease (pestilence) on them,
        and I will make them like rotten figs that are so bad they cannot be eaten. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will pursue them with the sword, with famine and with virulent
        disease; and I will make them a terror (warning) to all the kingdoms of the
        earth, to be a curse, a horror, a hissing, and a disgrace among all the nations
        to which I have driven them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "because they have not listened to and honored My words,\u2019 says
        the Lord, \u2018which I sent to them again and again by My servants the prophets.
        Moreover, you [exiles] did not listen [either],\u2019 says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Hear, therefore, the word of the Lord, all you exiles whom I have
        sent away from Jerusalem to Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, concerning
        Ahab the son of Kolaiah and concerning Zedekiah the son of Maaseiah, who
        are prophesying lies to you in My Name, \u2018Behold, I will hand them over
        to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and he will slaughter them before your
        eyes [yes, all the false prophets in Babylon whom you follow shall die]! "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Because of them, this curse shall be taken up and used by all the
        exiles from Judah who are in Babylon, saying, \u201CMay the Lord make you
        like Zedekiah and like Ahab, whom the king of Babylon roasted in the fire, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "because they have acted foolishly in Israel and have committed adultery
        with their neighbors\u2019 wives and in My Name have spoken false and concocted
        words, which I did not command them. I am He who knows and I am a witness,\u201D
        says the Lord.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Also you shall speak to Shemaiah of Nehelam [among the exiles in
        Babylon], saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Because
        you have sent letters in your own name to all the people who are in Jerusalem,
        and to Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah, the priest, and to all the priests,
        saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThe Lord has made you [Zephaniah] priest instead of Jehoiada
        the [deputy] priest, to be the overseer in the house of the Lord over every
        madman who prophesies, to put him in the stocks and in the iron collar, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'now therefore [continued the letter from Shemaiah in Babylon to Zephaniah
        in Jerusalem], why have you not rebuked Jeremiah of Anathoth, who prophesies
        to you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For he has sent word to us in Babylon, saying, \u2018This captivity
        [of yours] will be long; build houses and live in them and plant gardens
        and eat their fruit.\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Zephaniah the priest read this letter to Jeremiah the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then came the word of the Lord to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CSend [this message] to all the exiles, saying, \u2018Thus says
        the Lord concerning Shemaiah of Nehelam, \u201CBecause Shemaiah has prophesied
        to you, although I did not send him, and he has made you trust in a lie,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord, \u201CBehold, I am about to punish
        Shemaiah of Nehelam and his descendants. He will not have anyone [born] to
        live among this people, nor will he see the good that I am about to do to
        My people,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cbecause he has spoken and preached
        rebellion against the Lord.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Freedom from Captivity Promised'
      title: Freedom from Captivity Promised
      number: 1
      content: '  The word which came to Jeremiah from the Lord: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord God of Israel, \u2018Write in a book all
        the words which I have spoken to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For behold (hear this), the days are coming,\u2019 says the Lord,
        \u2018when I will restore the fortunes of My people Israel and Judah,\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018and I will return them to the land that I gave to their
        forefathers and they will take possession of it.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now these are the words the Lord spoke concerning Israel and Judah:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord,\u2018We have heard a terrified voiceOf
        panic and dread, and there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Ask now, and seeWhether a man can give birth [to a child].Why then
        do I see every manWith his hands on his loins, as a woman in labor?Why have
        all faces turned pale?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Alas! for that day is great,There is none like it;It is the time
        of Jacob\u2019s [unequaled] trouble,But he will be saved from it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018It shall come about on that day,\u2019 says the Lord of hosts,
        \u2018that I will break the yoke off your neck and I will tear off your bonds
        and force apart your shackles; and strangers will no longer make slaves of
        the people [of Israel]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But they shall serve the Lord their God and [the descendant of] David
        their King, whom I will raise up for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Fear not, O Jacob My servant,\u2019 says the Lord,\u2018Nor be dismayed
        or downcast, O Israel;For behold, I will save you from a distant land [of
        exile]And your descendants from the land of their captivity.Jacob will return
        and will be quiet and at ease,And no one will make him afraid.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For I am with you,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018to save you;For I will
        destroy completely all the nations where I have scattered you,But I will
        not destroy you completely.But I will judge and discipline you fairlyAnd
        will by no means regard you as guiltless and leave you unpunished.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord,\u2018Your wound is incurableAnd your
        injury is beyond healing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'There is no one to plead your cause;No [device to close and allow
        the] healing of your wound,No recovery for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'All your lovers (allies) have forgotten you;They do not seek and
        long for you.For I have injured you with the wound of an enemy,With the punishment
        of a cruel and merciless foe,Because your guilt is greatAnd your sins are
        glaring and innumerable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Why do you cry out over your injury [since it is the natural result
        of your sin]?Your pain is incurable (deadly).Because your guilt is greatAnd
        your sins are glaring and innumerable,I have done these things to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore all who devour you will be devoured;And all your adversaries,
        every one of them, will go into captivity.And they who plunder you will become
        plunder,And all who prey upon you I will give for prey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Restoration of Jacob'
      title: Restoration of Jacob
      number: 17
      content: "For I will restore health to youAnd I will heal your wounds,\u2019
        says the Lord,\u2018Because they have called you an outcast, saying:\u201CThis
        is Zion; no one seeks her and no one cares for her.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord,\u2018Behold (hear this), I will restore
        the fortunes of the tents of JacobAnd have mercy on his dwelling places;The
        city will be rebuilt on its [old, mound-like] ruin,And the palace will stand
        on its rightful place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'From them (city, palace) will come [songs of] thanksgivingAnd the
        voices of those who dance and celebrate.And I will multiply them and they
        will not be diminished [in number];I will also honor them and they will not
        be insignificant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Their children too will be as in former times,And their congregation
        will be established before Me;And I will punish all their oppressors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Their prince will be one of them,And their ruler will come forward
        from among them.I will bring him near and he shall approach Me,For who is
        he who would have the boldness and would dare [on his own initiative] to
        risk his life to approach Me?\u2019 says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018Then you shall be My people,And I will be your God.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Behold, the tempest of the Lord!Wrath has gone forth,A sweeping and
        gathering tempest;It will burst on the head of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The fierce (righteous) anger of the Lord will not turn backUntil He
        has fulfilled and until He has accomplishedThe intent of His heart (mind);In
        the latter days you will understand this.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Mourning Turned to Joy"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Mourning Turned to Joy"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt that time,\u201D says the Lord, \u201CI will be the God
        of all the families of Israel, and they shall be My people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CThe people who survived the swordFound grace
        in the wilderness [of exile]\u2014Israel (the Northern Kingdom), when it
        went to find its rest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The Lord appeared to me (Israel) from ages past, saying,\u201CI have
        loved you with an everlasting love;Therefore with lovingkindness I have drawn
        you and continued My faithfulness to you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Again I will build you and you will be rebuilt,O Virgin Israel!You
        will again be adorned with your tambourines and  timbrelsAnd go out to the
        dances of those who celebrate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Again you will plant vineyardsOn the mountains of Samaria;The planters
        will plantAnd enjoy the [abundant] fruit [in peace].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For there will be a day when the watchmenOn the hills of Ephraim
        cry out,\u2018Arise, and let us go up to Zion,To the Lord our God.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For thus says the Lord,\u201CSing aloud with gladness for Jacob,And
        shout for the first and foremost of the nations [the chosen people, Israel];Proclaim,
        give praise and say,\u2018O Lord save Your people,The remnant of Israel!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Behold, I am bringing them from the north country,And I will gather
        them from the remote parts of the earth,Among them [will be] the blind and
        the lame,The woman with child and she who labors in childbirth, together;A
        great company, they will return here [to Jerusalem].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They will come with weeping [in repentance and for joy],And by [their]
        prayer [for the future] I will lead them;I will make them walk by streams
        of waters,On a straight path in which they will not stumble,For I am a Father
        to Israel,And Ephraim (Israel) is My firstborn.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Hear the word of the Lord, O you nations,And declare it in the isles
        and coastlands far away,And say, \u201CHe who scattered Israel will gather
        himAnd will keep him as a shepherd keeps his flock.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the Lord has ransomed JacobAnd has redeemed him from the hand
        of him who was stronger than he.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThey will come and sing aloud and shout for joy on the height
        of Zion,And will be radiant [with joy] over the goodness of the Lord\u2014For
        the grain, for the new wine, for the oil,And for the young of the flock and
        the herd.And their life will be like a watered garden,And they shall never
        sorrow or languish again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the virgin will rejoice in the dance,And the young men and old,
        together,For I will turn their mourning into joyAnd will comfort them and
        make them rejoice after their sorrow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will fully satisfy the soul of the priests with abundance,And My
        people will be satisfied with My goodness,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CA voice is heard in Ramah,Lamentation (songs
        of mourning) and bitter weeping.Rachel (Israel) is weeping for her children;She
        refuses to be comforted for her children,Because they are gone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CRestrain your voice from weepingAnd your
        eyes from tears,For your work will be rewarded,\u201D says the Lord;\u201CAnd
        your children will return from the enemy\u2019s land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "There is [confident] hope for your future,\u201D says the Lord;\u201CYour
        children will come back to their own country.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I have surely heard Ephraim (Israel) moaning and grieving,\u2018You
        have chastised me, and I was chastised,Like a bull unaccustomed to the yoke
        or an untrained calf;Bring me back that I may be restored,For You are the
        Lord my God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "After I turned away [from You], I repented;After I was instructed,
        I struck my thigh [in remorse];I was ashamed and even humiliatedBecause I
        carried the disgrace of my youth [as a nation].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Is Ephraim My dear son?Is he a darling and beloved child?For as often
        as I have spoken against him,I certainly still remember him.Therefore My
        affection is renewed and My heart longs for him;I will surely have mercy
        on him,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CPlace for yourself road signs [toward Canaan],Make for yourself
        guideposts;Turn your thought and attention to the highway,To the way by which
        you went [into exile].Retrace your steps, O virgin of Israel,Return to these
        your cities.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "How long will you hesitate [to return],O you faithless and renegade
        daughter?For the Lord has created a new thing in the land [of Israel]:A woman
        will encompass (tenderly love) a man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201COnce more they
        will speak these words in the land of Judah (the Southern Kingdom) and in
        her cities when I restore their fortunes and release them from exile,\u2018The
        Lord bless you, O habitation of justice and righteousness,O holy mountain!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And [the people of] Judah and all its cities will live there together\u2014the
        farmer and they who wander about with flocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For I [fully] satisfy the weary soul, and I replenish every languishing
        and sorrowful person.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: A New Covenant'
      title: A New Covenant
      number: 26
      content: 'At this I (Jeremiah) awoke and looked, and my [trancelike] sleep
        was sweet [in the assurance it gave] to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBehold (listen carefully), the days are coming,\u201D says
        the Lord, \u201Cwhen I will sow the house of Israel and the house of Judah
        with the seed of man and with the seed of beast. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "It will be that as I have watched over them to uproot and to break
        down, to overthrow, destroy, and afflict with disaster, so I will watch over
        them to build and to plant [with good],\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIn those days they will not say again,\u2018The fathers have
        eaten sour grapes,And the children\u2019s teeth are set on edge.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "But everyone will die [only] for his own wickedness; every man who
        eats sour grapes\u2014his [own] teeth shall be set on edge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cwhen
        I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel (the Northern Kingdom)
        and with the house of Judah (the Southern Kingdom), "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "not like the covenant which I made with their fathers in the day
        when I took them by the hand to bring them out of the land of Egypt, My covenant
        which they broke, although I was a husband to them,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CBut this is the covenant which I will make with the house of
        Israel after those days,\u201D says the Lord, \u201CI will put My law within
        them, and I will write it on their hearts; and I will be their God, and they
        will be My people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And each man will no longer teach his neighbor and his brother, saying,
        \u2018Know the Lord,\u2019 for they will all know Me [through personal experience],
        from the least of them to the greatest,\u201D says the Lord. \u201CFor I
        will forgive their wickedness, and I will no longer remember their sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Thus says the Lord,Who gives the sun for light by dayAnd the fixed
        order of the moon and of the stars for light by night,Who stirs up the sea\u2019s
        roaring billows or stills the waves when they roar;The Lord of hosts is His
        name:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CIf this fixed order departsFrom before Me,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThen
        the descendants of Israel also will ceaseFrom being a nation before Me forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Thus says the Lord,\u201CIf the heavens above can be measuredAnd
        the foundations of the earth searched out below,Then I will also cast off
        and abandon all the descendants of IsraelFor all that they have done,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cwhen
        the city [of Jerusalem] will be rebuilt for the Lord from the Tower of Hananel
        to the Corner Gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The measuring line will go out farther straight ahead to the hill
        Gareb; then it will turn to Goah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And the whole valley (Hinnom) of the dead bodies and [the hill] of
        the ashes [long dumped there from the temple sacrifices], and all the fields
        as far as the brook Kidron, to the corner of the Horse Gate toward the east,
        shall be holy to the Lord. It (the city) will not be uprooted or overthrown
        anymore to the end of the age.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Imprisoned'
      title: Jeremiah Imprisoned
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord in the tenth year
        of Zedekiah king of Judah, which was the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now at that time the army of the king of Babylon was besieging Jerusalem,
        and Jeremiah the prophet was shut up in the court of the guard, which was
        in the house of the king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For Zedekiah [the last] king of Judah had locked him up, saying,
        \u201CWhy do you prophesy [disaster] and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CBehold,
        I am giving this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he shall
        take it; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Zedekiah king of Judah will not escape from the hand of the Chaldeans,
        but he will surely be given into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he
        will speak with him face to face and see him eye to eye; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and he will lead Zedekiah to Babylon, and he will be there until
        I visit him [for evaluation and judgment],\u201D says the Lord. \u201CIf
        you fight against the Chaldeans, you will not succeed\u201D\u2009\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Jeremiah [answered King Zedekiah and] said, \u201CThe word of
        the Lord came to me, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Behold (listen carefully), Hanamel the son of Shallum your
        uncle is coming to you, saying, \u201CBuy my field that is in Anathoth, for
        you have the right of redemption to buy it [in accordance with the law].\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Hanamel my uncle\u2019s son came to me in the court of the guard
        in accordance with the word of the Lord, and he said to me, \u2018Please
        buy my field that is at Anathoth, which is in the land of Benjamin, for you
        have the right of inheritance and the redemption is yours; buy it for yourself.\u2019
        Then I knew that this was the word of the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI bought the field that was at Anathoth from Hanamel my uncle\u2019s
        son, and weighed out the money for him, seventeen shekels of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I signed the deed and sealed it, and called in witnesses, and weighed
        out the money on the scales. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So I took the deeds of the purchase, both the sealed copy containing
        the terms and conditions, and the unsealed copy; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and I gave the purchase deed to Baruch the son of Neriah, the son
        of Mahseiah, in the sight of Hanamel my uncle\u2019s son and in sight of
        the witnesses who signed the purchase deed, in the presence of all the Jews
        who were sitting in the court of the guard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I commanded Baruch in their presence, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CTake
        these deeds, both this purchase deed which is sealed and this unsealed deed,
        and put them in an earthen jar, that they may last a long time.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jeremiah Prays and God Explains'
      title: Jeremiah Prays and God Explains
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CHouses
        and fields and vineyards will again be purchased in this land.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CNow when I had delivered the purchase deed to Baruch the son
        of Neriah, I prayed to the Lord, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Ah Lord God! Behold, You have made the heavens and the earth
        by Your great power and by Your outstretched arm! There is nothing too difficult
        or too wonderful for You\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You who show lovingkindness to thousands, but repay the wickedness
        (sin, guilt) of the fathers into the bosom of their children after them [that
        is, calling the children to account for the sins of their fathers], O great
        and mighty God; the Lord of hosts is His name; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'great [are You] in counsel and mighty in deed, whose eyes are open
        to all the ways of the sons of men, to reward or repay each one according
        to his ways and according to the fruit of his deeds; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'who set signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, and even to this
        day [continues to do so] both in Israel and among mankind; and You have made
        a name for Yourself, as at this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You brought Your people Israel out of the land of Egypt with signs
        and wonders, with a strong hand and with an outstretched arm and with great
        terror; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and gave them this land, which You swore to their forefathers to
        give them, a land [of plenty] flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They entered and took possession of it, but they did not obey Your
        voice or walk in Your law; they have done nothing of all that You commanded
        them to do. Therefore You have caused all this disaster and suffering to
        come upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'See the siege ramps [of mounded earth that the enemy has built against
        the walls]; they have come up to the city to capture it. And the city is
        given into the hand of the Chaldeans [of Babylon] who fight against it, because
        of the sword, the famine and the virulent disease [that have overcome the
        people]. What You have spoken has come to pass, and behold, You see it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Yet, O Lord God, You said to me, \u201CBuy the field with money and
        get witnesses,\u201D even though the city is given into the hands of the
        Chaldeans.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then came the word of the Lord to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am the Lord, the God of all flesh; is there anything
        too difficult for Me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord, \u201CBehold, I am about to give this
        city into the hand of the Chaldeans and into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon, and he will take it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The Chaldeans who are fighting against this city will come in and
        set this city on fire and burn it, along with the houses on whose roofs incense
        has been offered to Baal and drink offerings have been poured out to other
        gods to provoke Me to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For the children of Israel and the children of Judah have done only
        evil in My sight from their youth; for the children of Israel have been provoking
        Me to anger by the [idols that are the] work of their hands,\u201D says the
        Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CFrom the day that they built it [during the reign of Solomon],
        even to this day, this city has been such a provocation of My anger and My
        wrath, that I must remove it from My sight, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "because of all the evil of the children of Israel and of the children
        of Judah which they have done to provoke Me to anger\u2014they, their kings,
        their princes, their priests, their prophets, the men of Judah and the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They have turned their back to Me and not their face; though I taught
        them repeatedly, yet they would not listen and receive instruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But they put their detestable things (idols) in the house which is
        called by My Name, to defile it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "They built the high places [for worship] of Baal in the Valley of
        Ben-hinnom (son of Hinnom) to make their sons and their daughters pass through
        the fire to [worship and honor] Molech\u2014which I had not commanded them
        nor had it entered My mind that they should do this repulsive thing, to cause
        Judah to sin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CNow therefore thus says the Lord God of Israel concerning this
        city of which you say, \u2018It is given into the hand of the king of Babylon
        by sword and by famine and by virulent disease.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Behold, I will gather them out of all countries to which I have driven
        them in My anger, in My wrath and in great indignation; and I will bring
        them back to this place and make them live in safety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'They will be My people, and I will be their God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and I will give them one heart and one way, that they may [reverently]
        fear Me forever, for their own good and for the good of their children after
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'I will make an everlasting covenant with them that I will do them
        good and not turn away from them; and I will put in their heart a fear and
        reverential awe of Me, so that they will not turn away from Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'I will rejoice over them to do them good, and I will faithfully plant
        them in this land with all My heart and with all My soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "For thus says the Lord, \u2018Just as I have brought all this great
        disaster on this people, so I am going to bring on them all the good that
        I am promising them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Fields will be bought in this land of which you say, \u201CIt is
        desolate, without man or animal; it is given into the hands of the Chaldeans.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "People will buy fields for money, sign deeds, seal them, and call
        in witnesses in the land of Benjamin, in the places around Jerusalem, in
        the cities of Judah, in the cities of the hill country, in the cities of
        the lowland, and in the cities of the South (the Negev); for I will restore
        their fortunes and release them from exile,\u2019 says the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Restoration Promised'
      title: Restoration Promised
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah the second time, while
        he was still confined in the court of the guard, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord who made the earth, the Lord who formed
        it to establish it\u2014the Lord is His name, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Call to Me and I will answer you, and tell you [and even show
        you] great and mighty things, [things which have been confined and hidden],
        which you do not know and understand and cannot distinguish.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For thus says the Lord, the God of Israel, concerning the houses
        of this city and the houses of the kings of Judah which are torn down to
        make a defense against the siege ramps and against the sword, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018While they (the besieged Jews) are coming to fight against
        the Chaldeans and to fill the houses with the dead bodies of men whom I have
        slain in My anger and in My wrath, for I have hidden My face [in disgust]
        from this city because of all their wickedness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, [in the restored Jerusalem] I will bring to it health and
        healing, and I will heal them; and I will reveal to them an abundance of
        peace (prosperity, security, stability) and truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will restore the fortunes of Judah and the fortunes of Israel and
        will rebuild them as they were at first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will cleanse them from all their wickedness (guilt) by which they
        have sinned against Me, and I will pardon (forgive) all their sins by which
        they rebelled against Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jerusalem will be to Me a name of joy, praise and glory before all
        the nations of the earth which will hear of all the good that I do for it,
        and they shall fear and tremble because of all the good and all the peace
        (prosperity, security, stability) that I provide for it.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, \u2018Yet again there will be heard in
        this place of which you say, \u201CIt is a [desolate] waste, without man
        and without animal\u201D\u2014even in the cities of Judah and in the streets
        of Jerusalem that are desolate, without man and without inhabitant and without
        animal\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "the [sound of the] voice of joy and the voice of gladness, the voice
        of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride, the [song-filled] voice of
        those who say,\u201CGive praise and thanks to the Lord of hosts,For the Lord
        is good;For His [steadfast] lovingkindness (mercy) endures forever\u201D; 
        and of those who bring a thank offering into the house of the Lord. For I
        will restore the fortunes of the land as they were at first,\u2019 says the
        Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018There will again be in this
        desolate place\u2014[a place] without man or animal\u2014and in all its cities,
        pastures for shepherds who rest their flocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Davidic Kingdom'
      title: The Davidic Kingdom
      number: 13
      content: "In the cities of the hill country, in the cities of the lowland,
        in the cities of the South (the Negev), in the land of Benjamin, in the places
        around Jerusalem and in the cities of Judah, the flocks will again pass under
        the hand of the one who counts them,\u2019 says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Behold, the days are coming,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018when
        I will fulfill the good word and promise which I have made regarding the
        house of Israel and the house of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In those days and at that time I will cause a righteous Branch of
        David to spring forth; and He (the Messiah) shall execute justice and righteousness
        on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "In those days Judah will be saved and [the people of] Jerusalem will
        live in safety; and this is the name by which she will be called: the Lord
        Our Righteousness (Justice).\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For thus says the Lord, \u2018David shall never lack a man (descendant)
        to sit on the throne of the house of Israel; "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and the Levitical priests shall never lack a man (descendant) to
        offer burnt offerings before Me and to burn grain offerings and to prepare
        sacrifices all day long.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The word of the Lord came to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, \u2018If you can break My covenant for
        the day and My covenant for the night, so that day and night do not take
        place at their appointed times, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'then My covenant may also be broken with David My servant so that
        he will not have a son to reign on his throne, and [My covenant may also
        be broken] with the Levitical priests, My ministers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As the host of [the stars of] heaven cannot be counted and the sand
        of the sea cannot be measured, so I will multiply the descendants of David
        My servant and the Levites who minister to Me.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CHave you not noticed what this people have spoken, saying,
        \u2018The two families [Israel the northern kingdom, and Judah the southern
        kingdom] which the Lord chose, He has rejected\u2019? Thus they despise My
        [chosen] people, no longer are they [considered] as a nation in their sight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u2018If My covenant with day and night does
        not stand, and if I have not established the fixed patterns of heaven and
        earth, [the whole order of nature,] "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then I would [also] reject the descendants of Jacob and David My
        servant, not taking from his descendants rulers over the descendants of Abraham,
        Isaac, and Jacob. But I will restore their fortunes, and will have mercy
        on them.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Prophecy against Zedekiah'
      title: A Prophecy against Zedekiah
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord when Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon and all his army, with all the kingdoms of the earth that
        were under his sovereignty and all the peoples, were fighting against Jerusalem
        and against all of its cities: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord God of Israel, \u2018Go and speak to Zedekiah
        king of Judah and tell him: \u201CThus says the Lord, \u2018Behold, I am
        giving this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he will set it
        on fire and burn it down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You will not escape from his hand, for you will definitely be captured
        and handed over to him; you will see the king of Babylon eye to eye, and
        he will speak with you face to face; and you will go to Babylon.\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet hear the word of the Lord, O Zedekiah king of Judah! Thus says
        the Lord concerning you, \u2018You will not die by the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You will die in peace; and as spices were burned for [the memory
        and honor of] your fathers, the former kings who reigned before you, so shall
        a [ceremonial] burning be made for you; and people will lament (grieve) for
        you, saying, \u201CAlas, lord (master)!\u201D\u2009\u2019 For I have spoken
        the word,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Jeremiah the prophet spoke all these words to Zedekiah king
        of Judah in Jerusalem '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'when the army of the king of Babylon was fighting against Jerusalem
        and against all the remaining cities of Judah, against Lachish and Azekah,
        for these were the [only] fortified cities among the cities of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The word came to Jeremiah from the Lord after King Zedekiah had made
        a covenant (solemn pledge) with all the [Hebrew] people who were [slaves]
        in Jerusalem to proclaim liberty to them: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'that every man should let his Hebrew slaves, male and female, go
        free, so that no one should make a slave of a Jew, his brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So all the princes and all the people who had entered into the covenant
        agreed that everyone would let his male servant and his female servant go
        free, and that no one would keep them in bondage any longer; they obeyed,
        and set them free. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But afterward they backed out [of the covenant] and made the male
        servants and the female servants whom they had set free return [to them],
        and brought the male servants and the female servants again into servitude.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u2018I made a covenant
        (solemn pledge) with your forefathers in the day that I brought them out
        of the land of Egypt, out of the house of bondage, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAt the end of seven years each of you shall set free his Hebrew
        brother who has sold himself [into servitude] or who has been sold to you
        and has served you six years, you shall release him from [serving] you; but
        your forefathers did not listen [submissively] to Me or obey Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So then you recently turned and repented, doing what was right in
        My sight, each man proclaiming release [from servitude] to his countryman
        [who was his bond servant]; and you had made a covenant before Me in the
        house which is called by My Name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Yet you backed out [of the covenant] and profaned My Name, and each
        man took back his servants, male and female, whom had been set free in accordance
        with their desire, and you brought them into servitude [again] to be your
        male servants and your female servants.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore says the Lord, \u2018You have not obeyed Me; you
        have not proclaimed liberty to your brother and your countryman. Behold (listen
        very carefully), I am proclaiming liberty to you\u2014[liberty to be put]
        to the sword, [liberty] to [be ravaged by] the virulent disease, and [liberty]
        to [be decimated by] famine,\u2019 says the Lord; \u2018and I will make you
        a horror and a warning to all the kingdoms of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The men who have violated My covenant, who have not kept the terms
        of the solemn pledge which they made before Me when they split the [sacrificial]
        calf in half, and then afterwards walked between its separated pieces [sealing
        their pledge to Me by placing a curse on themselves should they violate the
        covenant\u2014those men I will make like the calf]! "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The princes of Judah, the princes of Jerusalem, the high officials,
        the priests, and all the people of the land who passed between the parts
        of the calf, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will give into the hand of their enemies and into the hand of those
        who seek their lives. And [like the body of the calf] their dead bodies will
        be food for the birds of the sky and the beasts of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Zedekiah king of Judah and his princes I will place into the hand
        of their enemies and into the hand of those who seek their life, and into
        the hand of the army of the king of Babylon which has withdrawn from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Behold, I am going to command [the Chaldeans who rule Babylon],\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018and I will bring them back to this city; and they will
        fight against it and take it and set it on fire. I will make the cities of
        Judah a desolation without inhabitant.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Rechabites\u2019 Obedience"
      title: "The Rechabites\u2019 Obedience"
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord in the days of Jehoiakim
        the son of Josiah, king of Judah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to the house of the Rechabites and speak to them, and bring
        them into the house of the Lord, into one of the [side] chambers; then give
        them [who are pledged not to drink wine] some wine to drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So I took Jaazaniah the son of Jeremiah, the son of Habazziniah,
        and his brothers and all his sons and the whole house of the Rechabites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and I brought them into the house of the Lord, into the chamber of
        the sons of Hanan the son of Igdaliah, the man of God, which was near the
        chamber of the princes, above the chamber of Maaseiah the son of Shallum
        the doorkeeper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I set before the men of the house of the Rechabites pitchers
        full of wine, and cups, and I said to them, \u201CDrink wine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But they said, \u201CWe will not drink wine, for Jonadab the son
        of Rechab, our father, commanded us: \u2018You shall not drink wine, neither
        you nor your sons, forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Nor shall you build a house or sow seed or plant a vineyard or own
        one; but you shall live in tents all your days, that you may live many days
        in the land where you are sojourners (temporary residents).\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'We have obeyed the words of Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father,
        in all that he commanded us, in all our days we have never drunk wine, nor
        have our wives, our sons, or our daughters, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'nor have we built ourselves houses to live in; nor do we have vineyards
        or fields or seed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We have lived only in tents, and have obeyed and done [everything]
        according to all that Jonadab our father commanded us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Judah Rebuked'
      title: Judah Rebuked
      number: 11
      content: "But when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against the land,
        we said, \u2018Come and let us go to Jerusalem for fear of the army of the
        Chaldeans [who rule Babylon] and for fear of the army of the Arameans.\u2019
        So we have lived in Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then came the word of the Lord to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Go and
        say to the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, \u201CWill you
        not receive instruction by listening to My words and honoring them?\u201D
        says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThe command which Jonadab the son of Rechab gave to his sons
        not to drink wine has been observed [as a custom for more than two hundred
        years]. To this day they do not drink wine, for they have obeyed their father\u2019s
        command. But I have repeatedly spoken to you, yet you have not listened to
        Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I have also sent to you all My servants the prophets, sending them
        repeatedly, saying, \u2018Let every one of you turn now from his evil way
        and alter your behavior, and do not follow other gods to worship and serve
        them; and then you will live in the land which I have given to you and to
        your forefathers. But you have not submitted or listened to Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Indeed, the sons of Jonadab the son of Rechab have observed the command
        of their father which he gave them, but this people has not listened to Me.\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Behold
        (hear this), I am bringing on Judah and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem
        all the disaster that I have pronounced against them, because I have spoken
        to them, but they have not listened, and I have called to them, but they
        have not answered.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to the house of the Rechabites, \u201CThus says
        the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Because you have obeyed the command
        of Jonadab your father and have kept all his commands and have done according
        to all that he commanded you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CJonadab
        the son of Rechab shall never fail to have a man (descendant) to stand before
        Me always.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Scroll Read in the Temple"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Scroll Read in the Temple"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah,
        this word came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTake a scroll [of parchment] and write on it all the words
        which I have spoken to you concerning Israel and Judah, and all the nations,
        from the day I [first] spoke to you in the days of [King] Josiah until this
        day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "It may be that the house of Judah will hear all the disaster which
        I plan to bring on them, so that each one will turn from his evil way, that
        I may forgive their wickedness and their sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Jeremiah called Baruch the son of Neriah, and Baruch wrote on
        the scroll of the book all the words which Jeremiah dictated, [words] which
        the Lord had spoken to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jeremiah commanded Baruch, saying, \u201CI am [in hiding, virtually]
        restrained; I cannot go into the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So you go to the Lord\u2019s house on a day of fasting and read from
        the scroll the words of the Lord to the people which you have written as
        I dictated. And also you shall read them to all the people of Judah who come
        from their cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It may be that their supplication [for mercy] will come before the
        Lord, and everyone will turn from his evil way, for great is the anger and
        the wrath that the Lord has pronounced against this people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Baruch the son of Neriah did everything that Jeremiah the prophet
        commanded him, reading from [Jeremiah\u2019s scroll] the words of the Lord
        in the Lord\u2019s house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now in the fifth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah,
        in the ninth month, a fast was proclaimed before the Lord for all the people
        in Jerusalem and all the people who came to Jerusalem from the cities of
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Baruch read to all the people the words of Jeremiah from the
        scroll of the book in the house of the Lord, in the chamber of Gemariah the
        son of Shaphan the scribe, in the upper court, at the entry of the New Gate
        of the Lord\u2019s house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Micaiah the son of Gemariah, the son of Shaphan, had heard all
        the words of the Lord from the scroll, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "he went down to the king\u2019s house, into the scribe\u2019s chamber;
        and behold, all the princes were sitting there: Elishama the scribe, Delaiah
        the son of Shemaiah, Elnathan the son of Achbor, Gemariah the son of Shaphan,
        Zedekiah the son of Hananiah, and all the [other] princes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Micaiah declared to them all the words that he had heard when
        Baruch read from the scroll to all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore all the princes sent Jehudi the son of Nethaniah, the son
        of Shelemiah, the son of Cushi, to Baruch, saying, \u201CTake in your hand
        the scroll from which you have read to the people and come [to us].\u201D
        So Baruch the son of Neriah took the scroll in his hand and went to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CSit down now and read it to us.\u201D
        So Baruch read it to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now when they had heard all the words, they turned one to another
        in fear and said to Baruch, \u201CWe must surely report all these words to
        the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And they asked Baruch, \u201CTell us now, how did you write all these
        words? At his (Jeremiah\u2019s) dictation?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Baruch answered them, \u201CHe dictated all these words to me,
        and I wrote them with ink on the scroll.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Scroll Is Burned'
      title: The Scroll Is Burned
      number: 19
      content: "Then the princes said to Baruch, \u201CGo and hide, you and Jeremiah,
        and do not let anyone know where you are.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then they went into the court to the king, but they [first] put the
        scroll in the chamber of Elishama the scribe; then they reported all the
        words to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So the king sent Jehudi to get the scroll, and he took it out of
        the chamber of Elishama the scribe. And Jehudi read it to the king and all
        the princes who stood beside the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now it was the ninth month, and the king was sitting in the winter
        house, with a fire burning there in the brazier before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And after Jehudi had read three or four columns [of the scroll],
        King Jehoiakim would cut off that portion with a scribe\u2019s knife and
        throw it into the fire that was in the brazier, until the [entire] scroll
        was consumed by the fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Yet the king and all his servants who heard all these words were
        not afraid, nor did they tear their clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Even though Elnathan and Delaiah and Gemariah pleaded with the king
        not to burn the scroll, he would not listen to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: The Scroll Is Replaced'
      title: The Scroll Is Replaced
      number: 26
      content: "And the king commanded Jerahmeel the king\u2019s son, Seraiah the
        son of Azriel, and Shelemiah the son of Abdeel to seize Baruch the scribe
        and Jeremiah the prophet, but the Lord hid them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah after the king had burned
        the scroll containing the words which Baruch had written at the dictation
        of Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CTake another scroll and write on it all the former words that
        were on the first scroll which Jehoiakim the king of Judah burned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah you shall say, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord, \u201CYou have burned this scroll, saying, \u2018Why have
        you written on it that the king of Babylon will certainly come and destroy
        this land, and will cut off man and beast from it?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah,
        \u201CHe shall have no heir to sit on the throne of David, and his dead body
        shall be thrown out to the heat of the day and to the frost of the night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "I will also punish him and his descendants and his servants for their
        wickedness, and I will bring on them and the inhabitants of Jerusalem and
        the men of Judah all the destruction that I have declared against them\u2014but
        they would not listen.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Then Jeremiah took another scroll and gave it to Baruch the scribe,
        the son of Neriah, who wrote on it at the dictation of Jeremiah all the words
        of the scroll which Jehoiakim king of Judah had burned in the fire; and many
        similar words were added to them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Warns against Trust in Pharaoh'
      title: Jeremiah Warns against Trust in Pharaoh
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon made Zedekiah the son of Josiah
        king in the land of Judah so he reigned as king instead of Coniah (also called
        Jeconiah and Jehoiachin) the son of Jehoiakim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But neither he nor his servants nor the people of the land listened
        to the words of the Lord which He spoke through the prophet Jeremiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Yet King Zedekiah sent Jehucal the son of Shelemiah [along] with
        Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah, the priest, to the prophet Jeremiah, saying,
        \u201CPlease pray [now] to the Lord our God for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Jeremiah was coming and going among the people, for they had
        not [yet] put him in prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Meanwhile, Pharaoh\u2019s army had set out from Egypt; and when the
        Chaldeans who were besieging Jerusalem heard the news about them, they withdrew
        from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to the prophet Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u2018This is what you
        are to say to the king of Judah, who sent you to Me to inquire of Me: \u201CBehold,
        Pharaoh\u2019s army, which has come out to help you, will return to Egypt,
        to their own land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the Chaldeans [of Babylon] will come again and fight against
        this city, and they will capture it and set it on fire.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u2018Do not deceive yourselves, saying, \u201CThe
        Chaldeans will certainly stay away from us,\u201D for they will not stay
        away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jeremiah Imprisoned'
      title: Jeremiah Imprisoned
      number: 10
      content: "For even if you had defeated the whole army of the Chaldeans who
        fight against you, and there remained only the wounded men among them, yet
        they would rise up, every man confined in his tent, and burn down this city
        with fire.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now it happened when the army of the Chaldeans departed from Jerusalem
        for fear of Pharaoh\u2019s [approaching] army, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'that Jeremiah left Jerusalem [during the withdrawal of the Chaldean
        invaders] to go to [Anathoth, his hometown, in] the land of Benjamin to take
        possession of [the title to] the land [which he had purchased] there among
        the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When he was at the Gate of Benjamin, a captain of the guard whose
        name was Irijah, the son of Shelemiah the son of Hananiah was there; and
        he seized and arrested Jeremiah the prophet, saying, \u201CYou are deserting
        to join the Chaldeans [of Babylon]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Jeremiah said, \u201CThat is a lie! I am not deserting to join
        the Chaldeans.\u201D But the guard would not listen to him. So Irijah took
        Jeremiah and brought him to the princes (court officials). "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The princes were enraged with Jeremiah and beat him and put him in
        prison in the house of Jonathan the scribe\u2014for they had made that the
        prison. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When Jeremiah had come into the vaulted cell in the dungeon and had
        remained there many days,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Zedekiah the king sent and brought him out; and in his palace the
        king secretly asked him, \u201CIs there any word from the Lord?\u201D And
        Jeremiah said, \u201CThere is!\u201D Then he said, \u201CYou will be handed
        over to the king of Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Moreover, Jeremiah said to King Zedekiah, \u201CIn what way have
        I sinned against you, or against your servants, or against this people, that
        you have put me in prison? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Where then are your prophets who prophesied to you, saying, \u2018The
        king of Babylon will not come against you or against this land?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore now, please listen, O my lord the king; please let my petition
        come before you and be acceptable and do not make me return to the house
        of Jonathan the scribe, that I may not die there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then King Zedekiah commanded, and they committed Jeremiah to the
        court of the guardhouse, and a [round] loaf of bread from the bakers\u2019
        street was given to him daily, until all the bread in the city was gone.
        So Jeremiah remained [imprisoned] in the court of the guardhouse."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Thrown into the Cistern'
      title: Jeremiah Thrown into the Cistern
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Shephatiah the son of Mattan, and Gedaliah the son of Pashhur,
        and Jucal (also called Jehucal) the son of Shelemiah, and Pashhur the son
        of Malchijah heard the words that Jeremiah was speaking to all the people,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSo says the Lord, \u2018He who remains in this city will die
        by the sword, by famine, and by virulent disease (pestilence), but he who
        goes out to the Chaldeans [of Babylon] will live and have his [own] life
        as a reward and stay alive.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u2018This city will certainly be given into
        the hand of the army of the king of Babylon and he will take it.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore the princes (court officials) said to the king, \u201CPlease
        [we implore you] let this man [Jeremiah] be put to death; for [speaking]
        in this way he discourages and weakens [the will of] the soldiers who remain
        in this city and he discourages and weakens [the will of] all the people
        by speaking such words to them; for this man is not seeking the well-being
        of these people, but rather their harm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then King Zedekiah [fearing the princes] said, \u201CListen, he is
        in your hand; for the king is in no position to do anything against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they took Jeremiah and threw him into the cistern of Malchijah
        the king\u2019s son, which was in the court of the guardhouse; and they let
        Jeremiah down [into the cistern] with ropes. Now there was no water in the
        cistern but only mud, and Jeremiah sank in the mud. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now Ebed-melech the Ethiopian (Cushite), one of the eunuchs who was
        in the king\u2019s palace, heard that they had put Jeremiah in the cistern,
        and while the king was sitting in the Gate of Benjamin, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ebed-melech went out of the king\u2019s palace and spoke to the king,
        saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CMy lord the king, these men have acted wickedly in all that
        they have done to Jeremiah the prophet whom they have thrown into the cistern;
        and he will die [of hunger] where he is because of the famine, for there
        is no more bread in the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king commanded Ebed-melech the Ethiopian, saying, \u201CTake
        thirty men from here with you and lift Jeremiah the prophet out of the cistern
        before he dies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Ebed-melech took the men with him and went into the palace of
        the king to a place under the storeroom and took from there old rags and
        worn-out clothes and let them down by ropes into the cistern to Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Ebed-melech the Ethiopian said to Jeremiah, \u201CNow put these
        old rags and worn-out clothes under your armpits, then place the ropes under
        the padding\u201D; and Jeremiah did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So they pulled Jeremiah up with the ropes and took him up out of
        the cistern; and Jeremiah remained in the court of the guardhouse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then King Zedekiah sent and had Jeremiah the prophet brought to him
        at the third entrance that is in the house of the Lord. And the king said
        to Jeremiah, \u201CI am going to ask you something; hide nothing from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CIf I tell you, will you not
        certainly put me to death? Even if I do give you advice, you will not listen
        to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Interview with Zedekiah'
      title: Interview with Zedekiah
      number: 16
      content: "But King Zedekiah swore secretly to Jeremiah, \u201CAs the Lord lives,
        who made our lives, be assured that I will not put you to death or put you
        into the hand of these men who are seeking your life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CThus says the Lord God of hosts,
        the God of Israel, \u2018If you will go out and surrender to the officers
        of the king of Babylon, then you will live and this city will not be burned
        with fire; and you and your household will live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if you will not go out to the officers of the king of Babylon,
        then this city will be given into the hand of the Chaldeans [of Babylon]
        and they will set it on fire; and you yourself will not escape from their
        hand.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then King Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, \u201CI am afraid of the Jews
        [my former subjects] who have deserted to join the Chaldeans, for the enemy
        may put me into their hand and they will mock me and abuse me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Jeremiah said, \u201CThey will not hand you over [to them]. Please
        obey [the voice of] the Lord [who speaks to you through me] in what I am
        saying to you. Then it will go well with you and you will live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if you keep refusing to go out and surrender to them, this is
        the word [and the vision] which the Lord has shown me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018Then behold, all the women who are left in the palace of the
        king of Judah will be brought out to the officers of the king of Babylon
        and those women will say [to you, King Zedekiah],\u201CYour close friendsHave
        prevailed against your better judgment and have overpowered and deceived
        you;While your feet were sunk in the mire [of trouble],They turned back.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Also, all your wives and your children will be brought out to the
        Chaldeans; and you yourself will not escape from their hand, but you will
        be seized by the king of Babylon, and this city [Jerusalem] will be burned
        down with fire.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, \u201CLet no man know about this
        conversation and you will not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But if the princes (court officials) hear that I have talked with
        you, and they come to you and say, \u2018Tell us now what you said to the
        king and what he said to you; do not hide it from us and we will not execute
        you,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then you are to say to them, \u2018I was presenting my [humble] petition
        and plea to the king so that he would not send me back to Jonathan\u2019s
        house to die there.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then all the princes (court officials) came to Jeremiah and asked
        him [just what King Zedekiah had anticipated they would ask], and he reported
        to them in accordance with all that the king had commanded. So they stopped
        questioning him, since the conversation [with the king] had not been overheard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: So Jeremiah remained in the court of the guardhouse until the day
        that Jerusalem was captured [by the Chaldeans of Babylon].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem Captured'
      title: Jerusalem Captured
      number: 1
      content: '  Now regarding the capture of Jerusalem: In the ninth year of [the
        reign of] Zedekiah king of Judah, in the tenth month, Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon and all his army came against Jerusalem and besieged it; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and in the eleventh year of Zedekiah, in the fourth month, on the
        ninth day of the month, they breached the wall and broke into the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then all the officials of the king of Babylon came in and sat in
        the Middle Gate [establishing both military control of the city and their
        authority to judge the captives]: Nergal-sar-ezer, Samgar-nebu, Sar-sekim
        the Rab-saris (chief of the eunuchs), and Nergal-sar-ezer the Rab-mag (chief
        of the magicians), with all the rest of the officials of the king of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When Zedekiah the king of Judah and all the men of war saw them,
        they fled and escaped from the city at night by way of the king\u2019s garden,
        through the gate between the two walls; and the king went out toward the
        Arabah (Jordan Valley). "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the Chaldean (Babylonian) army pursued them and overtook Zedekiah
        in the plains of Jericho. When they had seized him, they brought him up to
        Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon at Riblah in the [Aramean] land of Hamath,
        where he passed sentence on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then at Riblah the king of Babylon killed the sons of Zedekiah before
        his eyes; the king of Babylon also killed all the nobles of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Moreover, he blinded Zedekiah and bound him with bronze shackles
        to take him to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Chaldeans also burned down the king\u2019s palace and the houses
        of the people, and they broke down the walls of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan the [chief executioner and] captain of the bodyguard
        took the rest of the people who remained in the city, along with those who
        had deserted and surrendered to him, and the rest of the [so-called better
        class of] people who were left and carried them into exile in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jeremiah Spared'
      title: Jeremiah Spared
      number: 10
      content: 'But Nebuzaradan the [Babylonian] captain of the bodyguard left behind
        in the land of Judah some of the poor people who had nothing, and gave them
        vineyards and fields at that time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon gave orders concerning Jeremiah
        through Nebuzaradan the captain of the bodyguard, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTake him and look after him; do nothing to harm him, but rather
        deal with him just as he asks of you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Nebuzaradan the captain of the bodyguard sent word, along with
        Nebushazban the Rab-saris (chief of the high officials), and Nergal-sar-ezer
        the Rab-mag (chief of the magicians), and all the leading officers of the
        king of Babylon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "they even sent and took Jeremiah out of the court of the guardhouse
        and entrusted him to Gedaliah [a prominent citizen], the son of Ahikam [who
        had once saved Jeremiah\u2019s life], the son of Shaphan, to take him home
        [with him to Mizpah]. So Jeremiah [was released and] lived among the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the word of the Lord had come to Jeremiah while he was [still]
        confined in the court of the guardhouse, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo and speak to Ebed-melech the Ethiopian, saying, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CBehold, I am about to bring
        My words [of judgment] against this city through disaster and not for good;
        and they will take place before you on that day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But I will protect you [Ebed-melech] on that day,\u201D says the
        Lord, \u201Cand you will not be handed over to the men of whom you are afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For I will certainly rescue you; and you will not fall by the sword,
        but you will have your [own] life as a reward of battle, because you have
        placed your trust in Me,\u201D says the Lord.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Remains in Judah'
      title: Jeremiah Remains in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The word which came to Jeremiah from the Lord after Nebuzaradan
        the captain of the bodyguard had released him from Ramah, when he had taken
        him bound in chains among all the captives of Jerusalem and Judah who were
        being taken as exiles to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the captain of the bodyguard had taken Jeremiah and said to him,
        \u201CThe Lord your God promised this disaster on this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the Lord has brought it about and has done just as He promised.
        Because you [people of Judah] have sinned against the Lord and did not listen
        to and honor His voice, therefore this thing has happened to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But now, listen carefully, [because of your innocence] I am freeing
        you today from the chains which are on your hands. If you would prefer to
        come with me to Babylon, come, and I will look after you [carefully]; but
        if you would prefer not to come with me to Babylon, then do not do so. Look,
        all the land is before you; go wherever it seems good and right (convenient)
        for you to go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "While Jeremiah was still hesitating, the captain of the bodyguard
        said, \u201CGo on back then to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan,
        whom the king of Babylon has appointed [governor] over the cities of Judah,
        and stay with him among the people; or else go wherever it seems right for
        you to go.\u201D So the captain of the bodyguard gave him an allowance of
        food and a gift and let him go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Jeremiah went to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam at Mizpah and stayed
        with him among the people who were left in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when all the commanders of the forces that were [scattered] in
        the open country [of Judah] and their men heard that the king of Babylon
        had made Gedaliah the son of Ahikam governor in the land [of Judah] and had
        put him in charge of the men, women, and children, those of the poorest of
        the land who had not been exiled to Babylon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "they went to Gedaliah at Mizpah\u2014Ishmael the son of Nethaniah,
        Johanan and Jonathan the sons of Kareah, Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth, the
        sons of Ephai the Netophathite, and Jezaniah the son of the Maacathite, they
        and their men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, swore to them
        and their men, saying, \u201CDo not be afraid to serve the Chaldeans; stay
        in this land and serve the king of Babylon, that it may go well with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As for me, I am going to stay at Mizpah to stand [for you] before
        the Chaldeans who come to us [ministering to them and looking after the king\u2019s
        interests]; but as for you, gather in wine, summer fruit and oil and store
        them in your utensils [designed for such purposes], and live in your cities
        that you have taken over.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Likewise, when all the Jews who were in Moab and among the people
        of Ammon and in Edom and who were in all the [other] countries heard that
        the king of Babylon had left a remnant [of the people] in Judah and had appointed
        Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan over them [as governor], '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then all the Jews returned from all the places to which they had
        been driven and came back to the land of Judah, to Gedaliah at Mizpah, and
        gathered a great abundance of wine and summer fruits.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Moreover, Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the
        forces that were [scattered] in the open country came to Gedaliah at Mizpah '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and said to him, \u201CDo you know that Baalis the king of the Ammonites
        has sent Ishmael the son of Nethaniah to take your life?\u201D But Gedaliah
        the son of Ahikam did not believe them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Johanan the son of Kareah spoke secretly to Gedaliah in Mizpah,
        saying, \u201CLet me go and kill Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and not a
        man will know [who is responsible]. Why should he kill you and cause all
        the Jews who are gathered near you to be scattered and the remnant of Judah
        to perish?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam said to Johanan the son of Kareah,
        \u201CDo not do this thing, for you are lying about Ishmael.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Gedaliah Is Murdered'
      title: Gedaliah Is Murdered
      number: 1
      content: '  Now in the seventh month Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, the son
        of Elishama, of the royal family [of David] and one of the princes of the
        king, came [at the instigation of the Ammonites] with ten men to Gedaliah
        the son of Ahikam in Mizpah. As they were eating a meal together there in
        Mizpah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Ishmael the son of Nethaniah and the ten men who were with him got
        up and struck down Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, with the
        sword and killed the one whom the king of Babylon had appointed [governor]
        over the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Ishmael also killed all the Jews who were [at the banquet] with Gedaliah
        at Mizpah, in addition to the Chaldean soldiers who were there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now it happened on the second day after the killing of Gedaliah,
        before anyone knew about it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'that eighty men came from Shechem, from Shiloh, and from Samaria
        with their beards shaved off and their clothes torn and their bodies cut,
        carrying in their hands grain offerings and incense to present at the [site
        of the] house of the Lord [in Jerusalem]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Ishmael the son of Nethaniah went out from Mizpah to meet them,
        weeping [false tears] as he went. As he met them, he said to them, \u201CCome
        to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet when they came into the city, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah and
        the men who were with him slaughtered them and threw them into the cistern
        (underground water reservoir). '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But ten men who were among them said to Ishmael, \u201CDo not kill
        us! We have stores of wheat and barley and oil and honey hidden in the field.\u201D
        So he stopped and did not kill them along with their companions.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the cistern into which Ishmael had thrown all the corpses of
        the men whom he had killed along with Gedaliah was the one which King Asa
        [of Judah] had made [about three hundred years earlier] on account of King
        Baasha of Israel [believing that Baasha would lay siege to Mizpah]. Ishmael
        the son of Nethaniah filled it with [the bodies of] those who were killed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Johanan Rescues the People'
      title: Johanan Rescues the People
      number: 10
      content: "Then Ishmael took captive all the rest of the people who were in
        Mizpah\u2014even the king\u2019s daughters (ladies of the court) and all
        the people who remained in Mizpah, whom Nebuzaradan the captain of the bodyguard
        had put under the charge of Gedaliah the son of Ahikam. Ishmael the son of
        Nethaniah took them captive and crossed over [the Jordan] to [meet his allies]
        the Ammonites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the
        forces that were with him heard of the murderous behavior of Ishmael the
        son of Nethaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'they took all their men and went to fight with Ishmael the son of
        Nethaniah and found him by the great pool in Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when all the [captive] people who were with Ishmael saw Johanan
        the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces that were with him,
        they were glad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So all the people whom Ishmael had taken captive from Mizpah turned
        around and came back, and joined Johanan the son of Kareah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But Ishmael the son of Nethaniah escaped from Johanan with eight
        men and went to join the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces
        that were with him took from Mizpah all the people whom he had rescued from
        Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, after Ishmael had killed Gedaliah the son of
        Ahikam: the soldiers, the women, the children, and the high officials whom
        Johanan had brought back from Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they went and stayed in Geruth [the lodging place of] Chimham,
        which is near Bethlehem, intending to go to Egypt '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: because of the Chaldeans; for they were afraid of them because Ishmael
        the son of Nethaniah had killed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, whom the king
        of Babylon had appointed [governor] over the land [and whose death the king
        might avenge].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning against Going to Egypt'
      title: Warning against Going to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the commanders of the forces, and Johanan the son of Kareah
        and Jezaniah (Azariah) the son of Hoshaiah, and all the people from the least
        to the greatest approached '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said to Jeremiah the prophet, \u201CPlease let our petition be
        presented before you, and pray to the Lord your God for us, that is, for
        all this remnant [of the people of Judah]; for we were once many, but now
        [only] a few of us are left, as you see with your own eyes, [so please pray] "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "that the Lord your God may show us the way in which we should walk
        and the thing that we should do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jeremiah the prophet said to them, \u201CI have heard you. Now
        hear me, I will pray to the Lord your God in accordance with your words;
        and I will declare to you whatever message the Lord answers; I will keep
        nothing back from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then they said to Jeremiah, \u201CMay the Lord be a true and faithful
        witness against us if we fail to act in accordance with all the things that
        the Lord your God sends you to tell us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Whether it is pleasant or unpleasant, we will listen to and honor
        the voice of the Lord our God to whom we are sending you, so that it may
        go well with us when we listen to the voice of the Lord our God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now after ten days [of prayer] had passed the word of the Lord came
        to Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he called for Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders
        of the forces that were with him and all the people from the least to the
        greatest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and said to them, \u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, to
        whom you sent me to present your petition before Him: "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018If you will indeed remain in this land, then I will build you
        up and not tear you down, and I will plant you and not uproot you; for I
        will relent and be satisfied concerning the disaster that I have inflicted
        on you [as discipline, and I will replace judgment with compassion]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Do not be afraid of the king of Babylon, whom you now fear [as if
        he were deity]; do not be afraid of him,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018for [he
        is a mere man, but I am the living, omniscient God and] I am with you [always]
        to protect you and to deliver you from his hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will show you compassion, so that he will have compassion on
        you and restore you to your own land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But if you are going to say, \u201CWe will not stay in this land,\u201D
        and [in so doing] do not listen to the voice of the Lord your God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "saying, \u201CNo, but we will go to the land of Egypt, where we will
        not see war or hear the sound of the [warrior\u2019s] trumpet or hunger for
        bread, and we will stay there,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "then in that case listen to the word of the Lord, O remnant of Judah.
        Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CIf you are really determined
        to go to Egypt and to reside there [temporarily], "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then the sword, of which you are afraid, will overtake you there
        in the land of Egypt; and the famine of which you are afraid will follow
        closely after you in Egypt, and you will die there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So all the men who set their mind to go to Egypt to reside there
        [temporarily] will die by the sword, by famine and by virulent disease; none
        of them will remain or survive the disaster that I am going to bring on them.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CAs My anger
        and My wrath have been poured out on the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so My
        wrath will be poured out on you when you enter Egypt. You will become detested,
        an object of horror, a curse and a people scorned; and you will no longer
        see this place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The Lord has spoken to you, O remnant of Judah, \u201CDo not go into
        Egypt!\u201D Know with certainty that I [Jeremiah] have warned you and testified
        to you this day "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "that you have deceived yourselves; for you sent me to the Lord your
        God, saying, \u201CPray for us to the Lord our God; and whatever the Lord
        our God says, declare it to us and we will do it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And so I have told you today, but you have not listened to the voice
        of the Lord your God, in anything that He has sent me to tell you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Now therefore know for certain that you will die by the sword, by
        famine, and by virulent disease in the land [of Egypt] where you wish to
        reside [temporarily].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: In Egypt Jeremiah Warns of Judgment'
      title: In Egypt Jeremiah Warns of Judgment
      number: 1
      content: "  Now it happened when Jeremiah, whom the Lord their God had sent,
        had finished telling all the people all the words of the Lord their God\u2014that
        is, all these words\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Azariah the son of Hoshaiah and Johanan the son of Kareah and all
        the proud and insolent men said to Jeremiah, \u201CYou are not telling the
        truth! The Lord our God has not sent you to say, \u2018Do not go into Egypt
        to live there.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Baruch the son of Neriah is inciting you against us to hand us
        over to the Chaldeans, so they may [either] put us to death or exile us to
        Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces
        and all the people disobeyed the voice of the Lord [which told them] to stay
        in the land of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces
        took all the remnant of Judah who had returned to live in the land of Judah
        from all the nations to which they had been driven\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "the men, women, and children, the king\u2019s daughters (ladies of
        the court), and every person whom Nebuzaradan the captain of the bodyguard
        had left with Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan; he also took
        Jeremiah the prophet and Baruch the son of Neriah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they entered the land of Egypt (for they did not obey the voice
        of the Lord) and they went in as far as Tahpanhes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then came the word of the Lord to Jeremiah in Tahpanhes, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTake some large stones in your hands and hide them in the mortar
        in the brickwork [of the terrace] which is at the entrance of Pharaoh\u2019s
        house in Tahpanhes, in the sight of some of the men of Judah; "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel,
        \u201CBehold, I am going to send and get Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon,
        My servant, and I am going to set his throne over these stones that I have
        hidden; and his [majestic, royal] canopy will be spread over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He will also come and strike the land of Egypt, giving those who
        are [destined] for death, to death, and those who are [destined] for captivity,
        to captivity, and those who are [destined] for the sword, to the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And [through him] I will set fire to the temples of the gods of Egypt,
        and he will burn them and take them (Egyptian idols) captive. He will wrap
        himself with the land of Egypt as a shepherd wraps himself with his garment,
        and he will go away from there safely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Nebuchadnezzar will also break the images and shatter the obelisks
        of Heliopolis in the land of Egypt; and he will burn down the temples of
        the gods of Egypt.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Conquest of Egypt Predicted'
      title: Conquest of Egypt Predicted
      number: 1
      content: "  The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the Jews who were
        living in the land of Egypt\u2014at Migdol, at Tahpanhes, at Memphis, and
        in the land of Pathros, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018You have
        seen all the disaster that I have brought on Jerusalem and on all the cities
        of Judah; and see, this day they are desolated and no one lives in them "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'because of the wickedness which they committed, provoking Me to anger
        by continuing to burn sacrifices and incense to serve other gods that they
        had not known, neither they, nor you, nor your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet I sent to you all My servants the prophets, again and again,
        saying, \u201COh, do not do this shamefully vile thing which I hate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But they did not listen or turn [obediently] from their wickedness,
        and stop burning sacrifices and incense to other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore My wrath and My anger were poured out and burned in the
        cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem; so they have become a ruin
        and a desolation, as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore now thus says the Lord God of hosts, the God of Israel,
        \u201CWhy did you commit this great evil against yourselves [bringing disaster]
        that will cut off from you man and woman, child and infant, out of Judah,
        leaving yourselves without a remnant? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Why do you [deliberately] provoke Me to anger with the works (idols)
        of your hands, burning sacrifices and incense to [make-believe] gods in the
        land of Egypt, where you [of your own accord] have come to live [as temporary
        residents], that you might be cut off and become a curse and a disgrace [an
        object of taunts] among all the nations of the earth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you forgotten the wickedness of your fathers, the wickedness
        of the kings of Judah, the wickedness of their wives [who served their foreign
        gods], your own wickedness, and the wickedness of your wives [who imitated
        the sin of the queens], which they committed in the land of Judah and in
        the streets of Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They have not become apologetic [for their guilt and sin] even to
        this day; they have not feared [Me with reverence] nor walked in My law or
        My statutes, which I have set before you and before your fathers.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Behold,
        I am going to set My face against you for woe\u2014even to cut off (destroy)
        all Judah [from the land]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will take the remnant of Judah who have decided to go into
        the land of Egypt to live there [instead of surrendering to the Chaldeans
        as directed], and they will all fall and die in the land of Egypt; they will
        fall by the sword or perish by famine. From the least to the greatest, they
        will die by the sword or by famine; and they will become detestable, an object
        of horror, a curse, and a disgrace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For I will punish all the inhabitants of the land of Egypt, as I
        have punished Jerusalem, with the sword, with famine, and with virulent disease; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "so none of the survivors from the remnant of Judah who have entered
        the land of Egypt to live there will survive, even though they lift up their
        souls in longing to return to the land of Judah, [the place] to which they
        long to return to live; none will return except a few refugees.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then all the men who knew that their wives were burning sacrifices
        to other gods, and all the women who were standing by, a large group, including
        all the people who were living in Pathros in the land of Egypt, answered
        Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAs for the word (message) that you have spoken to us in the
        name of the Lord, we are not going to listen to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But rather we will certainly perform every word of the vows we have
        made: to burn sacrifices to the queen of heaven (Ishtar) and to pour out
        drink offerings to her, just as we ourselves and our forefathers, our kings
        and our princes did in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem;
        for [then] we had plenty of food and were prosperous and saw no misfortune. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But since we stopped burning sacrifices to the queen of heaven and
        pouring out drink offerings to her, we have lacked everything and have been
        consumed by the sword and by famine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Tragedy for the Jews'
      title: Tragedy for the Jews
      number: 19
      content: "And said the wives, \u201CWhen we were burning sacrifices to the
        queen of heaven and were pouring out drink offerings to her, was it without
        [the knowledge and approval of] our husbands that we made cakes [in the shape
        of a star] to represent her and pour out drink offerings to her?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Jeremiah said to all the people, to the men and to the women
        and to all the people who had given him that answer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThe smoking sacrifices (incense) that you burned in the cities
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem\u2014you and your forefathers, your
        kings and your princes, and the people of the land\u2014did not the Lord
        remember [in detail your idolatry] and did it not all come into His mind? "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Lord could no longer endure it, because of the evil of your acts
        and the repulsive acts which you have committed; because of them your land
        has become a ruin, an object of horror and a curse, without inhabitant, as
        it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Because you have burned sacrifices [to idols] and because you have
        sinned against the Lord and have not obeyed the voice of the Lord or walked
        in His law and in His statutes and in His testimonies, therefore this tragedy
        has fallen on you, as it has this day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to all the people, including all the women, \u201CHear
        the word of the Lord, all [you of] Judah who are in the land of Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, as follows: \u2018You
        and your wives have both declared with your mouth and fulfilled it with your
        hand, saying, \u201CWe will certainly perform our vows that we have vowed,
        to burn sacrifices to the queen of heaven (Ishtar) and to pour out drink
        offerings to her.\u201D Surely then confirm your vows and go ahead and perform
        your vows! [If you intend to defy all My warnings, proceed!]\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore hear the word of the Lord, all [you people of] Judah who
        are living in the land of Egypt, \u2018Behold, I have sworn [an oath] by
        My great Name,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018that My Name shall never again
        be invoked by the mouth of any man of Judah in all the land of Egypt, saying,
        \u201CAs the Lord God lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Behold, I am watching over them for harm and not for good; and all
        the men of Judah who are in the land of Egypt shall be consumed by the sword
        and by famine until they are all destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Yet a small number [of My choosing] who escape the sword will return
        from the land of Egypt to the land of Judah; and all the remnant of Judah
        who have gone to the land of Egypt to reside there will know whose words
        will stand, Mine or theirs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And this will be the sign to you,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018that
        I am going to punish you in this place, so that you may know that My words
        will surely stand against you for harm.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u2018Behold, I will give Pharaoh Hophra king
        of Egypt into the hand of his enemies and into the hand of those who seek
        his life, just as I gave Zedekiah king of Judah into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon, who was his enemy and was seeking his life.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Message to Baruch'
      title: Message to Baruch
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that Jeremiah the prophet spoke to Baruch the son of Neriah,
        when he had written these words in a book at the dictation of Jeremiah, in
        the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, to you, O Baruch: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018You said, \u201CWoe is me! For the Lord has added sorrow to
        my pain; I am weary with my groaning and sighing and I find no rest.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say this to him, \u2018The Lord speaks in this way, \u201CBehold,
        what I have built I will break down, and that which I have planted I will
        uproot, that is, the whole land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And do you seek great things for yourself? Do not seek them; for
        behold, I will bring disaster on all flesh,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018but
        I will give your life to you [as your only reward and] as a prize of war
        wherever you go.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Defeat of Pharaoh Foretold'
      title: Defeat of Pharaoh Foretold
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning
        the [Gentile] nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Concerning Egypt, against the army of Pharaoh Neco king of Egypt,
        which was by the river Euphrates at Carchemish, which Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon defeated [decisively] in the fourth year of Jehoiakim son of Josiah,
        king of Judah:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLine up the buckler (small shield) and [large] shield,And advance
        for battle!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Harness the horses,And mount, you riders!Take your stand with your
        helmets!Polish the spears,Put on the coats of mail!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Why have I seen it?They are terrifiedAnd have turned back,And their
        warriors are beaten down.They take flight in hasteWithout looking back;Terror
        is on every side!\u201DSays the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do not let the swift man run,Nor the mighty man escape;In the north
        by the river EuphratesThey have stumbled and fallen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who is this that rises up like the Nile [River],Like the rivers [in
        the delta of Egypt] whose waters surge about?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Egypt rises like the Nile,Even like the rivers whose waters surge
        about.And He has said, \u201CI will rise, I will cover that land;I will certainly
        destroy the city and its inhabitants.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Charge, you horses,And drive like madmen, you chariots!Let the warriors
        go forward:Ethiopia and Put (Libya) who handle the shield,And the Lydians
        who handle and bend the bow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For that day belongs to the Lord God of hosts,A day of vengeance,
        that He may avenge Himself on His adversaries.And the sword will devour and
        be satiatedAnd drink its fill of their blood;For the Lord God of hosts has
        a sacrifice [like that of a great sin offering]In the north country by the
        river Euphrates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Go up to Gilead and obtain [healing] balm,O Virgin Daughter of Egypt!In
        vain you use many medicines;For you there is no healing or remedy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The nations have heard of your disgrace and shame,And your cry [of
        distress] has filled the earth.For warrior has stumbled against warrior,And
        both of them have fallen together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The word that the Lord spoke to Jeremiah the prophet concerning the
        coming of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon to strike the land of Egypt:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CDeclare in Egypt and proclaim in Migdol,And proclaim in Memphis
        and in Tahpanhes;Say, \u2018Take your stand and get yourself ready,For the
        sword has devoured those around you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Why have your strong ones been cut down?They do not stand because
        the Lord drove them away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He will make many stumble and fall;Yes, they have fallen one on another.Then
        they said, \u2018Arise, and let us go backTo our own people and to the land
        of our birth,Away from the sword of the oppressor.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They cried there, \u2018Pharaoh king of Egypt is destroyed and is
        merely a loud noise;He has let the appointed time [of opportunity] pass by!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "As I live,\u201D says the King,Whose name is the Lord of hosts,\u201CSurely
        like Tabor among the mountainsOr like Carmel by the sea,So shall he [the
        great king of Babylon] come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'O you daughter who dwells in Egypt and you who dwell with her,Prepare
        yourselves [with all you will need] to go into exile,For Memphis will become
        desolate;It will even be burned down and without inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Egypt is a very pretty heifer,But a horsefly (Babylonia) is coming
        [against her] out of the north!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Also her mercenaries in her armyAre like fattened calves,For they
        too have turned back and have fled together;They did not stand [their ground],Because
        the day of their disaster has come upon them,The time of their punishment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sound [of Egypt fleeing from the enemy] is like [the rustling
        of] an escaping serpent,For her foes advance with a mighty armyAnd come against
        her like woodcutters with axes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They have cut down her forest,\u201D says the Lord;\u201CCertainly
        it will no longer be found,Because they (the invaders) are more numerous
        than locustsAnd cannot be counted.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The Daughter of Egypt has been shamed,Given over to the power of
        the people of the north [the Chaldeans of Babylonia].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, says, \u201CBehold, I am going
        to punish Amon [chief god of the sacred city] of Thebes [the capital of Upper
        Egypt], and Pharaoh, and Egypt along with her gods and her kings\u2014even
        Pharaoh and those who put their trust in him [as a shield against Babylon]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I will put them into the hand of those who seek their lives, and
        into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and into the hand of his
        servants. Afterward Egypt will be inhabited as in the days of old,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBut as for you, do not fear, O My servant Jacob,Nor be dismayed,
        O Israel!For behold, I will save you from [your captivity in] a distant land,And
        your descendants from the land of their exile;And Jacob will return and be
        quiet and secure,And no one will make him afraid.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Do not fear, O Jacob My servant,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CFor I
        am with you.For I will make a full and complete end of all the nationsTo
        which I have driven you;Yet I will not make a full end of you.But I will
        discipline and correct you appropriatelyAnd by no means will I declare you
        guiltless or leave you unpunished.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy against Philistia'
      title: Prophecy against Philistia
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning
        the Philistines before Pharaoh attacked and conquered [the Philistine city
        of] Gaza. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, waters are going to rise out of
        the north (Babylonia)And become an overflowing streamAnd overflow the land
        and all that is in it,The city and those who live in it.Then the people will
        cry out,And all the inhabitants of the land [of Philistia] will wail.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Because of the noise of the stamping of the hoofs of the war-horses
        [of the Babylonian king],The rattling of his chariots, and the rumbling of
        his wheels,The fathers have not looked and turned back for their children,So
        weak are their hands [with terror]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because of the day that is comingTo destroy all the PhilistinesAnd
        to cut off from Tyre and SidonEvery ally who remains.For the Lord is going
        to destroy the Philistines,The remnant [still surviving] of the coastland
        of Caphtor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Baldness [as a sign of mourning] will come on Gaza;Ashkelon will
        be cut off and ruined.O remnant of their valley,How long will you gash yourselves
        [as a sign of mourning]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'O you sword of the Lord,How long will it be before you are quiet?Put
        yourself into your sheath;Rest and be still.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "How can His sword be quietWhen the Lord has given it an order?Against
        Ashkelon and against the [whole Philistine] seashoreThere He has assigned
        it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy against Moab'
      title: Prophecy against Moab
      number: 1
      content: "  Concerning Moab.Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel,\u201CWoe
        (judgment is coming) to [the city of] Nebo, for it has been destroyed!Kiriathaim
        has been shamed, it has been captured;Misgab [the high fortress] has been
        shamed, broken down and crushed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The glory of Moab is no more;In Heshbon they planned evil against
        her,Saying, \u2018Come, let us cut her off from being a nation!\u2019You
        also, O [city of] Madmen, shall be silenced;The sword will pursue you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The sound of an outcry from Horonaim,\u2018Desolation and great destruction!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moab is destroyed;Her little ones have called out a cry of distress
        [to be heard as far as Zoar].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the Ascent of LuhithWill be climbed by [successive groups of]
        fugitives with continual weeping;For on the descent of HoronaimThey have
        heard the distress of the cry of destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Run! Save your lives,That you may be like a juniper in the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For because you have trusted in your works [your hand-made idols]
        and in your treasures [instead of in God],Even you yourself will be captured;And
        Chemosh [your disgusting god cannot rescue you, but] will go away into exile
        [along with the fugitives]Together with his priests and his princes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the destroyer will come upon every city;No city will escape.The
        [Jordan] valley also will be ruinedAnd the plain will be devastated,As the
        Lord has said.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Give a gravestone to Moab,For she will fall into ruins;Her cities
        (pastures, farms) will be desolate,Without anyone to live in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Cursed is the one who does the work of the Lord negligently,And cursed
        is the one who restrains his sword from blood [in executing the judgment
        of the Lord].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CMoab has been at ease from his youth;He has also been undisturbed,
        and settled like wine on his dregs,And he has not been emptied from one vessel
        to another,Nor has he gone into exile.Therefore his flavor remains in him,And
        his scent has not changed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cwhen
        I will send to Moab those who will tip him over and who will empty his vessels
        and break his [earthenware] jars in pieces. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Moab shall be ashamed of Chemosh [his worthless, disgusting god],
        as the house of Israel was ashamed of Bethel, their [misplaced] confidence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "How can you say, \u2018We are great warriorsAnd valiant men in war?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Moab has been made desolate and his cities have gone up [in smoke
        and flame];And his chosen young men have gone down to the slaughter,\u201DSays
        the King, whose name is the Lord of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThe destruction of Moab will come soon,And his disaster hurries
        quickly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Show sympathy for him, all you [nations] who are around him,And all
        you [distant nations] who know his name;Say, \u2018How has the mighty scepter
        [of national power] been broken,And the splendid staff [of glory]!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Come down from your glory,O Daughter living in Dibon,And sit on the
        parched ground [among the thirsty]!For the destroyer of Moab has advanced
        against you;He has destroyed your strongholds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "O inhabitant of Aroer,Stand by the road and keep watch!Ask [of] him
        who flees and [ask of] her who escapes,Saying, \u2018What has happened?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Moab is shamed, for she has been broken down and shattered.Wail and
        cry out!Tell by [the banks of] the ArnonThat Moab has been destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CJudgment has come on [the land of] the plain\u2014upon Holon,
        Jahzah, and against Mephaath, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'against Dibon, Nebo, and Beth-diblathaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'against Kiriathaim, Beth-gamul, and Beth-meon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'against Kerioth, Bozrah and all the cities of the land of Moab, far
        and near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The horn (strength) of Moab has been cut off and his arm [of authority]
        is shattered,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CMake him drunk, for he has become arrogant and magnified himself
        against the Lord [by denying Reuben\u2019s occupation of the land the Lord
        had assigned him]. Moab also will wallow in his vomit, and he too shall become
        a laughingstock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For was not Israel a laughingstock to you? Was he caught among thieves?
        For whenever you speak of him you shake your head in scorn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You inhabitants of Moab,Leave the cities and live among the rocks,And
        be like the dove that makes her nestIn the walls of the yawning ravine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "We have heard of the [giddy] pride of Moab, the extremely proud one\u2014His
        haughtiness, his arrogance, his conceit, and his self-exaltation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "I know his [insolent] wrath,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CBut it is
        futile;His idle boasts [in his deeds] have accomplished nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Therefore I will wail over Moab,And I will cry out for all Moab.I
        will sigh and mourn over the men of Kir-heres (Kir-hareseth).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "O vines of Sibmah, I will weep for youMore than the weeping of Jazer
        [over its ruins and wasted vineyards].Your tendrils [of influence] stretched
        across the sea,Reaching [even] to the sea of Jazer.The destroyer has fallenOn
        your summer fruits and your [season\u2019s] crop of grapes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So joy and gladness are taken awayFrom the fruitful field and from
        the land of Moab.And I have made the wine cease from the wine presses;No
        one treads the grapes with shouting.Their shouting is not joyful shouting
        [but is instead, a battle cry].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'From the outcry at Heshbon even to Elealeh, even to Jahaz they have
        raised their voice, from Zoar even to Horonaim and Eglath-shelishiyah; for
        even the waters of Nimrim will become desolations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Moreover, I will cause to cease in Moab,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthe
        one who ascends and offers sacrifice in the high place and the one who burns
        incense to his gods.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CTherefore My heart moans and sighs for Moab like flutes, and
        My heart moans and sighs like flutes for the men of Kir-heres (Kir-hareseth);
        therefore [the remnant of] the abundant riches they gained has perished. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For every head is [shaven] bald and every beard cut off; there are
        cuts (slashes) on all the hands and sackcloth on the loins [all expressions
        of mourning]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "On all the housetops of Moab and in its streets there is lamentation
        (expressions of grief for the dead) everywhere, for I have broken Moab like
        a vessel in which there is no pleasure,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CHow it is broken down! How they have wailed! How Moab has turned
        his back in shame! So Moab will become a laughingstock and a [horrifying]
        terror to all who are around him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, one (Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon)
        will fly swiftly like an eagleAnd spread out his wings against Moab.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Kerioth [and the cities] has been takenAnd the strongholds seized;And
        the hearts of the warriors of Moab in that dayShall be like the heart of
        a woman in childbirth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Moab will be destroyed from being a nation (people)Because he has
        become arrogant and magnified himself against the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Terror and pit and snare are before you,O inhabitant of Moab,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CThe one who flees from the terrorWill fall into the pit,And
        the one who gets up out of the pitWill be taken and caught in the trap;For
        I shall bring upon it, even upon Moab,The year of their punishment,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CIn the shadow of HeshbonThe fugitives stand powerless [helpless
        and without strength],For a fire has gone out from Heshbon,A flame from the
        midst of Sihon;It has destroyed the forehead of MoabAnd the crowns of the
        heads of [the arrogant Moabites] the ones in tumult.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to you, O Moab!The people of [the pagan
        god called] Chemosh have perished;For your sons have been taken away captiveAnd
        your daughters into captivity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Yet I will return the captives and restore the fortunes of MoabIn
        the latter days,\u201D says the Lord.  Thus far is the judgment on Moab."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy against Ammon'
      title: Prophecy against Ammon
      number: 1
      content: "  Concerning the sons (descendants) of Ammon.Thus says the Lord:\u201CDoes
        Israel have no sons [to reclaim Gad from the Ammonites]?Has he no heir?Why
        then has Malcam taken possession of GadAnd [why do] his people live in the
        cities [of Gad]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CWhen
        I will cause an alarm of war to be heardAgainst Rabbah of the Ammonites;And
        it [along with the high ground on which it stands] will become a desolate
        heap,And its villages will be set on fire.Then will Israel take possession
        of his possessors,\u201DSays the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CWail, O Heshbon, for Ai [in Ammon] has been destroyed!Cry out,
        O daughters of Rabbah!Wrap yourselves with sackcloth and lament (cry out
        in grief),And rush back and forth inside the enclosures;For Malcam [your
        powerless god] will go into exileTogether with his priests and his princes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Why do you boast of your valleys?Your valley is flowing away,[O Ammon]
        rebellious and faithless daughterWho trusts in her treasures, saying,\u2018Who
        will come against me?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Behold, I am going to bring terror on you,\u201DSays the Lord God
        of hosts,\u201CFrom all who are around you;And each of you will be driven
        out headlong,And there will be no one to gather the fugitives together.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Prophecy against Edom'
      title: Prophecy against Edom
      number: 6
      content: "But afterward I will reverseThe captivity of the children of Ammon
        and restore their fortunes,\u201DSays the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Concerning Edom.Thus says the Lord of hosts,\u201CIs there no longer
        any wisdom in Teman?Has good counsel vanished from the intelligent and prudent?Has
        their wisdom decayed?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Flee, turn back, dwell in the depths [of the desert to escape the
        judgment of Edom],O inhabitants of Dedan,For I will bring the destruction
        of Esau (Edom) upon himWhen I inspect and punish him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If grape gatherers came to you,Would they not leave some ungleaned
        grapes [on the vines]?If thieves came by night,Would they not destroy [only]
        what is enough [for them]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But I have stripped Esau (Edom) bare;I have uncovered his hiding
        placesAnd he cannot hide himself.His descendants have been destroyed along
        with his brothers (relatives) and his neighbors;And he is no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Leave your orphans behind; I will [do what is needed to] keep them
        alive.And let [those who are] your widows trust and confide in Me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For thus says the Lord, \u201CBehold, those (Israel) who were not
        sentenced to drink the cup [of wrath] shall certainly drink it, and are you
        to remain unpunished? You will not be acquitted and go unpunished, but you
        will certainly drink [from the cup of wrath and judgment]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I have sworn [an oath] by Myself,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthat
        Bozrah will become an object of horror, a reproach, a ruin, and a curse;
        and all its cities will become perpetual ruins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I have heard a report from the Lord,And a messenger has been sent
        to the nations, saying,\u201CGather together and come against her,And rise
        up for the battle.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CFor behold, [Edom] I have made you small among the nationsAnd
        despised among men.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "As for Your terror,The pride and arrogance of your heart have deceived
        you,O you who live in the clefts of the rock (Sela also called Petra),Who
        hold and occupy the height of the hill.Though you make your nest as high
        as the eagle\u2019s,I will bring you down from there,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CEdom will become an object of horror; everyone who goes by
        it will be astonished and shall hiss [scornfully] at all its plagues and
        disasters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "As [it was] in the overthrow of Sodom and Gomorrah with their neighboring
        cities,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cno man will live there, nor will a son
        of man dwell in it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "See, one will come like a lion from the thicket of the Jordan against
        the enduring habitation [of Edom] and its watered pastures; for in an instant
        I will make him (Edom) run from his land. I will appoint over him the one
        whom I choose. For who is like Me, and who will summon Me [into court] and
        prosecute Me [for this]? Who is the [earthly] shepherd who can stand [defiantly]
        before Me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Therefore hear the plan of the Lord which He has devised against
        Edom, and [hear] what He has purposed against the inhabitants of Teman: surely
        they will be dragged away, even the little ones of the flock; surely He will
        make their dwelling place desolate because of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The earth has quaked at the noise of their downfall. There is an
        outcry! The sound of its noise has been heard at the Red Sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Prophecy against Damascus'
      title: Prophecy against Damascus
      number: 22
      content: 'Behold, He will mount up and fly swiftly like an eagle and spread
        His wings against [the city of] Bozrah; and in that day the heart of the
        mighty warriors of Edom will be like the heart of a woman in childbirth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Concerning Damascus [in Syria].\u201CHamath and Arpad are perplexed
        and shamed,For they have heard bad news;They are disheartened;Troubled and
        anxious like a [storm-tossed] seaWhich cannot be calmed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Damascus has become helpless;She has turned away to flee,Terror (panic)
        has seized her;Anguish and distress have gripped herLike a woman in childbirth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Why has the renowned city not been deserted,The city of My joy!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore, her young men will fall in her streets,And all her men
        of war will be destroyed in that day,\u201D says the Lord of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Prophecy against Kedar and Hazor'
      title: Prophecy against Kedar and Hazor
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI will set fire to the wall of Damascus,And it will consume
        the palaces of Ben-hadad.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Concerning Kedar and concerning the kingdoms of Hazor, which Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon defeated. Thus says the Lord,\u201CArise, go up against KedarAnd
        destroy the men of the east.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "They (the Babylonians) will take away their tents and their flocks;They
        will carry off for themselvesTheir tent curtains, all their goods and their
        camels,And they will call out to one another, \u2018Terror on every side!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Flee, run far away! Dwell in the depths [of the desert],O inhabitants
        of Hazor,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CFor Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has
        planned a course of action against youAnd devised a scheme against you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Arise [Nebuchadnezzar], go up against a nation which is at ease,Which
        lives securely,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CA nation which has neither gates
        nor bars;They dwell apart and alone.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Their camels will become plunder,And their herds of cattle a spoil;And
        I will scatter to all the [four] winds those who cut the corners of their
        hair [as evidence of their idolatry],And I will bring their disaster from
        every side,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Prophecy against Elam'
      title: Prophecy against Elam
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CHazor will become a haunt and dwelling place of jackals,A desolation
        forever;No one will live there,Nor will a son of man reside in it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning
        Elam, in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah, saying:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts,\u2018Behold (listen carefully),
        I am going to break the bow of Elam,The finest [weapon] of their strength.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And I will bring upon Elam the four windsFrom the four corners of
        heaven;And I will scatter them toward all those winds,And there will be no
        nationTo which the outcasts of Elam will not go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So I will cause Elam to be shattered (dismayed) before their enemiesAnd
        before those who seek their lives;And I will bring disaster on them,Even
        My fierce anger,\u2019 says the Lord.\u2018And I will send the sword after
        themUntil I have consumed them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then I will set My throne [of judgment] in ElamAnd I will destroy
        from there the king and princes,\u2019Says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u2018But it will be in the last days (the end of days)That I will
        reverse the captivity and restore the fortunes of Elam,\u2019\u2009\u201DSays
        the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy against Babylon'
      title: Prophecy against Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that the Lord spoke concerning Babylon and concerning
        the land of the Chaldeans through Jeremiah the prophet:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDeclare among the nations.Lift up a signal [to spread the news]\u2014publish
        and proclaim it,Do not conceal it; say,\u2018Babylon has been taken,Bel [the
        patron god] has been shamed, Marduk (Bel) has been shattered.Babylon\u2019s
        images have been shamed, her [worthless] idols have been thrown down.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For out of the north a nation (Media) has come against her which
        will make her land desolate, and no one will live there. They have fled,
        they have gone away\u2014both man and animal.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIn those days and at that time,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthe
        children of Israel will come, they and the children of Judah together; they
        will come up weeping [in repentance] as they come and seek the Lord their
        God [inquiring for and of Him]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They will ask the way to Zion, with their faces in that direction,
        saying, \u2018Come, let us join ourselves to the Lord in an everlasting covenant
        that will not be forgotten.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CMy people have become lost sheep;Their shepherds have led them
        astray.They have made them turn aside [to the seductive places of idolatry]
        on the mountains.They have gone along [from one sin to another] from mountain
        to hill;They have forgotten their [own] resting place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "All who found them have devoured them;And their adversaries have
        said, \u2018We are not guilty,Because they have sinned against the Lord [and
        are no longer holy to Him], their [true] habitation of righteousness and
        justice,Even the Lord, the [confident] hope of their fathers.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWander away from the midst of BabylonAnd go out of the land
        of the Chaldeans;Be like the male goats [who serve as leaders] at the head
        of the flocks.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For behold, I will stir up and bring up against BabylonAn assembly
        of great nations from the north country.They will equip themselves and set
        up the battle lines against her;From there she will be taken captive.Their
        arrows will be like an expert warriorWho will not return empty-handed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Chaldea will become plunder;All who plunder her will be satisfied,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CThough you are glad, though you rejoice,O you who plunder My
        heritage,Though you are wanton and skip about like a heifer in the grassAnd
        neigh like stallions,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Your mother [Babylon] shall be greatly shamed;She who gave you birth
        will be ashamed.Behold, she will be the least of the nations,A wilderness,
        a parched land and a desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Because of the wrath of the Lord she will not be inhabitedBut she
        will be completely desolate;Everyone who goes by Babylon will be appalledAnd
        will hiss (mock) at all her wounds and plagues.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Set yourselves in battle formation against Babylon on every side,All
        you archers.Shoot at her! Do not spare the arrows,For she has sinned against
        the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Raise the battle cry against her on every side!She has given her
        hand [in agreement] and has surrendered; her pillars have fallen,Her walls
        have been torn down.For this is the vengeance of the Lord:Take vengeance
        on her;As she has done [to others], do to her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Cut off the sower from BabylonAnd the one who handles the sickle
        at the time of harvest.For fear of the sword of the oppressorEveryone will
        return to his own peopleAnd everyone will flee to his own land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Israel is a hunted and scattered flock [driven here and there as
        prey]; the lions have chased them away. First the king of Assyria devoured
        him, and now at last Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has broken (gnawed) his
        bones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Behold,
        I will visit (inspect, examine) and punish the king of Babylon and his land,
        just as I visited and punished the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will bring Israel [home] again to his pasture and he will graze
        on [the most fertile lands of] Carmel [in the west] and Bashan [in the east],
        and his soul will be satisfied on the hills of Ephraim and Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In those days and at that time,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018a search
        will be made for the wickedness of Israel, but there will be none and for
        the sins of Judah, but none will be found, for I will pardon those whom I
        leave as a remnant.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CGo against [Babylon] the land of Merathaim (Double Rebellion),Go
        up against it and against the people of Pekod (Punishment).Kill and utterly
        destroy them,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAnd do everything that I have commanded
        you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThe noise of battle is in the land,And [the noise of] great
        destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'How the hammer of the whole earthIs crushed and broken!How Babylon
        has becomeA horror [of desolation] among the nations!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I set a trap for you and you also were caught, O Babylon,And you
        did not know it;You have been found and also seizedBecause you have struggled
        against the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The Lord has opened His armoryAnd has brought out [the nations who
        unknowingly are] the weapons of His indignation (wrath),For it is a work
        of the Lord God of hostsIn the land of the Chaldeans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Come against her from the farthest border.Open her storehouses;Pile
        it up like heaps of rubbish.Burn and destroy her completely;Let nothing be
        left of her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Kill all her young bulls [her strength\u2014her young men];Let them
        go down to the slaughter!Woe (judgment is coming) to the Chaldeans, for their
        day has come,The time of their punishment.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Listen to the voice of the refugees who flee and escape from the
        land of Babylon,Proclaiming in Zion the vengeance of the Lord our God,The
        vengeance [of the Lord against the Chaldeans] for [plundering and destroying]
        His temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CCall together many [archers] against Babylon,All those who
        bend the bow.Encamp against her on every side;Let no one from there escape.Repay
        her according to her actions;Just as she has done, do to her.For she has
        been proudly defiant and presumptuous against the Lord,Against the Holy One
        of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore her young men will fall in her streets,And all her soldiers
        will be destroyed on that day,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am against you, [O Babylon, you] arrogant one, [you
        who are pride and presumption personified],\u201DSays the Lord God of hosts,\u201CFor
        your day has come,The time when I will punish you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The arrogant (proud) one will stumble and fallWith no one to raise
        him up;And I will set fire to his citiesAnd it will devour all who are around
        him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts,\u201CThe children of Israel are oppressed,And
        the children of Judah as well;And all who took them captive have held them
        tightly,They have refused to let them go.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Their Redeemer is strong; the Lord of hosts is His name.He will most
        certainly plead their case and defend their causeSo that He may bring rest
        to their land,But turmoil to the inhabitants of Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "A sword against the Chaldeans,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAnd against
        the inhabitants of BabylonAnd against her princes (officials, civic rulers)
        and against her wise men (astrologers, religious rulers)!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'A sword against the oracle priests (the babbling liars), and they
        will become fools!A sword against her mighty warriors, and they will be shattered
        and destroyed!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'A sword against their horses and against their chariotsAnd against
        all the foreign troops that are in her midst,And they will become [as weak
        and defenseless as] women!A sword against her treasures, and they will be
        plundered!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'A drought on her waters, and they will dry up!For it is a land of
        [worthless] idols,And they are mad over fearsome idols [those objects of
        terror in which they foolishly trust].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CTherefore wild beasts of the desert will live there [in Babylon]
        with the jackals;The ostriches also will live there,And it will never again
        be inhabited [with people]Or lived in from generation to generation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "As when God overthrew SodomAnd Gomorrah and their neighboring cities,\u201D
        says the Lord,\u201CSo no man will live there;Nor shall any son of man live
        there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CBehold, a people is coming from the north,And a great nation
        and many kingsWill be stirring from the remote parts of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They seize their bow and spear;They are cruel and have no compassion.They
        sound like the roaring of the sea;They ride on horses,Every man equipped
        like a man [ready] for the battleAgainst you, O Daughter of Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The king of Babylon has heard the report about them,And his hands
        fall limp and helpless;Anguish has seized him,And agony like that of a woman
        in childbirth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CSee, one will come up like a lion from the thicket of the Jordan
        against the enduring habitation [of Babylon] and its watered pastures; for
        in an instant I will make Babylon run from his land. I will appoint over
        Babylon the one whom I choose. For who is like Me, and who will summon Me
        [into court] and prosecute Me [for this]? Who is the [earthly] shepherd who
        can stand [defiantly] before Me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Therefore hear the plan of the Lord which He has devised against
        Babylon, and hear what He has purposed against [the inhabitants of the land
        of] the Chaldeans: surely they will be dragged away, [even] the little ones
        of the flock; surely He will make their habitation desolate because of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "At the shout, \u201CBabylon has been seized!\u201D the earth quakes,
        and an outcry is heard among the nations."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Babylon Judged for Sins against Israel'
      title: Babylon Judged for Sins against Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, I am going to stir up and put
        into action [a fury] against BabylonAnd against the [rebellious] people of
        Leb-kamai (Chaldea)A destroying wind and hostile spirit;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And I will send foreigners to Babylon that they may winnow herAnd
        may devastate and empty her land;For in the day of destructionThey will be
        against her on every side.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not let him (the Chaldean defender) who bends his bow bend it,Nor
        let him rise up in his coat of armor.So do not spare her young men;Devote
        her entire army to destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They shall fall down dead in the land of the Chaldeans,And wounded
        in her streets.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For neither Israel nor Judah has been abandonedBy his God, the Lord
        of hosts,Though their land is full of sin and guiltBefore the Holy One of
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Flee out of Babylon,Let every one of you save his life!Do not be
        destroyed in her punishment,For this is the time of the Lord\u2019s vengeance;He
        is going to pay her what she has earned.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Babylon has been a golden cup in the Lord\u2019s hand,Intoxicating
        all the earth.The nations drank her wine;Therefore the nations have gone
        mad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Babylon has suddenly fallen and is shattered!Wail for her [if you
        care to]!Get balm for her [incurable] pain;Perhaps she may be healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'We would have healed Babylon, but she was not to be healed.Abandon
        her and let each [captive] return to his own country,For her guilt and judgment
        have reached to heavenAnd are lifted up to the very skies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Lord has brought about our vindication and has revealed the righteousness
        of our cause;Come and let us proclaim in ZionThe work of the Lord our God!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Sharpen the arrows, take up the shields [and cover yourselves]!The
        Lord has stirred up the spirit of the kings of the Medes,Because His purpose
        concerning Babylon is to destroy it;For that is the vengeance of the Lord,
        vengeance [on Babylon] for [plundering and destroying] His temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Set up a signal on the walls of Babylon [to spread the news];Post
        a strong blockade,Station the guards,Prepare the men for ambush!For the Lord
        has both purposed and doneThat which He spoke against the people of Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '[O Babylon] you who live by many waters,Rich in treasures,Your end
        has come,And the line measuring your life is cut.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord of hosts has sworn [an oath] by Himself, saying,\u201CSurely
        I will fill you with men, as with [a swarm of] locusts [who strip the land
        clean],And they will lift up a song and shout of victory over you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He made the earth by His power;He established the world by His wisdomAnd
        stretched out the heavens by His understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When He utters His voice, there is a tumult of waters in the heavens,And
        He causes the clouds to ascend from the ends of the earth.He makes lightnings
        for the rainAnd brings out the wind from His storehouses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Every man has become stupid and brutelike, without knowledge [of
        God];Every goldsmith is shamed by the cast images he has made;For his molten
        idols are a lie,And there is no breath [of life] or spirit in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They are worthless (empty, false, futile), a work of delusion and
        worthy of derision;In the time of their inspection and punishment they will
        perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The Portion of Jacob [the true God of Israel] is not like these [handmade
        gods];For He is the Maker of all and the One who formed and fashioned all
        things,And Israel is the tribe of His inheritance\u2014The Lord of hosts
        is His name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CYou [Cyrus of Persia, soon to conquer Babylon] are My battle-axe
        and weapon of war\u2014For with you I shatter nations,With you I destroy
        kingdoms.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'With you I shatter the horse and his rider,With you I shatter the
        chariot and its driver,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'With you I shatter man and woman,With you I shatter old man and youth,With
        you I shatter young man and virgin,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'With you I shatter the shepherd and his flock,With you I shatter
        the farmer and his yoke of oxen,And with you I shatter governors and commanders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAnd I will [completely] repay Babylon and all the people of
        Chaldea for all the evil that they have done in Zion\u2014before your very
        eyes [I will do it],\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am against you,O destroying mountain [conqueror of
        nations],Who destroys the whole earth,\u201D declares the Lord,\u201CI will
        stretch out My hand against you,And roll you down from the [rugged] cliffs,And
        will make you a burnt mountain (extinct volcano).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "They will not take from you [even] a stone for a cornerstoneNor any
        rock for a foundation,But you will be desolate forever,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Lift up a signal in the land [to spread the news]!Blow the trumpet
        among the nations!Dedicate the nations [for war] against her;Call against
        her the kingdoms of Ararat, Minni, and Ashkenaz.Appoint a marshal against
        her;Cause the horses to come up like bristly locusts [with their wings not
        yet released from their cases].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Prepare and dedicate the nations for war against her\u2014The kings
        of Media,With their governors and commanders,And every land of their dominion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The land trembles and writhes [in pain and sorrow],For the purposes
        of the Lord against Babylon stand,To make the land of BabylonA desolation
        without inhabitants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The mighty warriors of Babylon have ceased to fight;They remain in
        their strongholds.Their strength and power have failed;They are becoming
        [weak and helpless] like women.Their dwelling places are set on fire;The
        bars on her gates are broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'One courier runs to meet another,And one messenger to meet another,To
        tell the king of BabylonThat his city has been captured from end to end;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And that the fords [across the Euphrates] have been blocked and [the
        ferries] seized,And they have set the [great] marshes on fire,And the men
        of war are terrified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel:\u201CThe Daughter
        of Babylon is like a threshing floorAt the time it is being trampled and
        prepared;Yet in a little while the time of harvest will come for her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CNebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has devoured me, he has crushed
        me,He has set me down like an empty vessel.Like a monster he has swallowed
        me up,He has filled his belly with my delicacies;He has spit me out and washed
        me away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "May the violence done to me and to my flesh and blood be upon Babylon,\u201DThe
        inhabitant of Zion will say;And, \u201CMay my blood be upon the inhabitants
        of Chaldea,\u201DJerusalem will say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord,\u201CBehold, I will plead your caseAnd
        take full vengeance for you;I will dry up her sea and great reservoirAnd
        make her fountain dry.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Babylon will become a heap [of ruins], a haunt and dwelling place
        of jackals,An object of horror (an astonishing desolation) and a hissing
        [of scorn and amazement], without inhabitants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "They (the Chaldean lords) will be roaring together [before their
        sudden capture] like young lions [roaring over their prey],They (the princes)
        will be growling like lions\u2019 cubs.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "When they are inflamed [with wine and lust during their drinking
        bouts], I will prepare them a feast [of My wrath]And make them drunk, that
        they may rejoiceAnd may sleep a perpetual sleepAnd not wake up,\u201D declares
        the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CI will bring them down like lambs to the slaughter,Like rams
        together with male goats.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CHow Sheshak (Babylon) has been captured,And the praise of the
        whole earth been seized!How Babylon has become an astonishing desolation
        and an object of horror among the nations!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sea has come up over Babylon;She has been engulfed with its tumultuous
        waves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Her cities have become an astonishing desolation and an object of
        horror,A parched land and a desert,A land in which no one lives,And through
        which no son of man passes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'I will punish and judge Bel [the handmade god] in BabylonAnd take
        out of his mouth what he has swallowed up [the stolen sacred articles and
        the captives of Judah and elsewhere].The nations will no longer flow to him.Yes,
        the wall of Babylon has fallen down!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CCome out of her midst, My people,And each of you [escape and]
        save yourselfFrom the fierce anger of the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Now beware so that you do not lose heart,And so that you are not
        afraid at the rumor that will be heard in the land\u2014For the rumor shall
        come one year,And after that another rumor in another year,And violence shall
        be in the land,Ruler against ruler\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Therefore behold (listen carefully), the days are comingWhen I will
        judge and punish the idols of Babylon;Her whole land will be perplexed and
        shamed,And all her slain will fall in her midst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Then heaven and earth and all that is in themWill shout and sing
        for joy over Babylon,For the destroyers will come against her from the north,\u201DSays
        the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Indeed Babylon is to fall for the slain of Israel,As also for Babylon
        the slain of all the earth have fallen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'You who have escaped the sword,Go away! Do not stay!Remember the
        Lord from far away,And let [desolate] Jerusalem come into your mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'We are perplexed and ashamed, for we have heard reproach;Disgrace
        has covered our faces,For foreigners [from Babylon] have comeInto the [most]
        sacred parts of the sanctuary of the Lord [even those places forbidden to
        all but the appointed priest].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CWhen
        I will judge and punish the idols [of Babylon],And throughout her land the
        mortally wounded will groan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "\u201CThough Babylon should ascend to the heavens,And though she
        should fortify her lofty stronghold,Yet destroyers will come on her from
        Me,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The sound of an outcry [comes] from Babylon,And [the sound] of great
        destruction from the land of the Chaldeans!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'For the Lord is going to destroy Babylon and make her a ruin,And
        He will still her great voice [that hums with city life].And the waves [of
        her conquerors] roar like great waters,The noise of their voices is raised
        up [like the marching of an army].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'For the destroyer is coming against her, against Babylon;And her
        mighty warriors will be captured,Their bows are shattered;For the Lord is
        a God of [just] restitution;He will fully repay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "\u201CI will make her princes and her wise men drunk,Her governors
        and her commanders and her mighty warriors;They will sleep a perpetual sleep
        and not wake up,\u201DSays the King\u2014the Lord of hosts is His name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts,\u201CThe broad wall of Babylon will
        be completely overthrown and the foundations razedAnd her high gates will
        be set on fire;The peoples will labor in vain,And the nations become exhausted
        [only] for fire [that will destroy their work].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'The message which Jeremiah the prophet commanded Seraiah the son
        of Neriah, the grandson of Mahseiah, when he went with Zedekiah the king
        of Judah to Babylon in the fourth year of his reign. Now this Seraiah was
        chief chamberlain or quartermaster [and brother of Baruch]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'So Jeremiah wrote in a single scroll all the disaster which would
        come on Babylon, [that is] all these words which have been written concerning
        Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Seraiah, \u201CWhen you come to Babylon, see
        to it that you read all these words aloud, "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "and say, \u2018You, O Lord, have promised concerning this place to
        cut it off and destroy it, so that there shall be nothing living in it, neither
        man nor animal, but it will be perpetually desolate.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'And as soon as you finish reading this scroll, you shall tie a stone
        to it and throw it into the middle of the Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "Then say, \u2018In the same way Babylon will sink down and not rise
        because of the disaster that I will bring on her; and the Babylonians will
        become [hopelessly] exhausted.\u2019\u2009\u201D Thus the words of Jeremiah
        are completed."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "  Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem; and his mother\u2019s name was Hamutal the daughter
        of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did that which was evil in the sight of the Lord like all that
        Jehoiakim had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For all this came about in Jerusalem and Judah because of the anger
        of the Lord, and [in the end] He cast them from His presence. And Zedekiah
        rebelled against the king of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now it came about in the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth month,
        on the tenth day, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came, he and all his army,
        against Jerusalem; and they camped against it and built moveable towers and
        siege mounds all around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the city was besieged until the eleventh year of King Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In the fourth month, on the ninth day of the month, the famine was
        so severe in the city that there was no food for the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the city was broken into, and all the soldiers fled. They left
        the city at night [as Ezekiel prophesied] passing through the gate between
        the two walls by the king\u2019s garden, though the Chaldeans were all around
        the city. They fled by way of the Arabah (the Jordan Valley). "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king and overtook Zedekiah
        in the plains of Jericho; and his entire army was scattered from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then they seized the king and brought him to the king of Babylon
        at Riblah in the [Syrian] land of Hamath [on the northern border of Israel],
        where he pronounced sentence on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The king of Babylon killed the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes;
        he also killed all the princes of Judah at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the king of Babylon blinded Zedekiah, bound him with bronze
        shackles and took him to Babylon and there he put him in prison [in a mill]
        until the day of his death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now in the fifth month, on the tenth day, which was the nineteenth
        year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, Nebuzaradan captain of the guard,
        who served the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He burned down the house of the Lord and the king\u2019s palace and
        all the houses of Jerusalem; every great house or important structure he
        set on fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So all the army of the Chaldeans who were with the captain of the
        guard broke down all the walls around Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took away into exile some
        of the poorest of the people, those who were left in the city [at the time
        it was captured], along with those who deserted to join the king of Babylon
        [during the siege] and the rest of the artisans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard left some of the poorest
        of the land to be vinedressers and farmers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the Chaldeans broke into pieces the pillars of bronze which belonged
        to the house of the Lord, and the bronze pedestals [which supported the ten
        basins] and the [enormous] bronze Sea, which were in the house of the Lord,
        and carried all the bronze to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They also took away the pots [for carrying away ashes] and the shovels
        and the snuffers and the bowls and the spoons and all the bronze articles
        used in the temple service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The captain of the guard also took away the [small] bowls and the
        firepans and the basins and the pots and the lampstands and the incense cups
        and the bowls for the drink offerings\u2014whatever was made of fine gold
        and whatever was made of fine silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The two pillars, the one [enormous] Sea (basin), and the twelve bronze
        bulls under the Sea, and the stands, which King Solomon had made for the
        house of the Lord\u2014the bronze of all these things was beyond weighing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Concerning the pillars, the height of each pillar was eighteen cubits
        (twenty-seven feet), and a line [an ornamental molding] of twelve cubits
        (eighteen feet) went around its circumference; it was four fingers thick,
        and [the pillar was] hollow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'A capital of bronze was on [top of] it. The height of each capital
        was five cubits (seven and one-half feet), with a lattice-work and pomegranates
        around it, all of bronze. The second pillar also, with its pomegranates,
        was similar to these. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'There were ninety-six pomegranates on the sides; and a hundred pomegranates
        were on the lattice-work all around.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the captain of the guard took [as prisoners] Seraiah the chief
        priest and Zephaniah the second priest and the three doorkeepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He also took out of the city one official who was overseer of the
        soldiers, and seven of the king\u2019s advisers who were found in the city,
        and the scribe of the commander of the army who mustered the people of the
        land, and sixty men who were still in the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them and brought them to
        the king of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then the king of Babylon struck them down and put them to death at
        Riblah in the land of Hamath. So Judah was led away into exile from its own
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the number of people whom Nebuchadnezzar took captive and
        exiled: in the seventh year, 3,023 Jews; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'in the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar, [he took captive] 832 persons
        from Jerusalem; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'in the twenty-third year of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuzaradan the captain
        of the [Babylonian] guard took captive 745 Jewish people; there were 4,600
        persons in all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now it came about in the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin
        [also called Coniah and Jeconiah] king of Judah, in the twelfth month, on
        the twenty-fifth of the month, Evil-merodach king of Babylon, in the first
        year of his reign, showed favor to Jehoiachin king of Judah and brought him
        out of prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He spoke kindly to him and gave him a throne above the thrones of
        the kings who were [captives] with him in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Jehoiachin changed his prison clothes, and he dined regularly at
        the king\u2019s table all the days of his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And his allowance, a regular allowance was given to him by the king
        of Babylon, a daily portion [according to his needs] until the day of his
        death, all the days of his life.
      comments: []
